title: apple pie ala mode shake
directions: Blend ingredients and serve.
Makes 2 servings.

title: simple broccoli salad
directions: In a bowl, combine broccoli, bacon and red pepper.
In another bowl, stir the mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar until smooth. Pour over broccoli mixture and toss to coat.

title: potatoes romanoff
directions: Grate potatoes on coarse grater.
Fold in sour cream, onions, 1 cup shredded cheese, salt and pepper.
Sprinkle remainder of cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: molasses wheat bread
directions: If using regular active dry yeast:
Scald milk; cool to 105°. Combine honey, molasses and yeast in warm water.
Cover and let stand until foamy, 10 minutes.
Add cooled milk, eggs, oil and salt.
Blend in oats, wheat germ and cereal.
Beat in whole wheat flour.
Stir in enough all-purpose flour to make a moderately stiff dough, adding more all-purpose flour if needed.
Knead on floured surface for 5 to 8 minutes.
Lightly oil bowl.
Place dough in bowl, turn so that oiled side is up.
Cover; let rise until doubled, about 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Punch dough down.
Half dough; let rest 10 minutes.
Shape into loaves; place in greased 8 x 4-inch or 9 x 5-inch loaf pans.
Cover and let rise until nearly double.
Bake in 350° oven for 40 minutes.
If bread top starts to get too dark, lay a piece of foil lightly on top.
Remove from pan immediately and grease top with margarine if desired, to keep crust soft.

title: freezer fruit salad
directions: Line 8 1/4-inch round pan with foil.
In bowl, combine cranberry sauce and pineapple.
In a smaller bowl, combine cream cheese, sour cream and powdered sugar.
Mix well.
Blend in cheese mixture into cranberry mixture.
Spoon into prepared pan.
Freeze until firm.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together; bake in 9 x 9 greased casserole at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Cream together first 3 ingredients; add egg and mix well.
Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Add raisins to mixture.
Bake in preheated 350° to 375° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cookies will be soft to touch.
Frost cookies while still warm.

title: meringue
directions: In small saucepan, mix cornstarch and cold water.
Stir in boiling water put over medium heat.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Set in cool water to hasten cooling.
Add lemon juice to egg whites and beat in electric mixer until whites stand in soft peaks.
Gradually add sugar, beating well after addition, then beat until whites stand in glossy peaks. Add cornstarch mixture all at once and beat until well blended.

title: sole venetian
directions: Wash and dry the sole. Rub with a paste made of mint, garlic, parsley and 1 tablespoon oil.
Saute the green onion in the remaining tablespoon oil. Add wine, water and seasonings.

title: rocky mountain cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on box, using 3 pans.
Grind raisins and pecans.
Mix powdered sugar, raisins, pecans, coconut, orange juice and salt.
Spread on cooled cake.
Store, covered, in cool place.

title: independence day salad
directions: This salad is great with barbecue and beans.

title: spinach and orange salad
directions: Toss spinach, oranges, onions and cheese in large bowl.
Add salad dressing and toss lightly.

title: mushroom-chicken casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, except cheese, in bowl.
Mix well. Spoon into buttered baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Bake for 3 minutes longer.

title: hobo dip
directions: Cut beef very fine.
Mix all ingredients together.
Hollow out bread; put dip in bread and cut up pieces of bread from the center to dip.

title: opal fullen's famous pound cake
directions: Cream margarine, Crisco, butter and sugar together.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk, beginning and ending with dry ingredients.
Add vanilla, coconut and almond extract.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan in preheated 325° oven for about 1 hour or until tests done.
This is my favorite cake!!!

title: cookie sheet cake
directions: Sift together flour, sugar and salt.
In a saucepan, combine margarine, oil, water and cocoa.
Cook, stirring until blended. Stir into flour mixture.
Stir soda into buttermilk and add eggs and vanilla.
Blend until smooth.
Pour into a greased and floured pan, 18 x 12 x 1-inch.
Bake in a 350° oven exactly 20 minutes. It fills the pan exactly.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix together the peanut butter, sugar and eggs.
Blend dry ingredients.
Mix with peanut butter mixture; chill 2 hours.
Roll into balls the size of walnuts.
Place 3 inches apart on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Dip fork in flour and press cookie ball. Bake at 350° until lightly browned.

title: mock margaritas
directions: In blender container, combine lemonade and limeade concentrates, powdered sugar and ice,
Cover; blend until of slush consistency.
Add club soda; stir gently.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together with mixer at medium speed. Pour into an unbaked pie crust and bake in 325° oven for 45 minutes or until set.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef, oil and onion.
Blend all ingredients. Simmer 30 minutes.

title: beans and beef
directions: Cook ground beef, onion, green pepper and celery until brown. Remove from heat; add other ingredients.
Mix well.
Place in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
(Optional:
Add a dash of garlic powder.)
Yield:
8 servings.

title: apple dumpling
directions: Cut apples in half and core them.
Wrap each half in rolled out biscuit.
Place in greased with butter pan.
Mix sugar, cornstarch, water and pour over apples; dot with butter.
Place in preheated oven 450°.
Bake until brown about 10 to 12 minutes.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.

title: frozen zucchini puree
directions: Melt 6 tablespoons butter. Add onions and cook 10 minutes. Add 1/4 cup water, then zucchini, bell peppers, garlic, salt and pepper. Cover and cook 3 minutes. Stir mixture and cook until soft. Add parsley, basil and tarragon. Cool.
Blend and put in 1 pint freezer containers and freeze.

title: peanut butter and jelly
directions: Noodles and cheese and then cook it and then you eat it.
Take a bowl and put noodels in it.
And then you cook it and then you eat it.
Yum?
Yum?

title: biscuits
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, sugar and cream of tartar.
Add margarine or shortening.
Add milk.
Stir with fork until moistened.
Knead.
Roll or pat dough 1/2-inch thick
Cut and place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake in oven at 450° until brown.

title: lime dessert
directions: Mix all together and serve.
Serves 8.

title: breakfast pizza(serves 6)
directions: Brown and drain sausage.
Separate dough into 8 triangles; place triangles with points toward center of greased 12-inch pizza pan.
Press to join and seal triangles.
Pinch up edge to form crust.
Sprinkle 1/2 hash browns over crust.
Follow with sausage, then other half of hash browns.
Beat eggs with milk, salt and pepper; pour over top.
Sprinkle with Cheddar followed by Parmesan.
Bake 25 minutes in 375° oven.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Mix pecans, graham crackers and sugar in bowl.
Add melted butter.
Spread mixture in a long 8 x 12-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Let cool.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Cook beef, onions and pepper until done.
Cook Kraft dinner as directed.
Put 3 or 4 slices of cheese on top.
Cook until bubbling.

title: shrimp roll-ups
directions: Mix ingredients together and spread 1/4 cup mixture on each tortilla; roll up tightly.
Wrap in plastic and refrigerate for 3 to 8 hours.
Slice into 8 pieces and serve.
Great for parties!

title: mulled cider
directions: Combine apple cider with jam in a nonaluminum saucepan.
Whisk to dissolve the jam, then simmer until the cider is warm.
Add lemon juice and pour into warm mugs.

title: baked sauerkraut and pork
directions: Roast piece of fresh pork until almost roasted.
Remove meat to plate; set aside.
Pour off fat, except 2 to 3 tablespoons; leave in pan.
Combine the remaining ingredients.
Mix all ingredients in roasting pan (except meat).
Bake for about 2 hours at 350°.
In the last half hour, heat pork in cabbage mixture. Enjoy.

title: sweet and sour barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients (except meat) in a saucepan and bring to a boil.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Makes enough sauce for 10 pork chops or chicken breasts.
Spoon sauce over meat; cover and bake in 375° oven for 1 hour or until tender.
Uncover for last 15 to 20 minutes of cooking.

title: chicken casserole spaghetti
directions: Boil and debone chicken. Using large pot, melt butter and saute onions; add celery and bell pepper, stirring until soft. Stir in both cans of soup, tomatoes and Ro-Tel tomatoes. Add deboned chicken and cooked spaghetti. Let simmer about 15 minutes. In large casserole dish, put a layer of this mixture and then a layer of cheese; repeat. Cover with foil so cheese will melt. Ready in 5 minutes.

title: pecan pie surprises
directions: Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: corn meal mix
directions: Sift dry ingredients together 3 times in large bowl.
Cut in shortening until very well blended.
Store in airtight container in a cool place.
Use within a month.

title: curry dip
directions: Add salt, garlic salt, Tabasco and lemon juice to taste. Serve with vegetables.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Spray a baking dish with nonstick cooking spray.
Dip chicken in spread. Coat with remaining ingredients. Place in pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: potato and leek soup with fried onions and chives
directions: Heat butter in saucepan over medium heat.
Cook chopped onion and chopped leeks until translucent, 5 to 7 minutes.
Add potato and broth.
Simmer, covered, until potato is very tender, 20 to 25 minutes.
Puree the soup in batches in blender; strain into saucepan.
Add milk, salt and white pepper, heat through.

title: raspberry meringue bars
directions: Cream together the butter, 1/2 cup of sugar and egg yolks. Add flour.
Pat dough in greased 15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch jelly roll pan and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes; let cool.
Spread raspberry jam on crust after cooking.

title: quick apple crisp
directions: Place 1/2 cup pie filling in each of 4 microwavable dessert dishes or cereal bowls.
Mix remaining ingredients with fork until crumbly.
Sprinkle about 2 tablespoons crumbly mixture over apples in each dish.
Cover with waxed paper and microwave on "High" until topping is melted and apples are hot, 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 minutes.
Let stand, uncovered, for at least 10 minutes to cool. Serve with ice cream, if desired.
Makes 4 servings.

title: apple cake
directions: Stir together first 6 ingredients.
Set aside.
In large bowl, combine apples, sugar, oil, walnuts, eggs and vanilla.
Add flour mixture.
Stir gently with wooden spoon to blend.
Turn into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until cake springs back when lightly touched.
Cool in pan on rack.
If desired, sprinkle with sifted powdered sugar.

title: alison's southern macaroni & cheese
directions: Combine milk, salt, pepper, butter, sugar, eggs, cheese and onion in blender.
Grease casserole dish and pour in sauce.
Drain macaroni and add.
Sprinkle bread crumbs on top.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Set casserole in pan of water while baking (keeps casserole moist).
Serves 6.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until light and frothy.
Add sugar, oil and vanilla; mix until thick.
Add zucchini and stir thoroughly.
Sift flour, cinnamon, baking powder, soda and salt; add to mixture.
Stir until smooth.
Add nuts and lemon juice.

title: mounds bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine 1 cup butter, flour, sugar, eggs, 3 tablespoons baking cocoa and salt.
Mix well.
Spread into greased 10 x 15-inch baking pan.
Bake 20 minutes.
Spread mixture of coconut and condensed milk on hot layer.
Bake 12 minutes. Cool on wire rack.
Combine 1/2 cup butter, 1/4 cup baking cocoa, milk, sugar and vanilla.
Mix until smooth.
Spread and cut into bars.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Combine and refrigerate 24 hours before using.
Stores in refrigerator several weeks.

title: russian chicken
directions: Mix the Russian dressing, soup mix and apricot preserves together in an 8 x 8-inch baking or casserole dish.
Place chicken in dish.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°, uncovered.
Serve over rice.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Crush wafers.
Beat eggs.
Mix all ingredients together well. Pour in a greased, floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 275° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: mock cooter soup
directions: Boil meat and water until one quart of liquid remains.
Add one pint of milk and 1/4 pound oleo.
Remove meat; allow to cool. Grind and return to stock.
Let it cook down a little more.
Add flour dissolved in cream.
Add seasoning.

title: herbie's ground beef stroganoff
directions: Melt butter; saute onion until golden brown.
Add the meat and garlic; simmer.
Stir in flour and spices.
Saute five minutes. Add soup and mushrooms.
Simmer, uncovered, ten minutes.
Stir in sour cream.
Serve over rice, noodles, or in patty shells.

title: granny mart's prune cake
directions: Bring sugar, milk, soda and syrup to soft ball stage.
Take off heat.
Add butter; mix and pour over cake.

title: pickle and ham roll-ups
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees.
Unroll one 8 oz. can refrigerated crescent dinner rolls and cut each piece in half along straight perforations.
Press diagonal perforations together on all pieces.
On lightly floured surface with floured rolling pin, roll each piece into a 9 inch by 6 inch rectangle.
Lightly spread mustard on each piece and top with ham slices, trimming slices to fit evenly on top of dough.
Cut each rectangle crosswise into 6 strips.
Cut each strip crosswise in half.
Place a sweet midget gherkin at one end of each strip and roll up jelly-roll fashion.
Place seam-side down on cookie sheet.
Bake 10 minutes or until golden.
Makes 48 appetizers.
To freeze up to one month, cool appetizers, wrap and freeze.
To serve, preheat oven to 375 degrees and bake frozen appetizers for 8 minutes or until heated through.

title: apple muffins
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Combine egg, milk and oil in mixing bowl.
Add dry ingredients.
Mix only enough to moisten. Fold in apples and nuts.
Fill greased muffin tins 2/3 full.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Yields 12 muffins.

title: terrific cheese broccoli casserole
directions: Melt butter with broccoli, onion and salt (no water); let this cook until broccoli has thawed.
Add undiluted soup, rice and Cheez Whiz; mix well.
Spray baking dish with Pam or rub with butter.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: lael's fudge
directions: Mix sugar, oleo, milk and salt together and cook over medium heat until soft ball forms in a cup of cold water.
Then add Nestle Bits, Marshmallow Creme (I use a mixer).
Add nuts and pour into a buttered pan.
Let cool and cut into squares.

title: guacamole
directions: In bowl, crush tomato with potato masher.
Peel avocados; remove pits.
Slice avocados into tomato; crush until well blended.
Add chiles, onion, vinegar, salt and pepper; mix well. Chill for 1 hour, covered.
Makes 8 servings.

title: oreo dessert
directions: Mix cookie and butter well by hand and press into a 13 x 9-inch pan to make crust.
Save 3/4 cup of cookie crumbs to sprinkle on top.
Blend remaining ingredients; spread on top of crust and sprinkle remaining crumbs on top.
Keep refrigerated.

title: texas pineapple cake
directions: Combine the first 7 ingredients in large loaf pan.
Stir to mix.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Remove and top.
Bring the 2/3 cup sugar, oleo and milk to a boil.
Pour over warm cake; sprinkle with the coconut.

title: quick chicken soup
directions: Mix all together and serve warm.

title: italian mushroom rice
directions: In large container, bring water to a boil.
Add salt and rice; stir.
Boil, uncovered, for 15 minutes.
Pour rice into colander and drain.
In separate saucepan, saute mushrooms in butter and wine.
Season with salt and pepper.
Add chopped parsley and let wilt slightly.
Toss drained rice with wine-mushroom mixture.
Put in greased 1-quart flat Pyrex dish.
Cover with foil.
Heat thoroughly in a 350° oven for about 20 to 30 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: iwegian carp
directions: Clean the carp (optional).
Nail carp to wooden shingle. Place in preheated oven at 350° for approximately 1/2 hour. Remove fixins' from oven.
Throw away carp and eat shingle.

title: apple crunch
directions: Butter bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Peel and slice apples into pan (2 to 3 inches deep).
Mix sugar, nutmeg and cinnamon. Sprinkle over apples.
Mix flour and brown sugar and then cut butter into it.
Put over apples.
Bake 15 minutes at 400°, then 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
Serve with ice cream or whipped cream.

title: emma kyle's old-fashioned tea cakes(makes 3 dozen)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat eggs and butter together.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Roll the dough on a large floured surface to 1/2-inch thick.
Cut with your favorite cookie cutter, or use a knife to cut into squares, about 3 x 3-inches. Place them on a cookie sheet, 2-inches apart.
Bake until brown (10 to 12 minutes).

title: chocolate angel food dessert
directions: Melt chocolate in double boiler.
Whip egg whites with sugar and salt until stiff.
Whip egg yolks.
Whip cream and vanilla. Add egg yolks to melted chocolate.
Put in large bowl and add egg whites and whipped cream.

title: overnight potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes.
Drain.
Mash using usual amount of milk and butter or margarine.
Use beater to mash.
Add onion salt, cream cheese and sour cream.
Beat with mixer.
Put in large casserole dish and cover overnight.
Next day heat oven to 350°.
Add grated cheese to top and place uncovered in oven for 30 to 45 minutes. Excellent for a crowd.

title: delicious chocolate pie
directions: Mix the first 2 ingredients together, then pour into pie crust.
Chill.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix cinnamon and sugar.
Add shortening and cream well.
Add eggs and beat.
Add apples and water mixing well.
Add flour and soda; continue mixing well.
Place in 13 x 9-inch lightly greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: chess squares
directions: Mix cake mix and softened butter.
Press into a lightly greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with nuts.
Mix the remaining ingredients and pour over the top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Let it cool, then cut into squares.

title: clam chowder
directions: Cut fine potatoes, onions and bacon.
Put in pan and cover with water.
Cook; when done add milk, clams, bay leaf, allspice and salt.
Let simmer for about 15 minutes and serve.
Note: Cost, including wood heat, = $0.2598 for 2 quarts in 1917 terms. From Telegram Conservation Cook Book, page 108.

title: baked beans
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Have ready a 3-quart casserole.
Mix all ingredients except bacon.
Pour into casserole and top with bacon. Bake 1 1/2 to 2 hours until juices have thickened.

title: gooey butter cake
directions: Melt margarine and beat one egg in margarine.
Mix in cake mix.
Put this in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix 2 eggs, cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Pour over cake mixture.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: praline cheese cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine crumbs, sugar and margarine. Press into bottom of a 9-inch spring-form pan.
Bake for 10 minutes.

title: cranberry-apple bars
directions: In large bowl, combine 2 cups flour, salt and brown sugar. With pastry blender, cut in margarine until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Remove 1/2 cup of mixture; set aside.
Press remaining mixture into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool 10 minutes.

title: cheese garlic biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients until a soft dough forms; beat vigorously for 30 seconds.
Drop dough by spoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes in a preheated 450° oven.
Should be golden brown.

title: rolo cookies
directions: Combine flour, cocoa and baking soda.
Beat sugar, brown sugar, butter, vanilla and eggs together.
Add flour mixture and 1/2 cup pecans.
Mix other 1/2 cup pecans with 1 tablespoon sugar and set aside.

title: rouladen(german meat dish)
directions: Cut round steak in 4 pieces.
Lay a strip of bacon lengthwise on each piece of round steak and a pickle spear crosswise.
Roll steak around pickle and secure with a toothpick.
Brown in bacon grease.

title: chicken liver hors d'oeuvres
directions: Sprinkle salt and pepper on livers. Wrap each liver with one half of bacon strip. Secure with toothpick. (If livers are real large, cut in half before wrapping.) Place on pan sprayed with vegetable spray. Place under broiler to brown on one side. Turn over and repeat. Watch closely-----these burn quickly.

title: salmon patties
directions: In a bowl, mix salmon, crushed crackers, egg, salt and pepper to taste.
Shape into patties (more crackers may be needed to make firm).
Fry in Crisco on both sides until crisp.
Serve with wilted lettuce and mashed potatoes.

title: minnesota egg and potato dish
directions: Spread hash browns on bottom of cake pan.
Spread meat on top. Spread mushrooms, olives and onions on next layer.
Spread cheese on top.
Combine eggs, milk, salt, oregano, pepper, parsley, garlic and dill.
Pour evenly over cheese.
Cover with foil. Bake at 425° for 45 minutes.

title: apple crunch pie
directions: Combine apple pie filling, brown sugar and cinnamon; add nuts and spread half of the mixture into pie shell.
Chill remaining apple mixture.
Pour milk and half and half into mixer bowl.
Add pie filling and beat at lowest speed until well blended.
Fold in whipped topping.
Spoon over apple mixture in pie shell.
Freeze 1 hour or chill 3 hours before serving.
Garnish with reserved apple mixture and whipped topping.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour and soda.
Then bananas and vanilla.
Add nuts last.
Bake at 350° until it test done.

title: oatmeal scotchies with rice krispies
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and set aside.
Mix butter, sugars, eggs and vanilla. Stir in oats, Rice Krispies, pecans, morsels and flour mixture, mixing well.
Bake at 375° for 7 to 8 minutes or just until edges are browned.
Let cool on cookie sheet for a couple of minutes before removing.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Form into 1-inch balls and bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes, until done.
Drain.
May be baked ahead of time and warmed in foil.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Soften ice cream.
Mix all ingredients together.
Place in 2 graham cracker crusts and freeze.
When ready to serve, warm chocolate syrup and pour over each slice.

title: "suga gravey" spaghetti sauce
directions: Saute chopped onion and chopped garlic in oil until they get soft.
Add tomato paste.
Using the tomato paste cans, fill them with water 2 times, pouring the water over the onion and paste.
Do the same with the sauce, except filling each can 1 time each.
Add sugar, salt, pepper, oregano, basil and parsley.
Bring this to a boil.
Turn down and simmer for 1 hour.
Stir periodically.

title: easy last minute punch
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Makes approximately 30 servings.

title: old time apple pie
directions: Line a 9-inch pie pan with pastry.
Mix sugar, salt, flour, butter, brown sugar, lemon juice and cinnamon.
Fill pie shell. Lay apple slices flat.
Dot with butter.
Roll out top crust and cut slits in several places for steam to escape.
Moisten edges of crust with cold water and adjust top crust on pie.
Pinch two crusts together to make a tight seal around pie.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat and bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes. Serve warm.

title: best macedonian strudel
directions: Soften yeast in water for
5 minutes and mix the flour, eggs, butter and salad oil.
Knead
very	well.
Divide into 4 equal parts.
Roll and
stretch dough until very thin.
Spread with your favorite filling,
such
as cheese, apples sprinkled with sugar, poppy seed, etc.

title: impossible quiche
directions: Lightly grease 8-inch square pan or 9-inch pie pan.
Sprinkle bacon, cheese and onion into pan.
Blend remaining ingredients until smooth and pour over cheese and bacon in baking dish.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until golden brown and knife inserted in middle comes out clean.
Let stand for 5 minutes before serving. Garnish with parsley sprigs and bacon crumbs.
Makes 6 servings.

title: vegetable quesadillas
directions: Saute zucchini, squash, mushrooms, onion and bell peppers just until crunchy.
Layer 1 large tortilla on bottom of baking sheet, then cheese above vegetable mixture.
Add more cheese and put tortilla on top.
Brush with butter.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes and slice pizza style.
Makes 4 quesadillas.

title: polenta with sausage sauce
directions: Bring salted water to a boil over medium heat.
Slowly pour in corn meal, stirring constantly, until thick, for at least 5 or 10 minutes.
Mixture will be very thick.
Pour into greased pie pan.
Serve hot with sauce or butter and grated cheese.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix meal, flour, both corns, oil, peppers, eggs and milk. Blend very good until very smooth.
Pour 1/2 of batter in greased pan (preferably cast-iron skillet).
Sprinkle 1 1/2 cups cheese over batter.
Pour rest of batter over top.
Sprinkle rest of cheese (1/2 cup) on top of last batter.
Bake in 400° oven for 45 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: caramel candy
directions: Combine ingredients in large pan.
Place on heat and cook to the hard ball stage.
Pour into buttered pan.
Let stand until cold.
Cut and wrap in wax paper.

title: wild rice salad
directions: Cook rice according to package directions, substituting seasoned salt.
Drain well; cool to room temperature.
Spoon into a large bowl; add chicken, grapes, water chestnuts and mayonnaise. Toss gently with a fork.
Cover and chill.
Just before serving, add cashews.
Serve on lettuce leaves or line a bowl with the leaves and fill with salad.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: vegetable cream cheese ball
directions: Mix to blend well.
Refrigerate until firm (about 2 hours). Shape into ball.
Roll in toasted sesame seed.

title: baked scallops
directions: Wash well and pat dry the Scallops.
Cream together the Mayonnaise, Milk, Salt, Pepper and Garlic Pepper.
Heat the creamy Mayonnaise first in the microwave oven.
Add Scallops to this mixture.
Top with Crumbs.
Bake at 350 for 15 minutes.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Spread crescent rolls on large cookie sheet and pinch edges together.
Bake according to package directions.
Mix cream cheese, sour cream, Ranch mix and salad dressing in large bowl. Spread mixture over thoroughly cooled rolls.
Garnish with chopped fresh broccoli, sweet red peppers and grated Cheddar cheese.
Cut into squares for serving.

title: chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Chill before serving. Yields 8 servings.

title: aunt sandra's hershey pie
directions: Soften candy bars in microwave or double boiler.
Mix with Cool Whip.
Pour in pie crust.
Let set.
Keep refrigerated.

title: chunky applesauce spread
directions: Place softened cream cheese in a bowl.
Add applesauce, raisins and cinnamon and sugar.
Mix well with a fork.
Serve with crackers (Pepperidge Farm butterfly crackers go well with this spread).

title: mushroom casserole
directions: Saute mushrooms with butter and garlic salt.
Line casserole dish with half the croutons.
Mix together in a bowl the flour, sour cream, milk, and mushrooms.
Pour this mixture on the croutons.
Pour remaining croutons on top of mushroom mixture. Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes, or microwave for 8 minutes.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Separate eggs, placing egg whites in a large bowl and yolks in another large bowl.
Let egg whites come to room temperature.
Add shortening and margarine to the egg yolks; beat at high speed until light and fluffy.
Add extract; beat until well blended. Beat in flour alternately with milk, beginning and ending with flour, with a mixer at low speed.
Add coconut; beat until well blended.
Beat egg whites just until stiff peaks form.
Fold into batter gently until well combined.
Turn into greased 10-inch tube or Bundt pan.
Bake at 300° for 2 hours.
Cool on wire rack for 15 minutes.
Remove from pan.

title: blintzes
directions: Let all ingredients stand one day in refrigerator.
Use one pullman size white sliced bread.
Trim crust and roll with pastry roller to flatten. Spread mixture on bread; roll up and dip in melted butter, cinnamon and sugar.
Cook in a 300° oven for 15 minutes.
Cut bread into bite size pieces.

title: strawberry jello salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in the 2 cups hot water; cool.
Add rest of ingredients, except sour cream.
Pour half of mixture in serving dish; chill until firm.
Spread layer of sour cream on top.
Add remaining half of Jell-O.
Chill until set.

title: cherry crisp
directions: Spread pie filling in 9 x 13 inch cake pan, sprinkle dry cake mix on top. Spread with fork to even it out. Sprinkle nuts on top of the cake mix. Pour melted margarine over all. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until golden brown.

title: sweet potatoes and opossum
directions: Clean opossum with damp cloth.
Rub inside and out with salt and pepper.
Lay possum in roasting pan on his back.
Baste with melted margarine.
Add 1/2 cup water; cover and bake at 350° for 3/4 to 1 hour.
Split peeled potatoes in half lengthwise.
Place around possum.
Add water as needed.
Bake for another 20 minutes, basting occasionally.
Uncover and let them finish cooking until golden brown and tender.

title: turkey casserole
directions: Chop almonds, celery, bell pepper and pimento.
Combine with turkey and all other ingredients, except potato chips.
Pour mixture into greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle potato chips on top of casserole and bake until chips are lightly browned.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: white chip chocolate cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Combine flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt. Sift this all together. Beat butter, sugar, brown sugar and vanilla until creamy. Beat in eggs. Then mix flour mixture in slowly. Stir in morsels and nuts. Dough will be very stiff. Drop by teaspoonfuls on a very lightly greased pan or a pan sprayed with Pam spray. Bake 9 to 11 minutes. Don't overbake. Take out of oven and let stand a few minutes. Then remove and cool. Makes 4 to 5 dozen, depending on size.

title: apple crisp
directions: Beat eggs until light and fluffy.
Gradually add sugar.
Sift flour, salt, and baking powder and add to egg mixture.
Mix well. Fold in nuts and apples.
Add vanilla. pour into a greased baking dish.
Bake 30 minutes at 350 degrees.
Serve with ice cream or whipped cream.

title: funnel cake
directions: Mix or beat until smooth.
Heat oil, about 1/2-inch, in skillet.
Hold
finger
over
hole	in bottom of funnel.
Pour batter in
funnel.	Hold over skillet and make a spiral shape. Fry until brown, turning once.	Drain on paper towel. Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: sour cream fruit salad
directions: Drain fruit well.
Mix all together and refrigerate 12 to 24 hours.

title: pretzelburgers
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together and shape into patties.
Melt margarine and add beaten egg.
Dip patties into egg and margarine mixture.

title: eggs benedict
directions: Split, toast and butter English muffins.
Cover with ham.
Top each half muffin with 1 poached egg.
Pour Hollandaise Sauce over all.
Makes 6 servings.

title: copper pennies
directions: Cook carrots until tender. Drain and cool. Mix onions and green pepper and add to carrots. Mix other ingredients and pour over carrots. Cover and refrigerate for 12 hours before serving.

title: vidalia onion pie
directions: Mix cracker crumbs with melted butter.
Place in a 9-inch pie pan. Bake at 350° for 8 minutes. Saute onions in oil until soft. Put into pie shell.

title: marinated broccoli
directions: Wash broccoli.
Use buds.
Mix ingredients and pour over broccoli.
Refrigerate for 24 hours.
Pour off oil and serve.

title: super beefy enchiladas
directions: Brown beef with onion.

Combine beans, beef, 1/2 cup cheese and onion. Set aside. Combine soups and enchilada sauce. Top each tortilla with 1 heaping tablespoonful of meat mixture and roll up. Place, seam side down, in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Pour sauce over and top with remaining cheese. Bake in a 350° preheated oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Spread cream cheese on bottom of plate.
Pour cocktail sauce over and spread evenly.
Sprinkle shrimp over sauce.
Serve with crackers.

title: impossible pie
directions: Put all ingredients into blender and blend 1/2 minute.
Grease and flour 10-inch pie pan or 9-inch square pan.
Pour batter into pan and sprinkle remaining 1/2 cup coconut over batter.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes until coconut is golden brown.
Chill overnight or at least several hours before cutting.
This recipe makes its own crust.

title: croutons
directions: Cut bread into 1/2 inch cubes.
Spread in a shallow baking pan.
Bake in 300° oven for 30 minutes or until dry and golden. (Each slice of bread makes about 3/4 cup).

title: pecan brittle
directions: Cook the first 4 ingredients over medium heat, stirring constantly, to 290°.
Stir in the soda. Stir quickly.
Mixture will foam.
Pour over greased cookie sheet.
Spread thin.

title: bread pudding
directions: Mix eggs, sugar and milk together.
Add bread and stir.
Pour in casserole dish.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and dot with butter. Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: four cheese pumpkin
directions: Place all ingredients except paprika and green pepper in food processor or large bowl of electric mixer.
Process until well combined.
Wrap in plastic wrap and refrigerate several hours for ease in shaping and to allow flavors to blend.
Shape into a pumpkin and sprinkle with paprika.
Use a piece of green pepper for the stem.
Let stand at room temperature for 20 minutes before serving with assorted crackers.

title: cherries in the snow
directions: Line bottom of large dish with graham cracker crumbs.
Mix Dream Whip as directed on the package.
Whip in the softened cream cheese, then add powdered sugar.
Beat well.
Spread this mixture over graham cracker crumbs.
Top with can of cherry pie filling. Place in refrigerator and chill for 8 hours, covered.

title: merry christmas cookies
directions: Cream butter
and
sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Mix small amount
of
flour with fruits and nuts.
Add flour, soda, spices and milk to creamed mixture.
Add fruits and nuts.
Drop by teaspoon
on
greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
This makes a big batch.

title: best pound cake
directions: Cream
margarine, sugar and Crisco well.
Add eggs, one at
a time.
Beat
well.
Add flavorings.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Add
milk
and flour, a little at a time, until all is used.
Bake
in
a
tube
cake pan that has been greased with
solid Crisco shortening and floured at 325° for 1 hour or longer, depending on how hot the oven cooks.

title: vegetable beef soup
directions: Cut beef into small pieces, removing fat.
Put into 6 quart soup pot.
Wash and dice potatoes (do not peel).
Add potatoes, onion, chopped celery and corn to soup pot.
Boil 1/2 to 3/4 hour. Add remaining ingredients, stir well.
Simmer 1/2 hour.

title: cabbage-potato soup
directions: Fry turkey with nutmeg and thyme.
Combine ingredients and cook until potatoes are tender.

title: fudgie scotch ring
directions: Melt chips and canned milk in top of double boiler. Stir until mixture begins to thicken.
Remove from heat. Add chopped nuts and vanilla.
Spoon mixture into halved nuts to form a ring.
Chill until firm.

title: kool-aid play dough
directions: Mix first four ingredients.
Add oil and water to dry ingredients.
Knead until very well mixed.
Let cool.
May feel sticky at first.
Just keep working it.
Keep in airtight container in refrigerator.

title: cheesecake
directions: Combine graham crumbs and butter for crust.
Prepare whipped cream and mix with cream cheese and sugar; spread over crust.
Top with pie filling.

title: chicken vegetable soup
directions: Boil chicken for 1/2 hour.
Add vegetables and seasonings to chicken.
Boil for 15 minutes, then simmer until vegetables are tender (about 5 minutes).

title: hamburger stew
directions: Brown meat with onion and drain.
Mix all ingredients together and simmer 30 minutes to an hour, stirring occasionally.

title: sour cream chicken enchiladas
directions: Boil chicken; chop. Heat soup, sour cream, chilies and onion together in saucepan. Fill tortilla with chicken, cheese and spoonful of sauce. Lay in casserole dish. Top with remaining sauce and cheese. Heat in oven at 350° for about 20 minutes or until cheese melts well.

title: my magic cake
directions: Grease and flour a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish or pan.
Spoon pie filling over cake.
Mix together sugar and melted margarine. Crumble mixture over pie filling.
You will see the magic when the cake is done.
Bake as directed on cake box.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix sugar, oil, vanilla, eggs, lemon juice and salt.
Then mix cinnamon, soda, apples, pecans and flour with first mixture and mix well.
Pour in Bundt pan for 1 hour and 15 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: jonas eddy
directions: Melt butter; add pork and onions and cook slightly.
Add other ingredients except cheese and noodles.
Cook for an hour, then add cheese.
Stir until blended.
Add cooked noodles and cook slowly for 1 hour.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: oyster stuffing
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in greased casserole and bake in preheated 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Serve with turkey gravy.

title: homemade spaghetti sauce
directions: For spaghetti you will need a 1 gallon pot and a large skillet.
Cook in the skillet the ground hamburger, turkey, Worcestershire sauce, garlic salt, pepper, bay leaves, Italian seasoning, red pepper, green peppers, mushrooms and onions until meat is well done.
Drain off any grease and dump into the 1 gallon pot with the rest of ingredients.
Cook on low for 4 hours. Stir every 15 to 30 minutes.
Spaghetti sauce is ready.
It is better served after the sauce sits in the refrigerator for one day.

title: sausage milk gravy
directions: Cook sausage until done.

Take sausage out of pan and leave grease in pan. Brown enough flour into grease pan together. Add salt and pepper according to taste. Add milk mixtures, a little at a time. Simmer and stir constantly until thickened. Add sausage. Make 16 biscuits out of Bisquick.

title: rock cornish hens
directions: Rub cavity of each hen with salt and butter and season outside with salt.
Tie wings and legs of bird to the carcass with cord. Either rotisserie on spit 12 inches from hot coals or roast. Baste frequently with glaze made by combining remaining ingredients.
Plan on 1 1/2 hours or a little more cooking time. Serves 4.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Mix all ingredients except chocolate chips.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan and top with chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° for 6 minutes.
Spread melted chips to cover top.
Cool until chocolate hardens.
Cut into squares.
Freeze.

title: jam cake
directions: Work all ingredients together.
Break eggs in mixture and work good.
Flour raisins before putting in mixture.
Dissolve soda in sour milk, adding last.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour or until done.
Bake in 3 round greased and floured pans.

title: pork chop risotto casserole
directions: In medium saucepan combine rice, beef broth and water.
Bring to boil, reduce heat and simmer 30 to 40 minutes.
Meanwhile, brown chops in skillet.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Stir carrots, onion, wine and seasonings into rice.
Turn into a slightly greased baking dish.
Arrange chops on top.
Bake covered for 1 hour.
Makes 4 servings.

title: green tomatoes parmesan
directions: Lightly sprinkle tomatoes with salt and drain on paper towels for 1 hour. Meanwhile, combine cornmeal, parmesan, flour and seasonings in a shallow plate. Dip each tomato slice in egg, then into cornmeal mixture. Fry tomatoes a few at a time in hot oil for 2 minutes per side or until golden. Drain on a paper towel lined rack. Serve hot. Four to six servings.

title: apple nut squares
directions: Cream oleo; add salt, sugar and beaten egg and continue beating until light and
creamy.
Add
dry ingredients and mix well.
Stir
in
apples and
nuts.
Mix
well.
Turn
into
a greased 7 x 11-inch pan.
Bake
at	350° for 40 minutes.
Cool in pan and cut into squares.
These keep exceptionally well.

title: apple-cinnamon cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Grease and flour 13 x 9 cake pan. Beat cake mix (dry), pie filling and eggs in large bowl on low speed 2 minutes. Spread half of the batter in pan. Mix sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle half of the mixture over

batter in pan. Spread remaining batter in pan. Sprinkle with remaining sugar-cinnamon mixture. Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool. Serve with whipped topping.

title: come-on-over cake
directions: Combine crackers, baking powder and nuts.
In another bowl, beat egg whites adding sugar and vanilla.
Fold cracker mixture into egg whites.
Press into a greased pan/dish and bake for 30 minutes at 300°.
Cool thoroughly.

title: spiced tea
directions: Combine all ingredients in saucepan.
Simmer 15 minutes and remove tea bags.
Serve hot in mugs.
Makes 3 quarts.

title: quick and easy chicken
directions: Place chicken in small roaster.
Cover with Swiss cheese.
Add salt and pepper.
Combine soup and wine.
Pour over chicken. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Serve with noodles or rice.
Serves 4.

title: spinach dip in pumpernickel loaf
directions: In a medium bowl, blend the vegetable soup mix with the sour cream, mayonnaise
and
lemon juice.
Stir in the spinach and green onions.
Chill.
Makes
about
cups.
Cut a round hole in center of
loaf	of
bread
and	put dip inside for serving. Use inside pieces and the other loaf for dipping.

title: texas straw hats
directions: In a large skillet, cook onion, celery and green pepper in hot oleo until tender, but not brown.
Add beef; brown lightly.
Add remaining ingredients except chips and cheese.
Simmer, uncovered, for 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Serve on bed of corn chips. Top with cheese.

title: hamburger soup
directions: In large Dutch oven brown ground beef, drain, stir in remaining ingredients.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 1 hour or until vegetables and barley are tender.

title: dressing
directions: Cook celery in oleo and water five to ten minutes.
Crumble together buns and cornbread.
Mix in poultry seasoning, celery and Croutettes.
Add chicken broth.
Put into 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Can put chicken on top if desired.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Uncover and bake 15 minutes more.

title: frozen fruit smoothie
directions: Put all ingredients in blender and blend on low speed until smooth.

title: buttermilk pecan chicken
directions: Rinse chicken breasts and pat dry.
Combine buttermilk and mustard in a bowl.
Add chicken, turn to coat and marinate for 1 hour.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Place pecans on plate.
Remove chicken from buttermilk mixture and shake off excess.
Dredge in pecans all over and place on baking sheet.
Season with seasoning salt and pepper.
Bake about 30 minutes, or until nicely browned and chicken tests done.

title: rhubarb sauce
directions: Mix altogether, except tapioca; cook until soft.
Add the tapioca; cook for 5 minutes.
It gets thick as it cools.

title: mother's fried chicken
directions: In a bowl, combine evaporated milk and egg.
In a separate bowl, combine flour, salt, pepper and garlic powder.
In a large skillet, heat oil on medium-high heat.
Dip chicken pieces in flour mixture, then evaporated milk and egg mixture and then back in flour mixture.
Fry in hot oil, turning frequently until done, about 35 to 40 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: midwest cranberry relish
directions: Combine cranberries and sugar in nonmetallic container and refrigerate overnight.
Drain the cranberry mixture, discarding the liquid.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into 8 x 8-inch pan.
Let stand in refrigerator for 24 hours.
May be doubled and placed in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: red cabbage
directions: Chop red cabbage.
Add apples (peeled and chopped).
Add onion (chopped).
Add butter, brown sugar, salt and 1 cup of water. Cook for 5 minutes, then drain.
Add vinegar and 1/2 cup of water. Simmer for 1/2 hour.

title: ham salad finger salads
directions: Chop ham and celery in food processor.
Put all ingredients in large bowl and mix thoroughly.
Spread each slice of bread with soft oleo to seal out moisture.
If sandwiches cannot be made on day needed, make sandwiches and put back in bread wrappers day before.
Just before serving, trim off crusts with electric knife and cut into finger sandwiches.

title: dirty rice
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Put margarine in skillet.
Add rice and cook 3 to 5 minutes to brown.
Pour into casserole dish; add onion and soups.
Pour mushrooms on top.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes.

title: skillet beef and macaroni
directions: Cook ground beef and onion in skillet until browned. Drain well. Stir in tomato sauce, corn, macaroni, chili powder and seasoned salt. Simmer, stirring occasionally, 5 to 10 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Stir in Cheddar cheese.

title: linda's luscious lemon pie
directions: Make custard in microwave.
Combine sugar, lemon rind, butter, juice, milk and egg yolks in a large 8 cup glass measuring cup. Stir well and cook on high for 2 minutes.
Stir and repeat until bubbly and thick, approximately 10 minutes.
Cover with plastic wrap and cool to room temperature.
Fold in sour cream.
Put in pie shell and chill two hours before serving.

title: lemon cookies
directions: Combine cake mix, egg and Cool Whip in large mixing bowl.
Drop dough by the spoonful in small bowl of confectioners sugar.
Shape into a ball and place on cookie sheet.

title: 7 up cake
directions: Blend together and then add a 10-ounce bottle of 7UP pop. Bake at 350° for 35-40 minutes in 9 x 13 pan.

title: mackie's cracked sugar cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease two cookie sheets. Cream sugar and butter together until light.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Sift together the measured sifted flour, baking soda and cream of tartar; then fold into the butter-sugar mixture.
Form dough into walnut-sized balls.
Place two inches apart on cookie sheets.
Do not flatten.
Bake for about 11 minutes until tops are cracked and just turning colors.
Cool on wire racks.
Makes 4 dozen.
If desired, you may sprinkle a mixture of sugar and nutmeg on top of cookie while hot.

title: quiche lorraine
directions: Line unbaked shell with 12-inch square of aluminum foil.
Fill with rice or dried beans or peas.
Cover rim of shell with edges of foil.
Bake in preheated oven at 450°
until lightly browned at edges, 10 to 15 minutes.
Lift out foil and rice.
Cool on wire rack.

title: johnny cake(corn bread)
directions: Bake either in an 8 x 8-inch pan or in muffin tin at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: easy veggie dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and blend thoroughly.
Chill for at least 2 hours.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.
Serve with raw vegetables.

title: traditional christmas bread(romanian)
directions: Melt sugar in warm milk with vanilla in a saucepan.
When the sugar is melted, add the walnuts and keep stirring.
After a few minutes of boiling, and after filling has thickened, remove from heat and add rum.
When the filling is cold, roll a sheet of dough about 1/2 inch thick.
Uniformly spread the filling on top and roll like a jelly roll.
Grease a bread pan and place the roll inside. Let rise.
Bake in oven until done.
(Temperature and baking time was not provided.)

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together in large mixing bowl.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes (until pie is set).

title: artichoke veggie dip
directions: Drain and chop artichoke hearts.
Mix everything together and put in small baking pan.
Bake at 350° until browned.
Serve as a dip for raw veggies or crackers.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Melt margarine and mix with stuffing. Place half of stuffing in dish.
Put in all other ingredients.
Top with rest of stuffing.
Bake until bubbly, approximately 1/2 hour.

title: sausage dip
directions: Brown sausage and drain grease.
Add flour and salt until it thickens.
Add milk and steam for 5 minutes.
Remove sausage mixture from heat.
Melt oleo and saute onions.
Add mushrooms, soy sauce, Worcestershire sauce and garlic salt.
Mix well.
Add sour cream and stir.
Serve in chafing dish with Melba rounds. This can be made ahead of time and frozen.

title: hot fudge sundae pudding cake
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients, stirring until blended.
Spread in 9-inch baking pan sprayed with cooking spray.
Sprinkle with brown sugar and 1/4 cup cocoa, mixed together.
Pour water over mixture.
Do not stir.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: chocolate pecan pie
directions: Mix chocolate, butter, brown sugar, egg, vanilla and nuts. Fill pie shells with mixture and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: pizza burger
directions: Brown ground beef with small amount of oil in skillet, stirring.
Add tomato sauce, salt and garlic salt; simmer for 5 minutes.
Add stuffed olives.
Simmer 5 additional minutes. Remove from stove and stir in diced Mozzarella cheese.
Cut eye-shaped holes in the top of the French rolls and with a spoon, scoop out the center.
Fill with meat mixture and wrap in foil. Place in 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.
These may be frozen. When heating frozen ones, it will take 30 to 45 minutes in the oven to heat thoroughly.

title: texas seafood sauces
directions: Combine ingredients.
Makes 1 1/2 cups sauce and is great served with crab claws or baked fish.

title: prune nut cake
directions: Mix ingredients in order listed.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Preheat oven.

title: old fashioned egg custard pie
directions: Beat eggs until light and foamy.
Add sugar and salt; blend well.
Add milk and vanilla.
Line a 9-inch pie pan with pastry. Brush with melted butter. Pour custard into unbaked pastry and sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Reduce to 325° and bake 25 minutes or until a knife inserted in middle comes out clean.

title: mushroom rice
directions: Grease a 1 1/2 or 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle in the raw rice.
Saute the green onions in the olive oil until they are soft.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil and then pour over the rice and stir.
Cover the casserole and bake 25 to 30 minutes at 375° until the rice is tender.

title: potato casserole
directions: Boil potatoes in skins until almost done.
Peel and grate. Heat soup and 1/4 cup butter; blend in sour cream, onions and cheese.
Stir in potatoes.

title: sun-dried tomato and feta pasta
directions: Combine first four ingredients and set aside.
Cook pasta according to directions.
Toss with tomato mixture.
Serve warm or cold.

title: blueberry zucchini muffins
directions: Beat eggs until foamy; add oil, sugar, vanilla and zucchini. Add all dry ingredients.
Blend well; add nuts and blueberries. Spoon into muffin tins.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
I like to use 2 1/2-inch bake cups.
Fill 3/4 full.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: sweet and sour cabbage
directions: Cut cabbage and onions into chunks; put in large pot with 1/2 cup water.
Add salt, pepper and tomatoes.
Cook, stirring often, until cabbage is soft.
Cut bacon into tiny squares; fry until crispy.
Drain about 1/3 of bacon grease; add flour to grease. Fry until flour is brown.
Make sure cabbage is soft.
Add vinegar; mix well.
Take about 1 1/2 cups juice from cabbage; add to bacon.
Cook bacon mixture until thick; add to cabbage.
Add vinegar to taste.

title: beef bake
directions: Brown
ground beef; drain.
Prepare macaroni and cheese by directions	on box.
Combine beef, soup and macaroni.
Pour into baking dish
and top with potato chips.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cinnamon bars
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Combine flour and cinnamon; gradually add to creamed mixture.
Stir in egg yolk and vanilla until well blended.
Spread dough in a greased 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch baking sheet and pat down.
Brush egg white on top of dough; sprinkle nuts over dough.
Press nuts down.
Bake in preheated 300° oven for 30 minutes.
Cut into bars and remove from sheet to cool. Makes 2 dozen bars.

title: italian wedding soup
directions: In small bowl, combine beef, crumbs, egg, onions and bouillon. Shape into 40 meatballs.

title: garlic grits
directions: Cook grits until thick.
Stir in butter and cheese.
Mix egg, milk and pepper together.
Add to grits.
Top with sharp grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 6.

title: garlic bread oreganotto(pane oreganotto)
directions: Cut bread in halves lengthwise.
Place halves on baking sheet. Soften butter and
blend with garlic.
Spread on bread and continue
adding ingredients
in
order,
ending
with
a sprinkle of olive oil all over
bread.
Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes until light
browned
and
bubbly.
To
serve,
cut diagonally. Makes 5 to 6 servings.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Drain the sauerkraut 15 minutes in a colander.
Cut with scissors into 1-inch pieces.
Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl.
Cover and store in the refrigerator for 24 hours. This salad will store indefinitely.

title: orange banana shake
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Serve cold.

title: texas sour cream enchiladas
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown ground beef and all ingredients except grated cheeses and heat.
Melt 2 tablespoons of butter in pan and heat tortillas until soft, one at a time.
Then add meat mixture by spoonfuls onto shell.
Sprinkle on cheese.
Roll up. Place in greased baking dish. Pour rest of mixture over top of rolled tortillas and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: cheese crisps
directions: Cream butter; add grated cheese.
Add flour, Tabasco sauce and Rice Krispies.
Roll in small balls the size of a quarter. Flatten with fork.
Sprinkle with paprika; bake 10 to 12 minutes in 350° oven.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix chicken, celery, almonds, green pepper, pimento, onion, salt, lemon juice and mayonnaise.
Turn into buttered casserole. Top with cheese and potato chips.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Top with cheese and potato chips.
Bake 10 more minutes.
Serves 6.

title: cornflake chews
directions: Bring sugar and syrup to boil. Add butter and peanut butter. Stir until able to pour over cornflakes. Drop by spoonfuls of desired size onto greased cookie sheet.

title: braised beef short ribs
directions: Season the ribs with salt and pepper in an oven-proof pan with a lid.
Heat the oil on the stove over medium-high heat.
Add the ribs and brown on all sides, then remove the ribs from the pan. Add the onion and garlic and saute for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Stir in the chicken broth, wine and tomato paste, scraping the bottom of the pan to loosen any vegetables stuck there.
Return the meat to the pan.
Add the bouquet garni and the olives.
Cover and cook in a preheated 350° oven for 1 1/2 to 2 hours, until the meat almost falls off the bone.
To serve, transfer the meat, broth and olives to soup bowls, discarding the bouquet garni.

title: cheesy onion bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cut French bread in half lengthwise. Combine shredded cheese, mayonnaise and onions.
Spread on cut side of bread.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and oregano.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake.
Slice and serve.

title: ernestine's coconut pie
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch together.
Add milk, water, egg yolks and vanilla.
Mix well.
Cook these ingredients until thickened, then add coconut.
Pour mixture into 2 baked pie crusts.
Put meringue on top and brown in 400° oven.

title: 7-layer salad
directions: Put ingredients in layers in a large salad bowl.
Combine the Miracle Whip dressing, mayo and sugar and spread over top of salad.
Refrigerate overnight.
Sprinkle with the bacon and cheese.
Toss just before serving.

title: rich sweet dough
directions: Scald milk in small saucepan over medium heat.
Stir in sugar, salt and margarine.
Cool to lukewarm.
Measure warm water into large bowl that can be covered.
Stir in yeast until dissolved. Stir in cooled milk mixture, beaten egg and half the flour.
Beat by hand until smooth.
Stir in remaining flour and beat until smooth.
Batter will be stiff.
Cover tightly and refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Dough may be kept for up to 3 days.
Use for tea rings, dinner rolls or sweet rolls.

title: florentine casserole
directions: In skillet, brown meat; drain fat.
Stir in tomato paste, water, onion, salt and pepper.
Simmer, uncovered, 10 minutes. Stir occasionally.

title: corn, tomato and summer squash soup
directions: In a large deep pot, heat oil; add garlic and onion and saute until softened.
Add broth, tomatoes, corn and chile peppers. Simmer for 15 minutes.
Add zucchini and basil and simmer for 5 minutes more.
Serve hot, passing garnishes.

title: popovers
directions: Mix together in bowl with spoon; disregard small lumps.
Use muffin pans (well greased).
Fill 3/4 full.
Put in cold oven; set at 450° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: tater crisp fried fish
directions: Rinse fish fillets under cold water and pat dry.
In shallow dish, beat eggs.
In another dish, combine potato flakes, parmesan cheese and oregano.
Dip fillets in eggs and coat with potato flakes mixture.

In large skillet, heat oil over medium heat for 1-2 minutes. Fry fish in skillet until crust is golden brown and fish flakes easily with fork (about 3-5 minutes) on each side. If fish sticks to pan, add more oil.

title: tortilla soup
directions: *Enough to line bottom of bowl.

title: peanut butter oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients except peanut butter, vanilla and oats and bring to a boil.
Boil for 2 minutes and remove from heat.
Add peanut butter and vanilla and mix thoroughly.
Next, add oats to mixture and mix thoroughly once again.
Use a spoon to spoon mixture onto wax paper and allow to harden.
Number of cookies yielded depends on their size.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown hamburg and onion.
Add tomato paste, water, Ragu, salt, oregano and pepper.
Simmer for half an hour while cooking lasagna noodles.
Put in layers in a casserole - sauce, cheese and noodles.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Simmer beef in butter until completely gray in color, covered. When beef is tender, add mushrooms and simmer for time to cook them.
Add sour cream and serve.
Add salt according to taste. Serve over noodles or rice.
Serves about 6 to 8 people.

title: pizzelles
directions: Beat eggs, adding sugar gradually.
Beat until smooth.
Add cooled, melted margarine and vanilla.
Sift flour and baking powder and add to egg mixture.
Dough will be sticky enough to be dropped by spoon.
Bake between 20 and 30 seconds on Pizzelle iron.

title: poncho cheese dip
directions: Cut cheese into chunks and place in blender. Boil rotel, water and seasoning, pour over cheese in blender. Blend on highest speed until mixed and smooth.

title: pie filling cake
directions: Cream margarine, sugar and vanilla; add eggs and mix well. Add flour and baking powder and mix well.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch cake pan and drop pie filling 1 inch apart.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate candies
directions: Put everything except the marshmallows in a double boiler. Melt and mix well.
Put 3 small marshmallows in the bottom of each paper cup.
Pour the chocolate mixture over this until almost full.
Yields about 3 dozen.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients in mixing bowl.
Beat in next 2 ingredients at medium speed.
Add sifted dry ingredients.
Beat all together until smooth.
Mix in nuts with wooden spoon.
Pour into 2 large, greased and floured bread pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
(Check bread with toothpick until it comes out clean.) Remove onto wire rack.

title: crabmeat casserole
directions: Mix together and pour into greased casserole. Bake uncovered at 300° for 1 hour.

title: orange caramel sticky buns
directions: Combine all ingredients, except biscuits, in a 9 x 5-inch glass loaf pan.
Microwave for about 1 1/2 minutes on High, or until the butter is melted.
Stir well.
Open and separate biscuits; place in sugar mixture, turning to coat.
Arrange biscuits on their sides.
Microwave for 3 minutes on simmer. Microwave for 1 to 1 1/2 minutes on High, or until biscuits are no longer doughy.
Let stand 2 minutes.
Invert onto a plate.

title: imperial chicken roll-ups
directions: Split and skin chicken breasts. Combine butter and garlic, stir well and set aside. Combine bread crumbs, cheese, parsley, salt and pepper, stir well. Dip chicken in butter mixture then coat with crumb mixture. Fold long sides of chicken together, bring short ends over and secure with a toothpick. Place chicken rolls seam side down in a greased pan, sprinkle with lemon juice and paprika. Bake at 350° for one hour or until done. Yield: 8 servings.

title: cheese ball
directions: Season to taste with onion soup mix, if desired.

title: cream of pertater soup
directions: Boil peeled pertaters 10 minutes and throw water away.
Now put in fresh water and add beef broth or extract (you can use one bouillon cube).
Add all the seasonin and cook until pertaters are tender.
Press your product through a strainer (sieve).

title: curried fruit
directions: Combine butter or margarine, sugar and curry powder and bring to a boil.
Drain the fruit and arrange it in a 2-quart baking dish.
Pour hot sauce over fruit.
Garnish with cherries.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serve hot.
Very good with poultry, curried ham and pork.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: cucumber and orange salad
directions: In a bowl, toss together chopped cucumber, drained orange sections, French or cucumber salad dressing and poppy seed. Cover and chill in the freezer for 8 minutes.
Sprinkle lightly with pepper, if desired.
Serves 4.

title: chili pie
directions: Spread 2 cups of chips in baking dish.
Arrange chopped onion and 1/2 of cheese on chips.
Pour chili over onion and cheese. Top with remaining Fritos chips and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes until hot.

title: ham 'n swiss loaf
directions: Set aside 1 cup flour.
Mix remaining flour, sugar, salt and yeast.
Heat water, mustard and margarine to 125° to 130°.
Stir into flour mixture.
Mix enough reserved flour to make soft dough. Knead 20 to 30 times.
Roll dough on greased cookie sheet. Sprinkle on ham, cheese and pickle down center third of dough length.
Fold into loaf shape and let rise 30 minutes.
Brush loaf with egg.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Stir together pineapple, Cool Whip, milk and lemon juice until well blended.
Pour into 2 pie crusts and refrigerate for several hours.

title: cheese chips
directions: Blend ingredients;
form into log and chill.
Slice and bake at 375° for about 8 minutes.

title: quick nut bread
directions: Blend sugar, eggs, and milk.
Beat hard, stir in nuts. Bake on greased pan at
350 degrees for 45 minutes.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Wash chicken breasts; cook, covered in water, until tender. Remove from broth.
Saute celery and onion in margarine.
Add soups, milk, and chicken broth.
Pour this mixture into a 9 X 13-inch pan.
Tear chicken into bite-size pieces and place on soup mixture.

title: glorified cabbage
directions: Chop cabbage; boil until very tender. Cook onion in butter until wilted. Add cheese in chunks. Allow to melt over low heat. Stir in soup and blend well over low heat. Stir in drained cabbage and mix well. Add bread crumbs. Mix well.
Season to taste with salt. Place in 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. Sprinkle bread crumbs on top. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: rice casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Pour soups into 9-inch casserole dish. Add rice and stir to distribute evenly among dish.
Slice margarine evenly over the top.
Cover and bake for 1 hour.

title: pepper corn brandy steak
directions: Sprinkle pepper on both sides of steak (press in).
Let stand for 30 minutes.
Place steaks on grill 4 to 6 inches from bed of coals.
Cook, turning once, 5 minutes for rare.
Place meat on platter.
Heat and ignite brandy.
Pour over steaks.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix together all except nuts and brown sugar.
Pour in 8-inch square pan (sprayed with Pam).
Mix together chopped nuts and brown sugar, then spread over top.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: delicious disappearing bars
directions: Melt sugar, syrup and peanut butter in 5-quart saucepan. Remove from heat; stir in corn flakes. Spread in 913 x 9-inch cake pan and sprinkle with chocolate chips. Let set for half an hour before serving.

title: dutch apple dream
directions: Combine 1/2 cup nuts and graham crackers.
Mix well.
Add melted margarine; blend well.
Press mixture into bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: sprout and spinach salad
directions: In a small bowl stir yogurt, soy sauce, pepper and garlic; cover and chill.
Fix spinach; don't use stem sprouts.
Fry bacon; crumble.
In a bowl, put spinach, sprouts, bacon, water chestnuts and mushrooms.
Cover and chill for 4 to 6 hours.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients first, then add remaining ingredients; bring to boil, stirring frequently.
Boil 10 to 20 minutes until filling thickens.
Pour into baked pie crust and top with meringue.
Makes two pies.

title: ham delights
directions: Blend margarine, poppy seed, Worcestershire sauce, mustard and onion. Split packages of party rolls. Spread top and bottom with margarine mixture. Place ham and Swiss cheese on rolls. Bake at 400° for 10 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: easy chewy brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan. Stir together cake mix, eggs, melted butter and nuts, if desired, in bowl until well blended. Mixture will be stiff. Spread in pan. Bake for 20 to 25 minutes or until set in the center. Let cool. Spread with prepared icing or sprinkle with powdered sugar. Cut into squares. Yield: 24 brownies.

title: fig bars
directions: Mash figs and butter in small bowl. Add 1 teaspoon vanilla. Set aside.

title: mexican shrimp and vegetable kebabs
directions: In a bowl or self-closing plastic bag, combine marinade ingredients.

title: chocolate chip cheese bars
directions: Cut cookie dough in half. For crust, press half of the dough onto the bottom of a greased 8-inch square baking pan. In a mixing bowl, beat cream cheese, sugar and egg until smooth. Spread over crust. Crumble remaining dough over top. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until a toothpick inserted near the center comes out clean. Cool on a wire rack. Refrigerate leftovers.

title: round steak
directions: Cut round steak into small pieces.
Cover with flour, salt and pepper.
Brown meat with onion in small amount of oil.
Drain off oil, then add soups and sour cream.
Simmer, stirring often, until meat is tender.
Serve over egg noodles.

title: quick ham pie
directions: Place ham in
bottom of baking dish.
Melt margarine and pour over ham.
Add
mushrooms.
Sift
together dry ingredients and mix well with 1 cup of milk.
Pour over ham.
Heat soup and 1 1/2 cups of
milk,
only long enough to combine milk and soup well.
Pour over all.
Bake
at 350° for 45 minutes.
Makes its own crust.

title: sausage and noodle casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into a greased baking dish.

title: grandma's applesauce cake
directions: Measure and sift flour, soda, salt and spices.
Cream the shortening; add sugar.
Beat after each addition of flour.
Add applesauce, raisins and nuts.
Pour into a tube pan (greased) and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: instant boiled custard
directions: Blend all ingredients well with electric mixer.
Store in glass container.
Three recipes yields 2 gallons.

title: mom's new year shrimp dip
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together and add shrimp.
Chill for several hours or overnight.
Serve with ripple potato chips.

title: taffy apple salad
directions: Drain pineapple, saving juice.
To the juice, add slightly beaten egg, sugar, cornstarch and vinegar.
Micro on High 4 minutes or until thick.
Cool completely and mix with other ingredients.

title: green beans baked lucette
directions: Alternate layers of drained beans (save 1/4 cup bean liquid) and onions in a baking dish.
Mix mushroom soup and bean liquid and pour over vegetables. Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake in oven at 350° about 30 minutes.

title: sugar-free chocolate chip cookies(diabetic)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. With electric mixer, cream first 7 ingredients until fluffy.
In separate bowl, mix flour and baking soda.
Add dry ingredients to creamed mixture and beat until well blended.
Stir in chocolate pieces.
Drop batter by teaspoonfuls onto cookie sheet which has been lightly coated with cooking spray. Bake for 12 minutes until golden brown. Yields 4 dozen cookies.

title: barbecue hamburger - sloppy joes
directions: Cook meat until brown; drain.
Add onion, celery and green pepper and cook until tender.
(When making a large amount, cook the vegetables in a little water and add it and the juice to the meat.)
Add remaining ingredients and simmer for at least 20 minutes or desired consistency.
Serve on buns.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream butter and cheese until smooth.
Add eggs, 1 at a time. Blend in sugar until smooth.
Add flour and flavorings.
Blend well.
Do not overbeat.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: peanut butter kisses
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Have cookie sheets ready.
With a wooden spoon, combine peanut butter, sugar and eggs.
With floured hands, roll into 1 1/4-inch balls.
Place 1 1/2-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 12 to 14 minutes until appear dry and cracked. Remove and immediately place a Kiss in each.
Cool on sheet 1 to 2 minutes.

title: kayla's kookies and kream
directions: With electric mixer cream together pudding and milk; add sugar, whipped topping and cream cheese.
Spread half of cream mixture on bottom of glass dish, next cookie pieces.
Top with other half of cream mixture.
Chill in refrigerator for about 1 to 2 hours.

title: country beef and vegetables
directions: In a 10 inch skillet over medium high heat, cook beef until browned.
Stirring to separate meat.
Spoon off fat.
Stir in soup and worcestershire and vegetables.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low.
Cook 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Serve over rice, garnish with cheese.

title: pork chop skillet meal
directions: Melt shortening and brown pork chops over high heat.
Brown well on both sides. Add salt.
Place a slice of onion and 1 pepper ring on each pork chop.
Place 1 tablespoon rice in each ring.
Pour tomatoes over the meat; add celery.
Cover and simmer for 1 hour.
Yields 4 servings.

title: creamy orange-pineapple salad
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving juices.
Add water to make 2 cups; heat to a boil.
Add boiling liquid to jello and cream cheese; beat with rotary beater until smooth.
Cool, stirring occasionally.
Whip cream.
Fold cream, grated carrot and pineapple into cooled jello.
Pour into molds.
Chill until firm.

title: quick chocolate cherry cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to directions. Gently fold in cherry pie filling. Pour into 9X13 pan and bake according to package.

title: mexican appetizer platter(makes about 20 servings)
directions: Spread refried beans on oval serving platter.
Layer avocados, onions, lettuce, tomatoes, sour cream and Cheddar cheese over beans.
Garnish with olives.
Cover and refrigerate at least 4 hours.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Place chicken in baking dish.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Mix soups in bowl; pour over chicken.
Sprinkle onion soup mix over all.
Add wine.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: weight watchers soup
directions: Cook 2 1/2 hours, then add 6 to 8 packages of Equal.

title: banana nut loaf
directions: Mix thoroughly the sugar, shortening and egg.
Stir in milk and bananas.
Sift together and stir in flour, baking pwd. and salt. Blend in the nuts.
Pour into well greased 9 by 5 by 3 in. loaf pan.
Let stand 20 minutes before baking.
Bake at 350° about 70 minutes or until toothpick stuck in center comes out clean.
(Crack in top is characteristic.)

title: aunt genna's meat loaf
directions: Saute onions in butter.
Mix stuffing and bouillon cubes (boiled with water) in bowl.
Add onions, beef, cheese, parsley, egg, salt and pepper; blend.
Form in loaf.
Dot with butter. Bake at 375° for 1 hour and 45 minutes until brown.
Add tomato sauce and oregano.
Bake 1/2 hour.

title: cucumber sandwich spread
directions: Cut cucumber in quarters; remove seeds.
Shred; drain on paper towels.
Combine all ingredients and mix until well blended. Chill.

title: hamburger vegetable soup
directions: Brown ground meat in Dutch oven.
Drain fat.
Add the onion and cook until tender.
Add the other ingredients and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer until vegetables are tender (about 45 minutes).

title: annie wingate's chicken ravioli
directions: Cook chicken tender with celery and 1 onion, cut into small pieces.
Save stock.
Put bacon fat in large skillet and brown other onion.
Add ground beef and cook until meat is done.
Add tomatoes and fill can with broth.
Add to meat; slowly cook (20 minutes).
Cook macaroni in chicken broth.
Mix all together in large baking dish.
Cheese may be added.
Bake in a medium oven until cheese is melted.

title: orange pudding
directions: Cut oranges into 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with a little sugar.
Mix the 1/2 cup sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Stir into beaten egg yolks and beat until runny.
Pour a little scalded milk over egg mix.
Add egg mix to remainder of milk and cook in double boiler until thick.
Pour over oranges.
Beat egg whites, adding 2 to 3 tablespoons of sugar and water a little at a time, until stiff.
Spread on custard and bake in 350° oven for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Boil potatoes, skin and run through a sieve.
Mix potatoes, spices, sugar and salt.
Add milk; pour in pie shell.
Bake in a slow oven at 350° until done.

title: polish sausage (kielbasa)(my grandma's recipe)
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Stuff in casing or into patties.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix applesauce, sugar, eggs and vanilla until well blended. Mix dry ingredients together and add to applesauce mixture.
Blend well and add apples.
Put into a 9 x 12-inch pan and sprinkle brown sugar on top.
Bake at 350° in a greased pan for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: almond cheesecake
directions: Add ingredients in order, blending together to make a soft dough.
Press into Phoenixware spring-form pan.

title: egg mcgirl scouts(method:  foil or coals)
directions: You will need a small tuna can for each person, plus aluminum foil to cover.
You will also need spray vegetable coating for cans.

title: mini pizzas
directions: Mix sausage or hamburger with tomato sauce.
Add Velveeta cheese until well blended.
Put foil on cookie sheets.
Place cocktail bread on sheets and spoon mixture onto bread.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: scalloped eggplant
directions: Slice and pare eggplant; cut into cubes.
Cook in boiling salted water about 8 minutes; drain.
Mix with all other ingredients.
Place in greased casserole (1 to 1 1/2-quarts); top with buttered cracker or bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sunset refresher
directions: Combine orange juice and apple juice. Fill frosted glass with ice and add juice. Top each glass with scoop of sherbet. Garnish with orange peel and add a straw.
Makes 8 tall glasses.

title: cake mix cinnamon rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup warm water, when dissolved, combine all- knead and let rise. Knead again and roll out, put on brown sugar and cinnamon, roll and cut roll, put in pan and let rise again. Bake at 350 degrees for 20-25 minutes.

title: shrimp-vegetable salad
directions: Reserve a few shrimp for garnishing.
Combine all remaining ingredients and serve in lettuce leaf.
Serves 4.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients on high for 2 minutes.
Add chocolate chips and grated chocolate to mixture.
Place in tube pan (greased and floured).
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Keep oven door closed.

title: chinese meat loaf
directions: Mix everything except meat and bread crumbs.
Mix thoroughly. Mix in meat; your hands work best.
Still with your hands, mix in bread crumbs briefly.
If you mix too long now, it will be tough. In a greased loaf pan, gently pat in mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: tarragon surprise
directions: Saut mushrooms in butter. Slice in thin strips the chicken and brown with mushrooms and butter. Add yogurt and cream cheese. Turn heat to simmer and add spices. Simmer 20 minutes, then add Parmesan cheese. Serve over brown rice.

title: potato cheese soup
directions: When potatoes are about half done, combine the next 4 ingredients in a large saucepan on low heat.
Stir frequently to prevent scorching.
Drain potatoes and combine with the soup/cheese mixture in Dutch oven size pot.
Add onions, if desired or onion powder.

title: crispy chicken
directions: In shallow bowl, combine cereal, flour and seasoning.
Place butter in another bowl.
Dip chicken in butter; roll in cereal mixture.
Place in greased baking dish.
Drizzle with remaining butter.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: betty's fish bake
directions: Mix together egg yolk, milk, crumbs, salt, pepper, parsley, onion, crabmeat and half of the melted butter.
Spread foil in baking pan (about 9 x 15-inch) large enough to make tent over fish. Lay three fillets flat.
Spread on crab mixture fairly thin.
Top with other three fillets.
Brush with butter and sprinkle with nuts.
Fold foil loosely.
Bake 30 minutes at 400°.
Uncover and bake 5 minutes longer to brown.
Cut each double fillet in half to serve.
A wedge of lemon and a touch of paprika gives this dish a very professional look.

title: kentucky pound cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar, oil and pineapple. Add egg yolks, cinnamon and water. Fold in beaten egg whites and chopped nuts. Bake in tube pan at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Cook mixed vegetables in its own juice for about 20 minutes (drain). Add celery soup and chopped chicken. Then put in 1 pie crust and cover with the other pie crust. Mash ends together with fork. Bake about 15 to 20 minutes or until crust is done and brown.

title: skillet okra and rice
directions: Heat oil in 10-inch nonstick skillet.
Over medium-high heat, cook rice in oil about 3 minutes, stirring frequently, until golden brown.
Stir in onion, bell pepper and garlic.
Cook 5 minutes, stirring frequently, until onion begins to soften.
Stir in remaining ingredients except okra.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer until rice is tender.
Stir in okra.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes longer or until okra is tender.
Remove bay leaf.

title: opal's strawberry bread
directions: In a large bowl, sift dry ingredients.
Combine eggs, strawberries and oil and add to dry ingredients.
