Add pecans. Pour into 2 greased loaf pans and bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Combine corn flakes, salt, pepper and paprika.
Dip chicken in butter and dredge in crumbs.
Place in lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Yields 4 servings.

title: corn relish
directions: Cut corn from cob; do not scrape.
Mix all ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Cook 30 minutes.
Stir frequently.
Pour into hot jars and seal.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels, butter and sugar together and spread into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.
Cool completely.

title: waffles
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Add egg yolks and milk.
Stir. Add oil and stir.
Fold in egg whites.
Do not overmix.
Pour 2/3 cup on waffle maker for each waffle.

title: nuts and bolts
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Melt in saucepan.
Combine remaining ingredients in a large roasting pan and stir in the melting mixture.
Mix well and bake in 225° oven for 45 minutes (roaster covered).
Stir about every 15 minutes.
Bake 30 minutes longer without lid.
Cool.
Put in container to store.

title: apple bread
directions: In bowl, combine flour, cinnamon, baking soda, baking powder and salt; set aside.
In a large mixing bowl, place oil, sugar, eggs, vanilla and apples.
Stir into flour mixture.
Add walnuts and mix.
Divide mixture between 2 greased 8 x 4-inch bread pans. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until breads test done.
Cool for 10 minutes on wire rack before removing from pans.
Yield:
2 loaves.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients together except chicken.
Place chicken in single layer skin side up in large shallow baking pan.
Pour preserves mixture on chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done, basting occasionally with the pan drippings.
Serve hot with plain rice and the sweet and sour sauce.

title: beef and cheese snacks
directions: Spread slices of dried beef with cream cheese.
Roll up, chill until firm and slice crosswise.

title: four bean salad
directions: Drain and "rinse" the beans and drain again.
Combine the beans and the rest of the ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate. Stir occasionally or before serving.

title: easy cake
directions: In a greased 9 x 13-inch pan, place peaches on bottom, sprinkle cake mix over peaches.
Dot with pats of margarine.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.
Cake mix and peaches can be reversed.

title: dirt pudding
directions: Break up Oreos.
Put in sack and use hammer to chop good. Make vanilla pudding.
Put in bottom of pan.
Layer ingredients, putting chopped Oreos on top.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Add to broccoli and cheese mixture.
Cook for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Grind the first 4 ingredients.
Sprinkle with salt and let stand overnight.
Drain and rinse thoroughly.
In a large kettle, bring the remaining ingredients to a boil.
Add the ground ingredients and simmer for 30 minutes.
Process.

title: quick and easy lasagna
directions: Cook 9 lasagna pasta noodles according to package. Brown ground meat and drain off all fat. Add spaghetti sauce and
tomato sauce and simmer 15 minutes. Drain off water from noodles and place 3 lasagna noodles on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: breakfast burritos
directions: Crumble bacon.
Beat eggs with cheese and milk.
Add bacon, onion and tomatoes.
Fry egg mixture until done.
Warm shells in oven (coat each shell with margarine).
Serve mixture in shells.

title: a holly treat
directions: Melt butter or margarine in a large saucepan.
Add marshmallow until completely melted.
Remove from heat.
Add cornflakes, food coloring and candy.
Mix well.
Pour mixture into a Bundt pan sprayed with vegetable spray.
When cool, turn out onto plate. Makes 24 treats.

title: garlic, cucumber, mint, yogurt salad
directions: Crush garlic cloves.
(If using mortar and pestle, cut cloves in pieces and add a sprinkle of salt and a few drops of water.) In a bowl combine garlic, salt, olive oil and yogurt.
Add minced fresh mint leaves.
Peel cucumber.
Slice very thinly into yogurt mixture.
Adjust salt to taste. Chill thoroughly.
May be served over ice cubes, if desired.

title: no cook pecan roll
directions: Mix all together and roll in a log.
Cover with wax paper and chill.
Slice to serve.

title: poor man dinners
directions: Shape ground chuck into 2 large patties and place in foil. Drizzle the top of patties with Worcestershire sauce.
Dice carrots, potatoes and onions.
Lay on top of the patties.
Add salt and pepper.
Fold foil over top of patties and vegetables.

title: lazy day brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease an 8-inch pan.
Combine ingredients and mix well.
Bake 20 minutes.
Cool and serve.

title: karmel korn
directions: Boil sugar, syrup and vinegar until cracks (real hard in water).
Add soda.
Pour over dishpan of popped corn.
Can make into balls or break into pieces.
Store in airtight container.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Beat eggs; add milk and mix well. Add
flour, salt and baking powder. Have dough very moist. Put a little flour in kneading bowl. Use a little at a time until you can roll out dough. Cut in strips.

title: chicken livers in port
directions: Saute onions in melted butter a few minutes. Add livers and saute 3 to 5 minutes, depending on the size of the livers. Bruise sage. Add along with the salt, lemon juice, Port and pepper. Cook slowly about 8 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Correct seasoning and serve on toast or with crackers.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix pineapple juice with lemon juice.
Combine fruit and nuts.
Sprinkle pudding over fruit and nuts.
Then pour juice over this and mix well.
Refrigerate for a while.

title: shoepeg corn casserole
directions: In a large bowl combine the first seven ingredients. Transfer to a greased 2 quart baking dish. Sprinkle with cracker crumbs then drizzle with margarine. Bake uncovered at 350 degrees for 20 to 25 minutes or until bubbly. Yields 6 servings. This can be doubled but be sure you bake until it bubbles.

title: steven's favorite spaghetti sauce
directions: In a large saucepan over medium heat, add olive oil.
Add garlic and cook until lightly browned.
Puree the whole tomatoes and add to pan along with tomato sauce and water.
Add seasonings and hamburger meat. Simmer 1 hour, stirring occasionally. Serve over spaghetti or any other type of pasta.

title: cheddarburger loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Form into a loaf (8 x 4 x 1 1/2-inches).
Place in shallow pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: delicious meatballs
directions: Mix ingredients together and make into meatballs the size of walnuts.
Place in 9x13 inch glass baking dish.

title: refrigerator bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1 cup water.
Blend remaining ingredients: water, sugar, salt, oil, eggs and 2 cups flour.
Add the yeast mixture, blend.
Then add remaining flour one cup at a time. Knead until smooth and satiny.
Shape either dinner rolls or buns for hamburgers; let rise 20 to 30 minutes and bake in 400° oven for 10 minutes.
Remaining dough may be kept in airtight container for up to two weeks, you can use as needed.
Refrigerated dough may take more time to rise after rolls are shaped.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together and bring to a boil.
Boil until soft ball stage (10 minutes).
Remove from heat.
Add last 3 ingredients.
Mix until smooth.
Pour into foil-lined pan. Chill.

title: spinach artichoke dip
directions: Boil chicken in a pot of water.
When chicken is cooked, cut or shred and return to pot.
(Also boil onions, celery and carrots with chicken.)
Skim fat out of pot.
Add tomato sauce.

title: italian goulash
directions: Brown and drain hamburger.
Add tomato sauce. Add 1 1/2 cans water.
Bring to a boil.
Season with salt and pepper, maybe some garlic powder.
Add noodles.
Cook until tender.
Add corn and chili con carne.
Heat thoroughly.

title: busy day chicken
directions: Place chicken pieces in bottom of greased casserole dish and salt lightly.
Sprinkle rice over chicken pieces after mixing it with the dry onion soup mix.
Combine cream soups with water as directed on can and stir until free of lumps, then pour them over the rice and chicken pieces.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: In
saucepan,
melt butter.
Blend in flour and cheese. Add milk. Cool and stir until mixture boils. Stir in broccoli. Place in a 1-quart casserole. Top with cracker crumbs. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: tex-mex cornbread
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Grease an 8-inch square casserole. Combine cornmeal and cayenne pepper in a large bowl. Add onion, green pepper, cheese, milk, eggs and corn.
Mix well. Spoon batter into casserole. Bake at 450° for 25 minutes or until golden. Cut into 2-inch squares.
Makes 16 servings.

title: cole slaw dressing
directions: Mix together and put on shredded cabbage.

title: strawberry pudding
directions: Put strawberries in pie plate or bowl.
Pour sugar over strawberries and set aside.
Mix milk and pudding mix in a bowl, stirring until smooth and thick.
Pour pudding mix over strawberries and cover with graham cracker crumbs.
Keep in refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water; add sugar and Crisco.
Beat in other ingredients.
Spoon into greased muffin tins (only 1/3 to 1/2 full).
Bake in heated 400° oven for 13 to 15 minutes.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen.

title: chicken and stuffing casserole
directions: Place breasts in rectangular flat baking dish.
Top chicken with cheese slices.
Mix soup, wine and cream together well; pour over the cheese slices.
Sprinkle stuffing over top.
Melt butter and pour over stuffing mix.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°, uncovered. Holds well in warm oven.

title: potato-onion soup
directions: Cook potatoes and onions until soft; drain most of the water off.
Add milk and seasonings (to cover 2/3 of mixture).
On low heat, let simmer until hot.
With low speed of mixer, mix 3 minutes.
Add cheese to garnish.

title: peach dessert
directions: Empty the can of sliced peaches in an ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle the box of dry cake mix over the peaches, then sprinkle on the flaked coconut and chopped pecans.
Melt the margarine and drizzle over all.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Serve with whipped topping or ice cream.

title: apple dumplin
directions: Heat oven to 325°, make pie dough, peel apples, core, leaving apple whole.
Sit apple on a square of dough.
Put white sugar in hole, put a pat of butter on top.
Then close up dough around apple.
Wet as needed with water so it will stick together.
Cook in a glass pan for 35 minutes.
Spoon juice back over top to glaze.
Cook for 15 minutes more.
When done, let cool for a few minutes to firm before serving.

title: oven fried chicken and potatoes
directions: Arrange chicken and potatoes in a pan.
Squeeze butter over top.
Sprinkle generous amount of seasoning salt and dashes of pepper.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.
Turn chicken over and add seasoning salt and pepper again.
Bake another 40 minutes or until done.
Serve with vegetable of choice and rolls for a delicious meal.

title: easy fudge
directions: Add all ingredients. Bring to a boil. Stir constantly for 3 minutes.
Take off heat.
Let cool for 15 minutes. Stir, then pour in buttered pan. Cut and eat in short time.

title: german potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes in skins until tender. Slice and put into a large bowl. Add the rest of the ingredients.
Blend well and serve.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Stir chicken, bell pepper, cream cheese and 1/2 cup salsa in saucepan on low heat until cream cheese is melted.
Spoon 1/3 cup chicken mixture down center of each tortilla; roll up.
Place, seam side down, in lightly greased 12x8 inch baking dish.

title: tomato dumplings
directions: Boil tomatoes and butter.
Mix the flour and milk.
Drop flour mixture a spoonful at a time into boiling tomatoes.
Turn stove down and cook until looks done.
Add a little more milk and stir.

title: hazel gentry's a to z bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients and set aside.
Beat eggs in a large bowl.
Add oil and sugar.
Cream well.
Add A to Z and vanilla. Add dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Add nuts.
Spoon into 2 well greased loaf pans.
Bake in a preheated oven at 325° for 1 hour. Makes 2 large loaves.

title: one pot macaroni supper
directions: In Dutch oven, combine soup, water and chili powder. Heat until boiling. Stir in macaroni, hot dogs and mushrooms. Cook over low heat until macaroni is tender (about 12 minutes). Makes 6 servings.

title: main dish beans
directions: Sort and rinse dried beans.
Cook until tender.
In a large frypan, fry bacon pieces and onion until brown, then add ground beef.
Cook until brown.
Add mixture to cooked beans and season with garlic, salt and pepper.
Add Ro-Tel tomatoes (2 cans if you like beans hot).
Bring to a boil, then turn off and let set for 30 minutes before eating.

title: onion-cucumber salad
directions: Pull tines of fork firmly down the length of cucumber, repeating around the cucumber; thinly slice.
Thinly slice the onion; separate into rings.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Pour over vegetable and marinate in refrigerator for at least one hour.

title: my mom's favorite pecan cookies
directions: Mix and stir all ingredients.
Drop on cookie sheet lined with aluminum foil.
Bake at 325°.
Cool before removing from foil. They will have a nice shiny bottom and will be a good crispy treat.

title: fruit cake
directions: Mix by hand.
Have fruit and nuts ready.
Save some for decorating top of cake.
Mix sugar, eggs and brandy flavoring in large bowl.
Sift remaining ingredients together and mix well with butter mixture.
Work into batter with hands.
Add fruit and nuts.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 275° for about 3 hours.
One and one-half hours before cake is done, remove from oven and glaze with light corn syrup or honey and decorate with leftover fruit and nuts.
Return to oven and finish baking.
Store in airtight container in cool place for 3 weeks before eating.

title: david's beer batter
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients, then gradually add flour until desired consistency is reached.
May be used to dip fish, onion rings, zucchini, mushrooms, shrimp, etc., in for frying.

title: balkan cucumber salad
directions: Peel and slice cucumbers (unless they are homegrown and unwaxed, in which case, do not peel them).
Combine all ingredients, except walnuts.
Chill thoroughly and serve on a bed of fresh, crisp greens with walnuts on top.
Garnish lavishly with tomato wedges, chopped black olives and carrot slices.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: saucy herb vegetables
directions: In 10-inch skillet over medium heat, combine soup, milk, basil and pepper.
Heat to boiling, stirring occasionally.

title: holiday canape spread
directions: Mix all ingredients except bread. Spread 1 teaspoon onto each slice of buffet bread.
Broil until cheese bubbles.
Makes approximately 150 (1 1/4 inch) slices.
Mix can be made ahead and refrigerated or frozen.
Thaw before using.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Sift flour, salt and sugar together.
Then add dry yeast. Melt butter.
Add water and milk.
The water and milk need to be lukewarm.
Mix together liquid and dry mixture.
Let set approximately 1 1/2 hours in greased pan to rise.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown the beef in oil. Drain.
Add the garlic, parsley, oregano, tomato paste, basil, salt and tomatoes.
Simmer until thick.
In a bowl, mix the cottage cheese, salt, Parmesan cheese, pepper, eggs and parsley flakes.
Cook the lasagna noodles. Slice the Velveeta and Mozzarella. In a 9 x 13-inch pan, alternate layers, starting with noodles, cottage cheese, meat and cheeses. Make 2 layers.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: tex-mex chicken
directions: Spray an 11 x 13-inch baking dish with Pam. Cover bottom with crushed tortilla chips. Set aside.
Boil chicken 45 to 60 minutes. Cool and chop.
Saute onion and green chilies in butter until tender. Add soups, milk and chicken.
Heat.
Pour chicken mixture over chips. Sprinkle cheese on top.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until bubbly.

title: hopping john
directions: Place ham hock in a large pot; cover with water and cook for 30 minutes.
Using a crock-pot, place ham hock and water in the crock-pot with all the ingredients except the rice.
Cook on low setting on the crock-pot for 4 to 5 hours.
Take ham hock out and remove bone and skin; put rice in the crock-pot and cook for about 1 hour after which return the ham hock to the crock-pot, stirring thoroughly.
You now have Hopping John.

title: lemon lush or pistachio chocolate
directions: Blend with fork or hands.
Press into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes, until lightly browned, in a 350° oven.
Cool.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Cream oil and sugar.
Add eggs and beat well.
Sift dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture.
Stir in vanilla, raisins, nuts and zucchini.
Bake in 2 loaf pans at 350° for 1 hour.

title: creamy corn italiano
directions: In saucepan, cook onions with garlic, oregano and basil in butter until tender.
Add remaining ingredients.
Heat; stir occasionally.
Makes about 4 1/2 cups.

title: weenie soup
directions: Brown the onions and weenies in the butter.
Add the soup, water or milk and the rice.
Heat to a boil.
Remove from heat and serve.
Serves 6.

title: mexican hominy
directions: Mix all ingredients except Cheddar cheese.
Pour into a greased baking dish; top with grated Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: dijon pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta in boiling water just until done, usually 11 to 13 minutes.
Drain.
Run cold water over pasta until it is completely cool.
In a large bowl, whisk together oil, vinegar, mustard and mayonnaise.
Add pasta and all other ingredients to dressing, mix carefully and taste for seasoning.
Chill thoroughly before serving.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: croutons
directions: Toss bread cubes with margarine and seasoning.
Spread on baking sheet and toast 45 minutes or until crisp at 300°.
Watch closely to prevent overbrowning.
Store in airtight containers.

title: cheesy corn bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a 3-quart saucepan, over low heat, melt margarine.
Whisk in flour, garlic powder and cayenne pepper. Blend well and slowly add milk, whisking constantly, until smooth.
Increase heat to medium and cook 3 to 4 minutes, stirring constantly, until the mixture is thickened and bubbling.

title: strawberry or cherry cheese cake
directions: Mix graham crackers and oleo.
Press into cookie sheet.
Put in 350° oven for 10 minutes, turning with spatula.
Mix cream cheese, milk, powdered sugar and Dream Whip.
Beat until stiff. Add vanilla to cream cheese mixture.
Pour this over graham cracker crumbs.
Top with strawberry or cherry pie filling.
Set in refrigerator until firm.
Best to let set overnight.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Cube
potatoes	and
slice
carrots, lengthwise.
Slice sausage
lengthwise.
Layer
potatoes,
carrots, mushrooms and onions
in a casserole dish.
Put butter over mixture and pour sweet and sour sauce over ingredients, enough to soak ingredients. Lay
sausage
with
cut side down over the ingredients. Cook for 1 hour or until potatoes and carrots are done.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix and chill.
May also add chopped pecans, if desired.

title: cranberry bread
directions: Sift flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and soda in a large bowl. Cut in butter until mixture is crumbly. Add eggs, orange peel and orange juice all at once. Stir just until mixture is evenly moist. Fold in cranberries. Spoon into greased loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes. Remove from pan and let cool on wire rack.

title: mincemeat
directions: Cook
several
hours on low heat or bake in oven, stirring often.
Freeze or can.
Makes about 20 quarts.

title: mary's pound cake
directions: Cream Crisco and oleo with sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time. Mix flour and baking powder together and add to mixture alternating with milk and vanilla.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Combine beans, milk, soup, pepper and 1/2 can French fried onion rings.
Pour into a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes, then top with remaining French fried onion rings and bake 5 minutes longer.

title: freezer cole slaw
directions: Mix the cabbage and salt; let stand for 1 hour.
Squeeze moisture from cabbage.
Add carrot and green pepper.

title: corn chowder
directions: In medium saucepan, add water, potatoes and onion. Cook over medium heat until potatoes are tender. Add corn, milk and butter. Heat until hot.
Serve.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: clam chowder #1
directions: Melt butter in very large pot.
Mix all other ingredients and heat.
Enjoy.

title: party punch
directions: Blend juices and gelatin in punch bowl.
Stir in sherbet and soda.
Makes 40 cups.

title: snow cake
directions: Bake cake in a large pan.
Cool completely.
Mix pudding with milk.
Mix pudding with softened cream cheese.
Spread on cooled cake with pineapple.
Top with Cool Whip.
Cover with coconut. Store in refrigerator.

title: waffles
directions: Prepare batter as for pancakes with the new liquid ingredients listed in this recipe.
Heat your waffle iron according to the manufacturer's instructions.
Pour the batter into the hot waffle iron.
Bake until the waffle stops steaming.
Serve warm with butter, maple syrup and bacon slices.

title: tuna croquettes
directions: Drain
fish and flake coarsely.
Melt butter;
blend in flour and gradually stir in milk.
Cook, while stirring, until sauce boils
and thickens.
Add fish, vinegar and seasonings. Cool. Shape
into 6 to 8 croquettes.
Dip in beaten egg, then in potato chip
crumbs.
Fry
in deep fat heated to 365° to a golden brown, about 5 minutes.

title: biscuit nugget chicken
directions: Mix chicken with paprika, salt, milk, soup and mushrooms. Heat and pour in baking dish.
Cut biscuits into 4 pieces.
Shake biscuit pieces in a plastic bag with remaining ingredients.
Place pieces on top of chicken mixture.
Sprinkle remaining spices on top.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: meat marinade
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour over uncooked meat (beef, pork or chicken).
Let marinate for several hours in refrigerator, drain and cook the meat.
May use a basting sauce while cooking.

title: healthy pancakes(serves 6)
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together with wire whisk in a large bowl. Next, in a separate bowl, whip egg whites, applesauce, milk and vanilla for about a minute with electric mixer.
Pour liquid ingredients into dry ingredients, stirring with wire whisk just long enough to combine the two (less than a minute).
Cook in a nonstick skillet or griddle, at about 375°.
(No oil is required.)

title: brown sugar squares
directions: Boil sugar, syrup and milk to soft ball stage.
Remove from fire.
Add butter or butter substitute.
Cool to room temperature. Beat until thick and creamy.
Add coconut, nuts, salt and flavoring.
Pour into well buttered, shallow pan.
Cut into squares.

title: indian wedding cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients together, then pineapple, then eggs.
Bake in a 13 x 9 x 2 inch pan for 30-35 minutes at 350° or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Take 1 cup of perfect berries and spread on bottom of baked shell.
Mash remainder of quart in pan.
Add water.
Mix sugar, cornstarch and salt and mix with berries.
Cook the mixture until clear and cooling, then add lemon and butter.
Pour into baked shell.
Cool.
Top with whipped cream or Cool Whip before serving.

title: cream of potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes ahead; save liquid and keep warm.
Saute bacon, onion, celery; add hot half and half.
Thicken with roux to desired thickness.
Add potatoes and liquid, then salt and pepper.
To garnish, sprinkle with paprika and chopped fresh parsley.

title: caramel fudge frosting
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Add brown sugar.
Cook over low heat for 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add milk and cook until mixture boils.
Remove from heat and cool 10 minutes.
Gradually add confectioners sugar, beating until frosting is of good spreading consistency.
Makes 2 cups.

title: beef and potatoes
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine ground beef, bread crumbs, egg, onion, ketchup, salt and pepper.
Spread into an 8-inch square baking dish.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven and drain the excess fat.

title: taco-casserole
directions: Layer chips, mixture and cheese twice.
Cook 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: hawaiian pie
directions: Freeze the crust overnight.
The next day get it out.
Mash sides down on the crust.
Cook crust 1/2 hour.
Make chocolate and put on top.

title: all-occasion punch
directions: Cook on medium heat sugar and water till well dissolved stirring constantly.
Add lemon jello; stir until well dissolved and remove from heat.
Pour all juices and jello mixture into large container, mix well.
Add extract and ginger ale and 1/2 gallon of water.
Stir well.
Put in freezer until mixture becomes slushy.
Makes 1
1/2 gallons.

title: zesty chicken and rice
directions: Combine rice, 1 cup French fried onions and Italian seasoning in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Pour broth over rice mixture. Arrange chicken on top.
Pour salad dressing over chicken.
Bake, covered, at 400° for 30 minutes.
Place vegetables around chicken, covering rice.
Bake, uncovered, 20 to 30 minutes or until cooked. Top chicken with remaining onions.
Bake, uncovered, 1 minute or until onions are golden.
Makes 4 servings.

title: kosher dill pickles
directions: It is recommended that you do one jar at a time.
Slice two cucumbers, not too thin, and pack into jar after placing 1 teaspoon of dill in the bottom of the empty jar.
Place 1 teaspoon of dill on the top of the cucumbers and then add the other spices.
Fill jar almost to the top with boiling water, vinegar and salt mixture. Seal at once.

title: chicken san juan
directions: In large skillet, brown sausage and chicken.
Set aside.
Add vegetables to skillet and cook, stirring occasionally until vegetables are slightly wilted, about 10 minutes.
Add rice, saffron, broth, chicken and sausage.
Cover and bring to boil. Place in paella pan or casserole and bake about 40 minutes.
You may also continue cooking in skillet.

title: creamy lemon pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Beat egg yolks.
Stir in condensed milk.
Add lemon juice and food coloring, if desired.
Pour into prepared crust.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Cool and chill.
Spread with whipped topping.
Keep refrigerated.
Makes 1 (8 or 9-inch) pie.

title: hawaiian chicken
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
In large skillet, cook onion and celery in oil until tender.
Add chicken.
Blend catsup and reserved pineapple juice with enough water to make 2 1/2 cups liquid.
Stir salt and black pepper into liquid mixture.
Pour over chicken.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Dissolve cornstarch in soy sauce.
Gently stir into chicken mixture.
Add green pepper and pineapple. Cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Prepare hot cooked rice. Serve chicken and sauce over rice.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.
Enjoy!

title: linguine pesto
directions: Blend the pistachios, basil, parsley and garlic in a food processor until they form a paste. Add the next five ingredients. Cook linguine. Add butter and stir pesto into the noodles.

title: danish potato pancakes
directions: Grate potatoes.
Pour off excess water.
Grate onion; add other ingredients.
Mix.
Pour one-half inch oil in frypan. Allow oil to get real hot.
With a tablespoon or spatula, drop little flattened cakes in pan.
Fry until brown on both sides. Drain on paper towel.

title: savory chicken-stuffing bake
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Prepare stuffing mix according to package directions, but do not let stand as directed on package. In a 12 x 8-inch baking dish, spoon stuffing down the center of the dish, leaving space on each end to arrange chicken. In bowl, combine soup, milk and parsley. Pour over chicken. Cover with foil. Bake 15 minutes. Uncover. Bake 10 minutes more or until chicken is no longer pink.
To serve, sprinkle with paprika. Stir sauce at edges and spoon over chicken.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Combine all ingredients, spread in oven proof serving dish.
Bake for 25 - 30 minutes.
Serve with assorted crackers.
Best made a day ahead.

title: carrot cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325 degrees.

title: james ward's crab dip
directions: Bake until it bubbles at 350° in a bake and serve dish. Combine all ingredients first and "feel" through crabmeat for shell pieces.
Serve with Triscuits.

title: orange date nut bread
directions: Pour juice of orange in cup and fill with boiling water. Grind orange rind with dates.
Mix fruit and juice.
Stir in shortening, vanilla and egg.
Add sifted dry ingredients.
Beat and add nuts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
I use a 13 x 4 1/2-inch loaf pan.

title: lemon whippersnappers
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine Cool Whip, egg and cake mix in a large bowl. Drop by teaspoonfuls into powdered sugar.
Roll to cover.
Place on cookie sheet.
Flatten slightly with fork. Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes on greased cookie sheet.

title: coconut cake
directions: Cook cake, using directions on box.
Cool.
Put holes in cake. Pour Eagle Brand milk over cake.
Let set 3 hours.
Put Cool Whip and coconut on top of this.

title: green pepper steak
directions: Brown beef in hot oil; add garlic clove and chopped green peppers.
Cook until the mixture looks yellow.
Add soy sauce, salt, 1/2 cup water, onions and celery.
Cook for 45 minutes.
Stir cornstarch in 1 cup water and add to mixture.
Serve over rice.

title: banana split cake
directions: Melt 1 stick margarine and mix with crumbs.
Spread in bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Beat 2 sticks margarine, powdered sugar and eggs, not less than 15 minutes.
Spread over the crust.
Slice bananas over this.
Spread pineapple over this.
Cover with Cool Whip.
Garnish with nuts and maraschino cherries.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: saucy meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 300° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: angel food pudding treat
directions: Tear the angel food cake into bite size bits.
Mix with prepared instant pudding.
Turn in fresh sliced strawberries (other fresh fruit if desired).
Set in fridge overnight.
Just before serving, put Cool Whip on top and mix.

title: ground beef stroganoff
directions: In a skillet with approximately 2 cups water and 2 beef bouillon cubes, cook off and brown beef and onion.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Stir well.
Heat through and serve over cooked noodles.

title: idiot's delight
directions: Cook meat, onion, chopped celery and green pepper.
(Season meat with Worcestershire, garlic salt, etc.)
Add tomatoes and corn. Add crushed noodles (uncooked) and cook slowly until noodles are soft.
Add sliced cheese over top and bake in oven until cheese melts.

title: danish pastry apple bars
directions: Combine flour and salt.
Cut in shortening.
Beat egg yolk in a measuring cup.
Add enough milk to make 2/3 cup liquid.
Mix well. Stir into flour mixture.
On floured surface, roll half the dough to a 17 x 12-inch rectangle.
Fit into and up the sides of a 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle with cornflakes.
Top with apples.

title: date nut cake
directions: Pour hot water over cut up dates; let cool.
Cream Crisco and sugar; add egg.
Mix dry ingredients together, add to date mixture.
Add nuts.
Bake in loaf pan in 350°
oven for 45 minutes.

title: multi-bean and corn salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl.

title: lacy oatmeal cookies
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine sugar, oats, baking powder and salt until well mixed.
Add melted butter, then egg and water. Beat mixture well.
Stir in almond extract and nuts.
Drop by spoonful onto buttered cookie sheet.
(Allow plenty of room for cookies to expand in baking process.) Bake in a 350° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool several minutes before removing from cookie sheet.

title: ham loaf
directions: Bake in a slow oven about an hour.

title: bounty rice
directions: Saute meat, onion and peppers until lightly browned.
Stir in tomatoes, seasonings, rice and cabbage.
Cover and cook 10 to 15 minutes or until cabbage is tender and crisp.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Cover 2 to 3 minutes to melt cheese.
Makes 6 servings.

title: jello pie
directions: Mix Jell-O, pudding and water.
Bring to a boil and chill. Pour into baked pie shell and top with whipped cream.

title: spinach gratin
directions: Preheat the oven to 425°.
Melt the butter in a heavy-bottomed saut pan over medium heat.
Add the onions and saut until translucent, about 15 minutes.
Add the flour and nutmeg and cook, stirring for 2 more minutes.
Add the cream and milk and cook until thickened.
Squeeze as much liquid as possible from the spinach and add the spinach to the sauce.
Add 1/2 cup of the Parmesan cheese and mix well.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Transfer the spinach mixture to a baking dish and sprinkle the remaining 1/2 cup Parmesan and the Gruyere on top.
Bake for 20 minutes until hot and bubbly.
Serve hot.

title: taco pie
directions: Brown beef and onion; drain off grease, then heat taco mix with beef and onion.
Put mixture into greased glass pie dish. Add green chilies to top of beef.
Mix Bisquick, egg and milk together; pour Bisquick mixture over beef and chilies.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Top with cheese, then lightly brown the top under broiler.
Let cool 5 minutes.

title: meatball sandwiches
directions: Place meatballs in an ungreased 1-quart baking dish. Combine the next 5 ingredients; pour over meatballs. Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour. Serve on rolls. Yield: 6 servings.

title: old-time molasses fruitcake
directions: In large bowl, combine dark raisins, golden raisins and mixed candied fruit; toss with brandy or rum.
Cover with plastic film and allow to soak overnight at room temperature.

title: pecan pie squares
directions: Mix, press into 9 x 9-inch square pan and bake 15 to 17 minutes at 350°.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Fry together beef and onions until pink disappears from meat. Add enchilada sauce.
Mix soup, water, green chilies, salt and pepper.
Set aside.
Break tortillas into several pieces in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Put a layer of tortillas, a layer of meat mix, layer of soup mix, then cover with cheese.
Repeat layers, ending with cheese.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight for better flavor.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken pie
directions: Boil chicken until tender, debone and cut up.
Place chicken in buttered baking dish.
Mix soup and broth together and pour over chicken.
Mix together milk, flour, margarine (melted) and baking powder.
Spoon over chicken and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: strawberry daiquiri
directions: Agitate in blender for 1 minute. Serves 1.
Enjoy!

title: deviled eggs
directions: Cut eggs in half lengthwise.
Remove yolks carefully.
Add the remaining ingredients, except the paprika and whip until smooth and fluffy.
Insert mixture into egg whites and sprinkle with paprika.
Makes 12 halves.

title: lightning cake
directions: Melt butter in a 1-cup measuring cup. Add milk to fill to the 1 cup mark. Add a pinch of salt and vanilla. Mix the sugar, baking powder and flour and incorporate into the milk mixture. Pour batter into an 8 or 9-inch pan sprayed with cooking spray. Bake at 375° for 20 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: crock-pot wassail
directions: Combine all ingredients in crock-pot and simmer several hours. Serve in warm mugs and garnish with orange slice.
Yields 10 mug servings.

title: spinach salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 cup hot water.
Let cool.
Thaw spinach and squeeze out water.
Add all ingredients to jello and let set. Spread with 1/2 cup sour cream and 1/2 cup mayo.

title: cold pea salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill for 4 hours or longer.

title: pineapple pecan pound cake
directions: Mix together and beat well.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold in.
Grease and flour tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: rosemary roasted new potatoes
directions: In a bowl, mix oil, garlic, rosemary, thyme, salt and pepper. Add potatoes; toss to coat.
Place in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish, in one layer, adding any of oil mixture left in bowl. Bake uncovered in a 450° oven about 25 minutes or until brown and tender.

title: macaroni and tuna salad
directions: Cook macaroni, drain and pour red vinegar over hot macaroni. Cut up all but one egg.
Add eggs, celery, onions, parsley, olives and tuna.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Add enough mayonnaise to moisten thoroughly.
Chill in refrigerator.
Place in pretty salad bowl.
Slice remaining hard-boiled egg on top.
Sprinkle with paprika.

title: very thin benne cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add slightly beaten egg.
Add flour with baking powder and salt.
Add benne (sesame) seed.
Add vanilla and blend well all ingredients.
Drop batter with a coffee or small teaspoon in pan lined with aluminum foil.
Bake in 325° oven until brown.
Let cool before removing from pan.
Cookies will stick to foil if not completely cool.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix flour, salt and soda; set aside.
Mix butter and peanut butter. Add both kinds of sugar; blend well. Add egg and beat well.
Stir flour mixture into peanut butter mixture. Drop dough from a teaspoon onto a baking sheet. Flatten with a fork. Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes until lightly browned.

title: savory kraut quiche
directions: Place crumbled bacon in pastry shell. Cover with onion. Slightly beat eggs with milk and pepper. Stir in kraut and cheese, saving enough to sprinkle over top.
Pour over bacon and onion. Top with cheese. Bake 45 minutes at 375°.

title: cheddar squash bake
directions: Salt cooked squash.
Mix the next 3 ingredients; fold in the beaten egg whites.
Layer half the squash and egg white mixture in 12 x 9-inch baking dish.
Crumble strips of bacon on top.
Repeat layers.
Mix the butter and cracker crumbs; sprinkle over top. Bake in a 12 x 9-inch pan for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: stack pudding
directions: To make the crust, mix together and pat down in a 13 x 9 inch pan, the flour, oleo, and nuts.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes, the cool.
Mix together the cream cheese, confectionary sugar and Kool Whip and spread over cooled crust.
Spread the chocolate pudding on top of the cream cheese layer.
Spread rest of Kool Whip over top of pudding.
Sprinkle nuts or shaved chocolate over topping.
Chill until served.

title: lemon eclair dessert
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, place one layer of graham crackers.
Mix pudding with milk.
Let thicken and add lemon jello; mix well. Fold in Cool Whip.
Spread 1/2 of mixture on crackers.
Layer more crackers, then pudding, ending with crackers.
Spread lemon frosting on crackers.
Refrigerate for 24 hours.
The longer it sets, the better it gets!

title: golden punch
directions: Extensive use of an iron pot will cause a crust to build up on the inside and outside of the pot.
No amount of washing will prevent this build-up.
To clean, follow this procedure: in campfire.
Allow pot to cook until residue is burned away. slow cooling until pot is cool enough to hold.

title: pumpkin dessert
directions: Mix eggs, pumpkin, salt, spice, milk and sugar.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix margarine into cake mix.
Sprinkle on top of filling mix.
Sprinkle nuts over all.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: german chocolate pie
directions: Preheat oven and cookie sheet to 400°.
In a large saucepan, melt chocolate and butter.
Gradually add milk and coconut. Combine eggs and sugar.
Stir into chocolate mixture.
Then add pecans.
Mix well.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake at 400° for about 30 minutes or until done.
Cool completely.

title: casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Add soups and beans.
Pour into casserole dish and cover with crumbled chips.
Grate cheese over chips.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with lettuce and tomato.

title: kiwi fruit danish
directions: Unroll dough and shape into 8 triangles with equal sides. Combine cream cheese, egg yolk, sugar and almond extract, blending well. Place 1 tablespoon cream cheese mixture in center of triangle; top with kiwi fruit slice. Pull points of triangles to center and pinch to seal. Bake on greased baking sheet at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes. Heat jam and top each roll with jam and kiwi fruit. Brush each with jam again after placing fruit.

title: bisquick apple crisp
directions: Mix first three ingredients and pour into greased (with margarine) deep dish pie plate.
Blend next five ingredients and pour over apples.

title: lima beans in sour cream
directions: Cook beans until tender and rinse in hot water.
Put in a large casserole dish.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: little red hen chicken
directions: Place chicken breasts in baking dish. Mix ingredients. Pour over breasts. Cut up mushrooms on top. Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: baked corn
directions: Mix all ingredients together in either 9 x 12-inch pan or 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake, covered, in oven for 1 hour. About last 10 minutes, take out and cover with grated cheese; return to oven.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Combine cream cheese and chili sauce.
Beat with beater.
Add onion and garlic salt.
Add shrimp last.
Form 2 small balls and coat with shrimp sauce.
Chill several hours before serving.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Drop by teaspoon on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: peanut butter crust
directions: Chop peanut butter chips in blender or food processor or with nut chopper.
In 9-inch pan, combine chips and crumbs.
Drizzle with melted butter or margarine; mix well.
Press onto bottom and up sides of pie pan.
Freeze.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Peel and cut the potatoes; boil in water until tender.
Drain, mash and add one stick of butter or margarine, one cup of light brown sugar, the salt, evaporated milk and vanilla.
Blend thoroughly, then fold in the egg yolks.
Whip egg whites until stiff peaks are formed and fold into the potato mixture.
Transfer to a large casserole dish.

title: cracklin corn bread
directions: Combine all ingredients except oil.
Add more water or milk, if needed.
Should be the consistency of cake batter.
Heat oil in iron skillet until very hot.
Add mixture.
Bake in preheated oven, 450°, for 25 minutes.

title: spoon rolls
directions: In large bowl that can be sealed with a lid, mix yeast and warm water until yeast dissolves.
Add egg and oil, then sugar and flour.
Mix well with mixer.
Store tightly covered in refrigerator.
(The dough will keep up to two weeks in refrigerator if sealed well after each use.)
May be baked immediately or later at 425° until browned on top.
Spray muffin pan with nonstick spray and fill 2/3 full of dough.

title: oven barbecued steaks
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cut steaks in 10 equal parts.
Pour oil into skillet.
Brown each piece of steak on both sides.
Transfer steaks to a roasting pan.
Add onions to oil in skillet and brown lightly.
Add rest of ingredients to make a sauce and simmer 5 minutes.
Pour sauce over steaks in pan.
Cover and bake 2 hours or until tender.

title: chicken shells
directions: Prepare stuffing mix as directed on package. Set aside.
Cook shells al dente.
In a large bowl, mix 2 cups chicken, mayonnaise and prepared stuffing.
In a small bowl, mix soup and 3/4 can milk.
Place thin layer of soup mixture on bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan. Stuff shells with chicken mixture.
Line shells up in pan. Spoon remaining soup mixture over top. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until bubbly.

title: hearty beef enchiladas
directions: In a Dutch oven, cook beef and onions over medium heat until meat is no longer pink; drain.
Stir in the beans, two cans of enchilada sauce and 1 cup salsa; set aside.
In a skillet, heat 1/4 inch of oil. Dip each tortilla in hot oil for 3 seconds on each side or just until limp; drain on paper towels.

title: sunday chicken bake
directions: In a 13 x 15-inch glass baking dish, place rice, soups and milk, well mixed.
Place the chicken breasts, bone side down, on top of the rice mixture.
Sprinkle dry onion soup mix over the chicken.
Cover with foil; bake in a slow (275°) oven for 2 hours.

title: dove supreme
directions: Season dove with salt and pepper, roll in flour.
Place in oil in a
heavy
roaster.
Bake
at
400° until brown.	Add onions, water and 1 cup of sherry.	Bake covered until tender, basting with sherry
occasionally.	Add
parsley to gravy just before serving.

title: coaches crunch
directions: Line a cookie sheet with foil.
Cover with crackers.

title: green grape pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake in a 350° or 375° oven until bubbly and turns brown.

title: shirley's meat loaf sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in a small saucepan.
Boil slowly 10 to 15 minutes.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Cook in pot first 6 ingredients until mixture boils.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 10 minutes or until broccoli is tender. Remove bay leaf.
Place 1/2 mixture in blender.
Blend 30 to 60 seconds.
Pour into bowl.
Repeat with remaining mixture.
Set aside.

title: swiss steak
directions: Pound flour into meat.
Add salt, pepper and garlic powder. Brown meat in oil.
Add remaining ingredients; simmer until done, about 1 hour or until meat is tender.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: no bake beans
directions: Combine all ingredients in a 5-quart pot on top of stove. Cover on medium heat until beans begin to bubble.
Then cook on low heat for 30 minutes, stirring often.
Use just enough bacon grease to season beans to your taste.

title: baked chicken breasts
directions: Put chicken breasts
in
x
12-inch
buttered
dish. Cover with grated cheese.
Mix soup and milk together and pour on top. Sprinkle
with
Stove Top dressing mixed with butter. Bake at 350° for 1
hour.
Cover
with
foil for first 30 minutes, then remove foil
and
bake,
uncovered, for the last 30 minutes.

title: grape salad
directions: Wash, destem and drain grapes.
Mix brown sugar, pecans and sour cream.
Stir in with grapes.
Cover top with Cool Whip just before serving.

title: orange-raisin sauce
directions: Combine orange juice, raisins and cloves in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil over high heat.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 8 to 10 minutes.
In small bowl, combine cornstarch, water, mustard and salt, blending well.
Slowly stir into orange juice mixture.
Cook, stirring, 3 to 5 minutes longer or until thickened.
Transfer to serving bowl.
Float an orange slice on top.
Garnish with mint sprig.
Makes 2 cups.
Serve with baked ham.

title: lentil soup
directions: Wash the lentils and drain well.
Fry the onions in the olive oil until golden brown.
Add the lentils; season them with the salt, pepper and ground cumin.
Cover the whole with water.
Boil; then let them cook on medium heat until well done.
Puree them or pass them through a food mill.
The soup must have a thick consistency, but if you prefer it thinner, you could add a little water.
Serve with the squares of Lebanese bread as croutons.
Try also a squeeze of lemon in each serving.

title: fruit and cheese kabobs with dip
directions: Alternate 3 pieces of any combination of fruit and cheese on plastic or wooden picks or skewers.

title: strawberries and cream cake roll
directions: Grease bottom and sides of a 15 x 10 x 1 jellyroll pan with vegetable oil; line with wax paper and grease wax paper with oil. Set pan aside.

With electric mixer, beat egg yolks in a large bowl until thick and lemon colored; stir in vanilla and set aside. Beat egg whites until foamy; add cream of tartar and salt, beating until stiff, but not dry.
Fold in 3/4 cup powdered sugar. Fold whites into yolk mixture.
Gradually fold flour into egg mixture.
Spread batter evenly into prepared pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Sift 1 to 2 tablespoons powdered sugar in a 15 x 10-inch rectangle on a cloth towel.
When cake is done, immediately loosen from sides of pan and turn out onto sugared towel.
Peel off wax paper.
Starting at narrow end; roll up cake and towel together.
Let cool completely on a wire rack, seam side down.
Combine sliced strawberries and 2 tablespoons sugar; set aside.
Beat whipping cream until foamy; gradually add 3 tablespoons sugar, beating until soft peaks form.
Unroll cake. Spread cake with sliced strawberries and half of whipped cream, reroll cake (without towel).
Place on serving plate, seam side down; spread remaining whipped cream on all sides.
Garnish with whole strawberries, if desired.
Chill until serving time.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Bring to a boil all ingredients except the berries.
Cool; add as many strawberries as desired.
Pour into pie shell.
Chill; then if you like, you can top with whipped topping and a few plain berries on top.

title: scalloped tuna and potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling, salted water for 10 minutes and drain.
Meanwhile melt butter and fat in top of double boiler over direct heat.
Stir in flour; add milk, onion, salt and pepper. Cook over hot water, stirring until smooth and thickened.
Add minced parsley.
Arrange potatoes and tuna in alternate layers in a greased 2-quart casserole.
Pour sauce over all and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 6.
(Salmon may be substituted.)

title: lemonade pie
directions: Mix lemonade, milk and Cool Whip until creamy.
Pour into crust and chill for about 2 hours.
Easy to make and delicious!

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Put in a casserole dish.
Put on topping.

title: berries and cream pie
directions: Bake pie crust; cool. Pour 1 cup water into microwave-safe bowl and sprinkle with gelatin. Stir to combine. Microwave 1 minute on High. Add topping and stir well. Add frozen berries and stir well to combine. Pour mixture into pie shell; spread evenly. Cover with plastic and refrigerate 15 minutes, to set.

title: lemon buttermilk pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar in mixer bowl until light and fluffy. Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift flour, salt and soda together.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk, beating well after each addition.
Stir in lemon extract.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/4 hours.
Cool in pan.
Invert onto serving plate.
Yield:
16 servings.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Mix sugar, vegetable oil and eggs together until well-blended.

Add flour, salt, soda, cinnamon and vanilla gradually. Beat until ingredients are well mixed. Add apples and pecans; stir until blended. Pour into greased 10-inch tube pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Three cups self-rising flour may be substituted for plain flour, salt and soda.

title: grilled vegetables
directions: Cut into quarters the squash, potatoes, carrots and onion. Place on large piece of aluminum foil.
Spray with Pam.
Place vegetables on foil.
Salt, pepper and sprinkle with Molly McButter.
Wrap foil tightly and grill until fork-tender, 15 to 25 minutes.
Some other vegetables good for grilling are corn, mushrooms, broccoli and cauliflower.

title: beauceron maple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift dry ingredients together.
In bowl mix vegetable oil, syrup, carrots, eggs, nuts and coconut together.
Gradually blend in dry ingredients.
Pour mixture into greased 9-inch pan.
Bake around 40 minutes.
Remove the cake.

title: banana split brownie pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix brownie mix as directed on package. Place parchment paper on 15-inch baking stone.
Pour mix on paper and spread into 14-inch circle.
Do not try without parchment paper, batter will run off stone while baking.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until set.
Cool.
Mix cream cheese and sugar until smooth.
Spread over brownie "crust."
Top with fruit and nuts. Melt chocolate and butter together, stirring until smooth. Drizzle over pizza.
Chill. Cut into wedges with pizza cutter. Serves 12 to 16.

title: fruit and angel dessert
directions: Break cake into bite size pieces.
Arrange half in bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Top with half the undrained pineapple and cherries.
Spread half of dessert topping; top with half of coconut.
Repeat layers.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: shrimp or crawfish etouffee(eh-to-faye; serves 4 to 6)
directions: Saute all vegetables, including mushrooms and tomatoes in the butter until very tender.
Add the mushroom soup and cook gently for about 15 minutes.
Add seafood and cook for an additional 20 minutes.
Serve over hot cooked rice.

title: delectable dessert
directions: Combine jello and make according to package directions.
When almost set add remaining ingredients and stir in.
Chill.
Serve on lettuce leaves.

title: cheese scalloped carrots
directions: Alternate layers of carrots and cheese in ungreased 13 x 9-inch baking dish or 2-quart casserole.
Saute onion in butter until tender.
Stir in flour, salt, mustard and pepper.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Gradually stir in milk.
Heat to boiling over low heat, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Pour sauce over carrots and sprinkle bread crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: chicken strips
directions: Heat oven to 400°. Mix together the flour, salt and pepper. Coat chicken in flour mixture. Mix together the eggs and milk. Dip chicken in egg, then roll in bread crumbs. Place on baking sheet and drizzle with butter. Bake 12 to 15 minutes until no longer pink in center. Serve with ketchup, barbecue sauce, hot sauce or Ranch dressing.

title: jerome bars
directions: Line an 11 x 13-inch pan with whole graham crackers.
Mix butter, sugar, milk and egg.
Boil 1 minute; remove from heat. Stir in pecans, coconut and graham cracker crumbs.
Spread on top of whole graham crackers; cover with another layer of whole graham crackers.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Melt margarine; combine with rice in large roasting pan.
Add all soups; stir until combined thoroughly.
Add chicken pieces, pushing them down into soup mixture until all are covered.
Drizzle some extra melted butter on top.
Cover; bake at 275° for 2 1/2 hours.

title: chopped beef zucchini casserole
directions: Saute
zucchini,
onions
and green pepper in margarine until tender.
Stir
in parsley as desired.
Saute separately chopped beef and stir until browned evenly.
Season with salt, pepper
and thyme.
Layer
of
vegetable	mixture in low baking
dish. Cover
with thin layer of sliced tomatoes, then with 1/2
of
meat mixture.
Repeat layers until all is used, making last layer vegetables and tomatoes.
Top with a mixture of 1/2
cup coarsely grated bread crumbs, 1/2 cup grated sharp cheese
and 2 tablespoons melted butter or margarine.
Bake 45 minutes at 350° or until browned.

title: zucchini and spinach casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook spinach.
Add nutmeg and set aside. Combine zucchini, water, margarine and salt.
Steam in skillet 5 minutes.
Set aside.
Mix cheeses, layer spinach, zucchini mixture and cheeses.
Bake 20 minutes.
Makes 3 cups.
One-half cup = 1 fat; 1 vegetable; calories 102; protein 8 gram; fat 6 gram.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Boil and debone chicken, reserving one cup of the stock.
Cut chicken into bite size pieces.
Combine mushroom soup, milk, butter and seasonings in saucepan and heat.
Gradually add chicken broth and mix well.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix sour cream and taco seasoning.
Refrigerate overnight. Place chopped veggies on top of dip and serve with taco chips.

title: easy lemon pie
directions: Squeeze lemon juice into a separate bowl.
Beat the yellow of eggs very well, then pour milk into this and mix very good.
Pour lemon juice in real slow.
Stir as you go.
Pour into a graham cracker pie crust and refrigerate at least 2 hours or until firm.

title: brown rice
directions: Saute chopped celery and green onions in butter or margarine until tender.
Drain mushrooms and chop.
In a large casserole dish, mix celery, onions, rice, beef bouillon and mushrooms.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until tender.

title: p.r. mallory casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; drain grease.
Add tomato soup and simmer 10 minutes.
Boil macaroni until tender.
To ground beef, add Velveeta and drained mushrooms.
Drain macaroni and add to ground beef mixture.
Place in casserole dish and bake for 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: shrimp gumbo
directions: Wash, peel, dice and devein shrimp, then refrigerate.
Save shrimp shells and rinse in cold water.
Combine shells, water and salt in kettle and simmer for 20 minutes.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Stuff the green peppers with the tuna mixture and place into a shallow baking dish.
Pour in 1/2 cup tomato juice over the peppers.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Turkey can be used.

title: dried apples and cinnamon cut-outs part 2(non edible)
directions: Slice apples lengthwise in the core sections 1/4-inch thick or more.
For wreath, ends can be sliced in 1/2 in slices so ends will curl.
Soak apples in 2 cups lemon juice and 1 tablespoon salt for 3 minutes.
Place slices on cake rack in 150° oven, leaving door ajar, for 6 hours.
Do not brown slices.
When dry, slices will be leathery but pliable.
To extend life, spray with acrylic spray.

title: tasty meat log
directions: Combine all ingredients except parsley or nuts.
Form into a log shape.
Wrap in plastic wrap.
Refrigerate.
Before serving, roll in chopped parsley or nuts.
Serve with an assortment of crackers.

title: dutch hustle cake
directions: Scald milk; stir in sugar, salt and half the margarine.
Cool to lukewarm.
In mixing bowl, dissolve yeast in warm, not hot, water.
Stir in lukewarm milk mixture.
Add egg and flour.
Beat until smooth.
Spread dough evenly in greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Arrange apple slices on top.
Sprinkle with spices.
Dot with remaining margarine.
Cover and let rise in warm place free from draft until doubled in size (about 40 minutes).
Bake in 400° hot oven for 25 minutes.
Drizzle with powdered sugar icing.

title: chili rellenos
directions: Combine chilies and cheese and put in bottom of oiled dish. Mix rest of ingredients in blender, pour over chilies, filling dish halfway.
Bake in 350 degree oven for 1 hour.

title: divinity candy
directions: Place sugar, syrup and water in same saucepan and cook to 248°.
Remove from heat and let temperature drop to 220°, without stirring.
Place egg whites in bowl and whip to soft peak.
Add syrup at medium speed for about 2 1/2 minutes. Turn to high speed and whip 20 to 25 minutes or until it begins to dry.
Drop from greased spoon onto a greased platter.
(Candy thermometer a must and beating time important for best results.)

title: cranberry spiced punch
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Boil 5 minutes.
Strain.
Mix in fruit juices.
Just before serving, pour over a decorative ice ring mold (a bag of cranberries frozen into the ice is beautiful). Add ginger ale and rum.
Serves 12.

title: blueberry delight
directions: Line 9-inch square pan with whole crackers, breaking some, if necessary, to cover.

title: apple cream pie
directions: Put apples in baked pie shell.
Mix sugar and flour together. Add cream; mix well and pour over apples.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°, until brown.
Drizzle 1 tablespoon butter over pie and sprinkle cinnamon on top.
Simple and delicious.

title: italian new york cheesecake
directions: Blend Ricotta cheese and cream cheese well.
Blend in sugar. Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Add vanilla, lemon juice, cornstarch, flour and butter.
Fold in sour cream and blend well. Pour into a 10-inch buttered spring-form pan.
Place in a cold oven and turn heat to 325°.
Bake 1 hour.
Do not open oven door. Turn off oven and leave until cool, at least 2 more hours.
Top with cherry pie filling or whatever you prefer.

title: cream cheese and raspberry coffee cake
directions: In a large mixer bowl, beat cream cheese, sugar and margarine until fluffy.
Add half of the flour, all of the eggs, milk, baking powder, baking soda, vanilla and salt.
Add remaining flour.
Spread in greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Spoon preserves in 8 to 10 dollops on top of batter.
With a knife, swirl preserves into batter to form a marble effect.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool slightly on a wire rack. Sift powdered sugar atop.
Cut into squares.
Serve warm.

title: creamy cucumber dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in food processor.
Store in refrigerator in airtight container.

title: nutty pudding bars
directions: Combine chips, peanut butter and unsweetened chocolate. Stir over low heat until melted. Spread 1/2 in 15 x 10-inch pan. Chill. Combine butter, pudding and milk. Cook and stir to melt butter. Stir in vanilla. Turn into large mixer bowl; beat in sugar until smooth. Spread over chilled layer. Sprinkle nuts on top. Spread remaining chocolate over all. Chill until firm. Makes 6 pounds.

title: broccoli bake
directions: In a
1 1/2-quart shallow casserole, combine soup, milk, soy sauce and pepper; stir in broccoli and 1/2 can of onions.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until hot.
Top with remaining onions; bake 5 additional minutes.

title: chicken suzanne
directions: First Layer:
8 ounces flat egg noodles, cooked.

title: reuben casserole
directions: Combine rice, sauerkraut, corned beef and 1/2 cup cheese. Blend mayonnaise, pickle relish, mustard, salt and pepper.
Stir into rice mixture.
Turn into a 2-quart casserole.
Arrange tomato slices on top.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Top with bread crumbs; bake at 350° for 30 minutes, or until hot and bubbly. Yields 6 servings.

title: roast beef and noodles
directions: Sear the roast in hot oil. Combine the cranberry sauce, tomato sauce, water and soup mix. Pour over the browned roast. Cover and bake at 350° for 3+ hours or until very tender. Remove and slice the meat; return to the pot. Arrange cooked noodles on a platter and put slices of beef over the top. Spoon the pan gravy all over. Garnish with fresh parsley and fresh orange slices cut thinly.

title: almond cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together, then add beaten egg. Slowly add flour, baking soda, almond extract and corn syrup.
Mix until smooth.
Make cookie size balls out of all the dough. Flatten each ball and place an almond in the center of each one. Bake at 375° on a greased cookie sheet for about 20 minutes.
Makes about 4 dozen.
Best if made ahead of time and frozen before use.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Cook sausage until brown, crumbling as it cooks.
Drain well. Spread bread cubes in a buttered 12 x 8-inch casserole dish.
Top with sausage and cheese.
Combine eggs, milk and seasonings; beat well and pour over cheese.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes, or until set.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: meat balls
directions: Mix ingredients; roll into balls and fry.
Add brown gravy or tomato sauce and simmer 1 hour.
Serve with pasta or rice.

title: caramel icing
directions: Mix together and cook about 10 minutes (time after a good rolling boil), stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and beat until stiff enough to spread on cake.

title: golden pound cake
directions: Mix in large bowl the cake mix, sour cream, oil, sugar, water and eggs.
Beat at high speed for 2 minutes.
Grease and flour a 10-inch tube pan.
Pour batter in pan and cook at 375° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: sour cream pot roast
directions: Melt butter in Dutch oven.
Brown meat and saute onions.
Stir in sour cream stock, dill weed, salt, pepper and parsley.
Cover and simmer 2 or 3 hours.

title: easy cobbler
directions: Mix flour, sugar and water or milk, making a thin batter. Melt in pie pan.
Pour the batter over the butter.
Pour the sweet fruit over the batter.
Bake at about 275° to 300° until top is crusted (allow about 1 hour).

title: chicken bundle(method:  grill)
directions: Place the chicken on a large piece of heavy-duty foil.
Add the vegetables, seasonings, butter and water.
Fold the foil closely around the chicken and seal.
Cook on grill over hot coals, turning every 10 to 15 minutes, for 1 hour.
Serve in foil.
Serves 1.

title: crisp little lemon cookies
directions: Combine lemon cake mix and butter (make sure butter is not too soft).
Add egg and mix well.
Stir in Rice Krispies.
Place 1-inch balls on ungreased cookie sheet 2 inches apart.
Bake at 350° for 9 to 12 minutes.

title: super nachos
directions: Mix the ground beef and taco mix; moisten with water.
Add chives and olives.
Shred cheese.
Spread the beans in bottom of casserole (oblong pan).
Spread beef mixture over beans.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Spread the sour cream over top.
Cover with guacamole.
Chop scallions or onions and sprinkle over.
Edge with taco shells.

title: fish and pasta
directions: In a large flat sauce pan put olive oil.
Add the cut up onion and green pepper, cook until soft.
Add the cut up tomatoes. Add bay leaf, garlic powder, paprika, sweet basil and creole seasoning stir and let cook for about 10 minutes.
Add the chopped up black olives, the cut up mushrooms and white wine.
Stir in well to mix and then let it cook down for about 15 minutes.
Add the Fish pieces and parmesan cheese, let the fish and cheese sit on top.
Cook until the fish is done, about 10 - 15 minutes. Serve over a bed of cooked flat noodles.
Serves 3 - 4 people.

title: french green beans deluxe(this is a good picnic vegetable.)
directions: In a large bowl, mix beans, peas, onion, green pepper and pimentos.
In a separate bowl, mix sugar, vinegar, oil, water and salt, then pour over vegetable mixture.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: filet of beef with mustard cream sauce
directions: Melt butter in heavy large skillet over medium-high heat.
Add steaks and cook 6 minutes per side for medium.
Add mustard and Worcestershire to skillet with steaks and stir to mix.
Season with pepper.
Add brandy and remove from heat.
Ignite the sauce with a long match.
When flames subside, return skillet to heat and remove the steaks, keeping them warm.
Add cream to skillet and boil for 1 to 2 minutes or until slightly thickened.
Pour sauce over steaks and serve.
Yields 2 servings.

title: cream cheese pie shells
directions: Mix well and chill overnight.
Roll out to fit pan, prick with fork and bake 8 to 10 minutes in 400° oven.
Fill with favorite filling.

title: eagle condensed milk
directions: Mix thoroughly in a blender and refrigerate.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in 13 x 9-inch pan. Sprinkle crumbs over butter, pressing it down.
Sprinkle coconut next.
Add a layer of chips and a layer of pecans.
Drizzle milk evenly over top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Let cool before cutting into bars.

title: peanut butter apples(on a stick)
directions: Wash apples; put stick in each apple.
Put peanut butter in saucepan; add enough honey to make it soupy.
Heat until it bubbles.
Dip each apple in until coated.
Place on cookie sheet covered with waxed paper and refrigerate for a short time.

title: delicious ambrosia
directions: Mix King Sour with fruit.
Add mini marshmallows and coconut. Stir well and chill.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Melt butter in 10 x 10 x 2-inch dish.
Mix together flour, milk and 1/2 cup sugar.
Pour over butter.
Spread 3 cups fruit over mixture.
Add remaining 1 cup of sugar over fruit.
Pour water over sugar.
(Can use juice from fruit.)
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: broccoli puff casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions, omitting the salt; drain thoroughly.
Place broccoli in pan.
Combine soup and cheese.
Add milk, mayonnaise and egg, gradually, stirring until well blended.
Pour over broccoli.

title: molasses pull candy(70 year old recipe)
directions: Mix sugar, molasses and vinegar.
Stir until sugar is dissolved.
Cook to hard ball stage.
Take from heat and add soda and butter.
Beat by hand until mixed.
Pour in greased platter to cool.
When cool, pull with buttered fingers.
Make into rope shape.
Break when cool.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Brown onion and butter.
Mix with all other ingredients.
Top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake for 40 to 50 minutes at 350°. Can also add leftover ham or chicken.

title: sour cream cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, sour cream and vanilla. Sift flour with the salt, baking soda and cream of tartar.
Add to first mixture and bake 10 minutes at 400°.
Drop by teaspoon. Frost with sour cream icing.

title: hobo bread
directions: Stir all together.
Grease and flour pans.
Pour into medium size vegetable cans.
Fill half full.
Bake at 350 degrees about 40 minutes.
Test for doneness.

title: black magic cake
directions: Melt chocolate with 2 tablespoons sugar and water in double boiler; cool.
Beat egg whites with salt and cream of tartar until soft peaks form.
Gradually beat in 1/2 cup sugar and beat until stiff peaks form.

title: barbecue sauce for deer meat
directions: Have deer meat in thin slices. Flour deer slices. Brown in 3 tablespoons oil.
Set aside.
Brown onion in same juice until transparent. Drain.
Put meat and onion in a 13 x 9-inch pan. After you mix up the barbecue sauce, pour over meat and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Brown pork chops in skillet about 10 minutes or until browned. Mix potatoes (thawed), soup and sour cream and make a layer in a buttered casserole dish.
Lay the pork chops on this and cover with more of the potato mixture.
Pat onions on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
If potatoes get brown, then cover for the last 45 minutes.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese on top before serving.

title: porcupine meatballs
directions: Mix ground beef, rice and onion.
Form into 1-inch round balls and place in a well-greased casserole dish.
Mix the soup with the salsa and pour over the meatballs.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: simple cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients and shape into small balls.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Press down.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: asparagus-cheddar cheese pie
directions: Mix room temperature creamed cheese and soup.
Stir in asparagus.
Pour into one pie shell.
Cover with second pie shell. Seal edges.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let sit 30 minutes before serving.

title: five hour beef stew
directions: In bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan, place the ingredients in the order listed.
Sprinkle tapioca over all and season to taste. Cover and place in 250° oven for 5 hours.

title: baked apricots
directions: In greased 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish, place apricot halves next to each other forming a bottom layer.
Cover with brown sugar, generously.
Then cover with crumbled Ritz crackers and dot generously with butter.
Repeat process for second layer.
Bake at 300° to 350° for one hour to one and a half hours.
Should be nice and brown on top.
Nice to serve as side dish for ham or pork roast.

title: cranberry salad jello mold
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Add cold water.
Chill until partially set.
Fold in remaining ingredients.
Chill until firm.

title: cranberry fruit sauce
directions: Combine sugar and water; bring to boiling point and add remaining ingredients.
Cook slowly, without stirring, until cranberry skins pop open and apple slices are clear (10 to 15 minutes).
Cool sauce in cooking dish.
Makes 1 quart sauce.

title: instant chocolate sauce
directions: Place instant cocoa mix in a small bowl.
Heat milk and butter in saucepan to scalding point.
Add hot liquid to instant cocoa mix and stir briskly for 2 minutes.
Serve hot or cold.
Yield: 3/4 cup.

title: peach pie
directions: Heat oven to 425°. Prepare pastry.
Mix peaches and lemon juice. Stir together sugar, flour and cinnamon.
Mix with peaches. Turn into pie dish. Dot with butter. Cover with top crust. Cut slits in crust. Sprinkle with sugar.
Cover edges of crust with aluminum foil to prevent too much browning. Bake for 35 to 45 minutes.
Makes a 9-inch pie.

title: biscuit mix(serves 100)
directions: Sift dry ingredients together three times or blend on low speed with a mixer.
Cut or rub in shortening.
Store in a tightly covered container.
Makes 6 pounds 8 ounces.

title: reese's cups
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Add peanut butter.
Add powdered sugar.
Melt chips and paraffin in a double boiler.
Press peanut butter mixture in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour chocolate over top of the peanut butter mixture.
Let cool for at least 5 minutes.
Cut into squares.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream margarine, cream cheese and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add salt, vanilla and butter flavor; beat well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Stir in flour.
Spoon mixture into well-greased and floured tube pan. Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°.
This makes a large, very moist cake.

title: tang pie
directions: Mix Tang, milk, Cool Whip and sour cream.
Pour into pie shells.
Refrigerate for 2 hours.
Makes 2 pies.

title: apple torte
directions: Cream first 3 ingredients.
Blend in flour. Spread dough onto bottom and sides of 10-inch spring-form pan. Combine softened cream cheese with 1/4 cup sugar; mix well.
Add egg and 1/2 teaspoon vanilla and mix.
Pour into pastry-lined pan.

title: good stuff
directions: Brown meat, onion and green pepper.
Drain.
Add seasoning pack from noodles, Worcestershire sauce and tomatoes with juice.
Add mushrooms, salt and pepper to taste and simmer for 15 to 20 minutes.
Break noodles, add and cook until noodles are tender. Leave in skillet or pour into casserole.
Top with cheese, cover with lid or foil, allowing cheese to melt (5 to 10 minutes).

title: jello strawberry cake
directions: Mix yellow cake mix, following directions on box; pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
In the same bowl, mix jello with 7-Up.
Stir, then gently pour over cake batter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Take out of oven and let cool for 10 minutes.
Refrigerate for 1 hour.
Take out of refrigerator and put strawberries on top and cover with Cool Whip.
Refrigerate until served.

title: western casserole
directions: Drain hamburger.
Put in baking bowl.
Add chili beans and stir.
Top with frosted flakes and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pickled beets
directions: Place eggs and beets in a large glass jar.
Heat beet juice, vinegar, sugar and spices to boiling.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes. Pour over beets and eggs.
Let set 1/2 hour, then put in refrigerator.
Chill.

title: bonbons
directions: Combine
butter, milk, sugar and coconut.
Chill for 30 minutes.
Form into balls and chill again.
Melt chips and wax over hot water.
Dip balls into chocolate, put on wax paper to cool.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and cool in refrigerator for 1/2 hour.
Serve.

title: chocowacky cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift together first 5 ingredients into an ungreased 9 x 9 x 2 pan.
Add vinegar, vanilla, oil and water. Blend only with a fork; do not beat.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Frost with sour cream white frosting.

title: kenny's dessert pizza
directions: Roll dough out on pizza pan and bake as package directs.
When cool, mix cream cheese and sugar together until creamy.
Spread on dough as you would sauce on pizza.
Top with fruit.
In a saucepan over medium heat, mix together some orange juice, fruit juice and cornstarch; boil until thickened.
Pour over fruit as a glaze. Serves 8 to 10.

title: garlic and cheese bruschetta(low calorie)
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a bowl; beat at medium speed of electric mixer until smooth.
Stir in 1/2 cup of Swiss cheese, Parmesan cheese and next 3 ingredients.
Spread cheese mixture evenly over toast slices; sprinkle evenly with remaining 1/2 cup Swiss cheese.
Broil for 1 1/2 minutes or until Swiss cheese melts.
Sprinkle with pepper.
Yield:
16 servings.

title: choceclair dessert
directions: In bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan, place one layer of crackers.
Mix vanilla pudding with milk.
Mix in Cool Whip.
Spread half of mixture over crackers.
Put another layer of crackers.
Top with remaining pudding mixture.
Add another layer of crackers; spread frosting over the top.
Refrigerate 12 to 24 hours.
You can use the chocolate Cool Whip instead of frosting if you desire.

title: paul newman cake
directions: Bake cake in 11 x 13-inch pan per package directions.

While warm, punch holes in top (a couple of inches apart) with straw or wooden spoon handle. Spread milk on cake, then spread butterscotch topping on top. Refrigerate to cool. Spread with Cool Whip and sprinkle with broken Heath bars.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Beat cream cheese and milk.
Add lemon juice and vanilla. Beat again.
Add peanut butter; beat again.
Fold in Cool Whip. Put into graham cracker crust.
Freeze several hours.
Before serving, drizzle syrup over pie.

title: pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a Bundt pan.
Mix dry ingredients in one bowl.
In another bowl cream the butter and sugar; add dry ingredients alternately with milk and vanilla. Bake 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: teresa lord's cheese wafers
directions: Cream the cheese and butter.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
Roll in balls and press flat with a fork dipped in water. Bake at 375° until brown.
Sprinkle with paprika.

title: meat loaf with glaze
directions: Mix first 10 ingredients and mix well.
Shape into loaves and place in pans. Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: soda cracker cookies
directions: Combine sugar, margarine and evaporated milk in saucepan. Bring to a boil.
Boil 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add 1/2 cup peanut butter.
Stir well until smooth. Add crushed saltines and vanilla.
Mix well and drop from teaspoon onto wax paper and let cool.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown hamburger.
Add tomatoes, beans and mushroom soup.
Put layer of meat mixture in greased casserole, layer of Fritos and layer of cheese.
Make 2 layers, ending with cheese on top.
Bake in 350° oven for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: my pop's batter bread
directions: Put corn meal in a mixing bowl.
Scald half of it with the boiling water.
Add salt and milk.
If more milk is needed to make a smooth running batter, add a little at a time.
Add eggs and sugar; beat well.
Melt the butter in an 8 x 8-inch baking dish (may be heated in the oven); circulate the butter over the dish well.
Pour melted butter into the batter and mix well.
Pour batter into baking dish.
Bake at 450° for about 35 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve with more butter!

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well, beating about 3 to 5 minutes.
Bake in 3 (9-inch) pans for 15 to 20 minutes or in an oblong dish around 30 minutes at 350°.
Cool before topping.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Mix together.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in an 8 x 8-inch pan.

title: oatmeal raisin chews
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
In a medium bowl, combine flour, soda, salt and oats.
Mix well with a wire whisk and set aside.

title: marinated tenderloin of beef(for a cocktail party)
directions: Marinate beef overnight in dressing.
Bake in an open pan at 500° for about 30 minutes, or until internal temperature reaches 130° to 135°.
Cool.
Slice thinly.
Serve on small, homemade rolls with a dish of sweet-sour mustard on the side.

title: blueberry dessert
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs, butter and 1/4 cup sugar.
Spread and press in 9 x 13 pan.
Cream together:
