cream cheese and 1/2 c. white sugar.
Mix in egg yolks and vanilla.
Beat egg whites and fold in.
Spread on crust.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: deluxe pea salad
directions: Drain all cans and mix well.
Pour dressing over and marinate overnight.

title: baked tuna stuffed potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Wash potatoes.
Rub skins all over with margarine.
Prick with fork.
Bake on oven rack 1 1/2 hours or until tender.
Meanwhile in a medium bowl, combine tuna, onion, parsley, soup, paprika, Tabasco and salt.
Toss with fork, to break up tuna and to blend well.
Remove 1-inch slice from top of each potato.
Scoop out inside of potatoes leaving a shell.
Add potatoes to tuna mixture, tossing to mix well.
Spoon lightly into potato shells.
Mound high top of each with 1/2 slice cheese. Place in shallow baking pan.
Bake 15 minutes or until filling is hot and cheese is melted.
Makes 8 servings.

title: italian love cake
directions: Beat until firm and spread topping over cool cake.

title: barbecued chicken
directions: Brown
chicken	slowly	in
oil.
Remove
chicken.
Add onion, cut
in 1/4-inch slices and celery.
Cook until tender. Add catsup, water, sauce, sugar, vinegar and mustard.
Season and simmer for 10 minutes; skim off excess fat.
Place chicken in an 11	x
x
1/2-inch
baking dish.
Pour sauce over. Bake, uncovered, in slow oven at 325° for 1 1/4 hours or until done, basting occasionally.

title: layered salad
directions: Note:
Amount varies according to number of servings needed.

title: forest ranger cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream shortening and sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Sift flour, salt, soda and baking powder together and add to creamed mixture.
Add oatmeal and rice cereal.
Mix well.
Form balls and place on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Remove to cooling rack.
Store in airtight container.

title: dipped pretzels
directions: Melt almond bark using package directions.
Dip pretzels into almond bark. Place on wax paper.
Let stand until firm.

title: fruited cream cheese pie
directions: Beat cream cheese and sugar until smooth.
Thoroughly fold in whipped cream and turn into pie shell.
Chill 2 hours.
Arrange fruit in rings as desired (example:
oranges on the outside ring, then cherries, then pineapple chunks in the middle).

title: wild rice soup
directions: Saute ham, mushrooms, onion and garlic.
Add flour, milk and chicken stock.
Cook about 15 minutes.
Add cooked potatoes, rice, cheese spread and pepper.
Cook until bubbly.

title: arlene's cornbread
directions: Combine in a bowl the dry ingredients (corn meal, flour, sugar, baking powder and salt).
Combine egg yolks with vanilla, half and half and margarine or butter; add to dry ingredients. Stir until moistened.
Beat egg whites until stiff, but not dry. Fold into mixture.
Pour into well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: easy cheesecake
directions: Blend juice and milk together.
Cut or break softened cream cheese.
Blend milk little by little by hand or mixer into cheese. Pour into crust.
Top with fresh fruit, canned pie fillings or sprinkles.
for firmer filling take out 1 tablespoon of milk before adding.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown together meat and onion.
Add remaining ingredients; simmer about 20 minutes.
Layer Doritos, meat mixture and grated cheese (about 1/2 to 3/4 lb.).
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix corn bread and biscuits.
Melt margarine; pour over bread. Add mushroom and chicken soups.
Start with bread mixture and alternate layers of chicken, cut up.
Put bread mixture on top. Cook 1 1/4 hours or until done at 350°.

title: scallops florentine
directions: Combine scallops, butter, milk, wine and onion in a saucepan; cook over low heat 10 minutes.
Combine cornstarch and a small amount of hot liquid.
Mix until smooth and stir into hot mixture. Cook until slightly thickened, stirring constantly.
Do not boil. Spoon spinach into a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Pour scallop mixture over spinach.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes or until bubbly.
Serves 4.

title: monkey food
directions: Cut together well butter and flour.
Press into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Fold remaining ingredients together.
Spread over baked crust.
Return to oven and bake for 15 to 20 minutes or until set.

title: pineapple-carrot bread
directions: Sift the dry ingredients together.
Beat eggs and sugar until pale and thick.
Stir in the oil, a little at a time.
Add carrots, pineapple, vanilla and flour mixture.
Bake in greased and floured pans at 325° for about an hour; test with toothpick. Cool in pans for 10 minutes.
Turn out onto racks.
Makes 3 or 4 regular sized loaf pans.
Freezes well.

title: caribbean fruit salad(light and easy)
directions: In a decorative clear glass bowl, layer pineapple, mango, banana and strawberry pieces.
Combine yogurt and powdered sugar, blending until smooth.
Spoon over fruit.
Serves 4.
Contains approximately 0.4 grams fat per serving.

title: fruit salad
directions: Combine cream cheese and sugar.
Mix well and fold in Cool Whip.
Drain fruit and add to cream cheese, Cool Whip mixture. Put in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan and sprinkle with nuts if desired. Refrigerate.

title: fabulous tongue tingling potato salad
directions: Peel and cut potatoes into cubes.
Boil in water until tender. While potatoes are boiling, dice peppers, onions, celery and carrots.
Boil eggs on high for 5 minutes, then cool in cold water.
Peel eggs and dice.
Put all diced ingredients in large bowl.
Drain cooked potatoes and add to diced vegetables.
Add Miracle Whip, relish and mustard; season with pepper, sugar and seasoned salt to taste.
Stir well to blend all the ingredients. Sprinkle finished salad with paprika.
Garnish with fresh parsley leaves.

title: oriental chicken
directions: Take chicken breasts and place in casserole dish.
Sprinkle soup mix on chicken.
Add strips of carrots and strips of bell pepper.
Pour dressing over all and spread preserves over dressing.
Cover with foil and cook at 325° for 2 hours, uncovering the last 30 minutes.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix together and let set overnight.

title: homemade banana pudding
directions: Separate egg yolks from whites; set whites aside.
Mix sugar, flour, egg yolks, milk, vanilla, butter and salt in a boiler (that will not stick) over medium heat.
Beat egg yolks before adding to flour mixture.
Bring to boil, stirring often.
Continue cooking until it is as thick as you like.
Lay vanilla wafers in bottom of medium casserole dish.
Slice bananas and arrange them on top of wafers.
Pour pudding on top of wafers and bananas.
Chill until thickened.
Whip egg whites and 1/2 cup sugar until stiff.
Spread on top of finished pudding.
Bake until brown.

title: apple crunch
directions: Pour can of apple pie filling into an 8 x 8-inch pan.
In a bowl, mix together flour, sugar, egg and salt.
With fingers, sprinkle over apples.
Top with melted margarine.
Drizzle over crust.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until brown.

title: toll house mud bars
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In bowl, combine flour, baking soda and salt; set aside.
In bowl, beat brown sugar, butter and vanilla extract until creamy.
Add eggs; beat well.
Gradually add flour mixture.
Stir in 1 1/2 cups chocolate chips and nuts.
Spread into foil-lined 9-inch square baking pan.
Bake at 375° for 23 to 25 minutes.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Drain and chop artichoke hearts.
Mix well with other ingredients. Spread in pan and heat until it bubbles. Can be put in oven or microwave.

title: capt. luck's clam chowder
directions: Dice potatoes, carrots and onions and add to several strips of salt pork which has been dried out (fried slowly) in a black iron pot.
Season and add water to cover.
Bring to boil (cook slowly until the potatoes and carrots are almost done).
Then add the ground up clams and tomatoes.
The chowder can simmer for a long time.
It is very good reheated.

title: perfect pie meringue
directions: Moisten cornstarch with a little water.
Add boiling water. Cook until clear.
Cool.
Beat egg whites with a pinch of salt until stiff.
Add sugar, one tablespoon at a time.
Beat in gradually to cooled cornstarch mixture.
Spread on pie.
Put in a 375° oven to brown.
Cool.

title: overnight scalloped chicken casserole
directions: In large bowl, combine soups, milk and cheese.
Add chicken, uncooked macaroni, onion, mushrooms and chopped eggs.
Stir in 1/4 cup melted butter.
Put in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Cover and refrigerate overnight or at least 8 hours.
Toss bread crumbs with remaining butter.
Sprinkle over casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 350°
for 1 hour or until bubbly and golden brown.

title: nina's swiss vegetable casserole
directions: Grease 1-quart casserole and put in the vegetables using 1/2 each of the onions and cheese.
Use the reserve of cheese and onions on top of the casserole.
Combine soup, sour cream and spices and pour over the vegetables.
Bake, uncovered, for 30 minutes at 350°.
Top with remaining cheese and onions and bake for 5 minutes longer.
Serves 6.

title: cherry cake
directions: First flour, then add cherries.
Stir it up, put it into cake holder.
Bake it at 10° for 20 minutes.
When oven beeps, cake is done.
Frost with canned cherry frosting.

title: italian boneless chicken
directions: Enjoy half of this entree now, freeze the other half and bake later.

title: bran muffins
directions: Stir together flour, baking powder, salt and sugar. Set aside. Measure 2 1/2 cups bran into mixing bowl; add milk and let set until cereal is softened. Add egg and shortening. Beat well. Add dry ingredients to cereal mixture, stirring only until combined. Portion batter evenly into 12 greased 2 1/2-inch muffin pan cups. Bake in oven at 400° about 25 minutes or until muffins are golden brown. Serve warm.
Makes 1 dozen.

title: salmon croquettes
directions: Drain salmon.
Remove bones and skin.
Mix all ingredients except fat.
Roll into croquettes.
Fry in deep hot fat until brown.
Drain on paper towel.

title: scalloped spinach
directions: Cut spinach according to package directions; drain well.
Mix with milk, 1/2 cup of the cheese, eggs, onion, 1/2 teaspoon salt and dash of pepper.
Turn into greased 8 x 8-inch baking pan. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Combine crumbs, remaining cheese and butter.
Sprinkle on spinach.
Bake until knife inserted off center comes out clean, 10 to 15 minutes longer.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Serves 6.

title: banana pudding cake
directions: Mix ingredients altogether in mixer.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan or 12-cup Bundt pan.
Bake a 9 x 13-inch pan for 40 to 45 minutes or a Bundt pan for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl.
Place in baking dish. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook your lasagna noodles until tender.
Brown hamburger then drain the fat off.
Add your sauce to the meat.
Put a layer of noodles then add meat sauce then a layer of noodles, adding Mozzarella cheese to every layer of noodles.
Just continue to layer until sauce, cheese and noodles are gone.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Combine oil and sugar.
Add eggs, flour, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Add vanilla and chopped apples.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 300° for 35 minutes.

title: taco baked potatoes
directions: Wash potatoes well.
Bake potatoes at 400° for 1 hour or until soft.
Cut potatoes in half lengthwise, carefully scoop out potato pulp into bowl (leave 1/2-inch pulp to keep potato skin intact). Set skins aside.
Add yogurt and pepper to pulp; mash until fluffy. Stir in 1/2 cup cheese, chilies, pimento and cilantro into mixture. Stuff skins with mixture.
Place stuffed potatoes on ungreased baking sheet, sprinkle with remaining 1/4 cup cheese.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes or until cheese is melted and bubbly.
Peel avocado and remove pit.
Mash with lime juice until smooth.
Spoon on hot potatoes.

title: spinach pie
directions: Wash and cut spinach (remove stems).
Steam for 5 minutes. Drain well and squeeze out all water.
Wash and cut mushrooms. Saute in oil and garlic powder.
Mix all ingredients.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 350° or until golden.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix together and mold into a ball.
Roll in more ham.
Serve with crackers.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Combine ingredients and place in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour crust over chicken mixture.

title: a better for me drink
directions: Mix together and serve over ice with a cherry.

title: blue hawaii cocktail
directions: Fill 10 oz. glass with crushed ice.
Add curacao and vodka. Fill glass with Collins mixer.
Mix and garnish.

title: turkey bake
directions: Cut apples and bread into small pieces.

title: mexican enchilada casserole
directions: 1. Brown meat and onions. Season with garlic, chilli powder, etc.
2. Add tomato sauce, Ro-tel's with juice, and broth soups.
Mix throughly. Layer meat mixture with quartered tortillias and cheese.
3. Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: chicken with artichoke(serves 8)
directions: Drain artichoke hearts; arrange in 8 greased ramekins or a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Spread chicken on top (1/3 cup per ramekin). Combine soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry; pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Toss bread with butter; place on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: pepper steak with rice
directions: While rice is cooking, salt and pepper steak and cut into 1/2-inch pieces.
Using a large skillet, melt margarine and add meat to margarine and brown.
Add garlic and broth; cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Stir in sliced onion and bell peppers; cover and cook 5 minutes more.
Blend cornstarch, water and soy sauce; stir into meat mixture.
Cook 5 minutes more or until gravy is thick. Serve over hot rice.
Makes 6 servings.

title: grits casserole
directions: Cook water, grits and salt until done and thick.
Add garlic cheese and margarine.
Let melt a minute.
Put eggs in measuring cup; add milk to fill cup; beat.
Add to other ingredients and stir.
Pour into 2-quart greased casserole and cover with grated cheese, then with crushed cornflakes.
Bake at 350° about 45 minutes or until set and brown.

title: snowballs
directions: Combine chocolate and milk in double boiler.
Heat over hot water until chocolate melts, stirring to blend.
Remove from heat; stir in confectioners sugar and nuts.
Cool slightly, then form in 1-inch balls.
Roll in coconut.
Makes about 24.

title: pecan pie
directions: Combine sugar, syrup and melted oleo.
Add beaten egg and pecans to syrup mixture.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: mexican dip
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together and spread in a glass dish. Spread sour cream over mixture.
Sprinkle taco seasoning over sour cream.
Layer Cheddar cheese and green onions.
Chill 3 to 4 hours before serving.

title: grilled tuna steaks on sticks
directions: Soak bamboo skewers in water.
Combine vinegar, soy sauce, water, olive oil and Mrs. Dash in medium bowl.
Cut tuna into 1 1/2-inch cubes and marinate in vinegar mixture 1 hour.
Cut pepper into 1 1/2-inch cubes.
Alternate pepper and tuna on skewers, starting and ending with pepper.
Cook on grill 15 to 20 minutes (or until done).

title: jo's boiled texas bar cake
directions: To make milk sour, just add 1 tablespoon white vinegar to the 1/2 cup milk. Do that and set aside.
Bring to a boil and set aside the water, margarine and cocoa.
Mix dry ingredients and then add boiled mixture and mix. Add sour milk. Stir and add egg last.
Mix all together. Bake in a 9
x 13-inch greased pan for 30 minutes at 350°.
Serve topped with vanilla or chocolate icing.

title: baked salmon
directions: In glass baking dish, melt the margarine.
Pour liquid from salmon and break into baking dish.
(Remove all bones as much as possible.)
Add onion and half of cream of mushroom soup.
Mix well.
Add the remainder of soup and spread evenly on top.
Bake for 30 minutes at 425° in preheated oven.
Serve with favorite vegetable, pan-fried potatoes and hot buttermilk biscuits.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: english toffee
directions: Brown almonds lightly on cookie sheet in the oven.
(You may change the quantity according to your taste.)
Melt butter; add sugar, salt and water.
Stir until sugar dissolves.
Cook to hard crack stage (310°F or 154°C), stirring constantly.
Add sliced, browned almonds.
Pour into greased cookie sheet and spread to about 1/4 inch thick.
Spread melted chocolate over top.
Cool. When cold, break into serving size pieces.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix together peanut butter and crushed graham cracker crumbs. Add powdered sugar.
Form into balls.
Set aside.

title: hamburg casserole
directions: Brown hamburg and onion in small amount of oil.
Season with salt and pepper.
Mix celery, soups, water, rice and soy sauce. Put in large casserole and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Top with noodles and bake another 15 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: To the eggs add butter, syrup, sugar, vanilla, and pecans. Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 1 hr.

title: willa's cake layers
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time; beat well.
Sift together the self-rising and cake flours.
Add flour and milk alternately.
Add vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Makes 3 layers.

title: skillet barbecue chicken
directions: Season chicken with salt and pepper.
Place in ungreased large skillet.
Combine Coca-Cola and ketchup; pour over chicken.
Cover and bake in oven for 45 to 55 minutes or until chicken is tender.

title: salsa sauce
directions: Combine and boil 10 minutes.
Process 15 minutes.

title: tim's quick meal
directions: Heat Veg-All with other ingredients and simmer while rice is cooking.
Serve over hot rice.
Delicious with tossed salad or slaw for complete meal.
(Bread of any kind.)

title: stuffed cabbage rolls
directions: Wilt cabbage leaves in hot water.
Blend beef, rice, butter, tomato paste, onions, salt, red pepper and cinnamon together. Place 2 heaping tablespoons of mixture in each leaf.
Roll firmly and secure with toothpick.
Cover bottom of large saucepan with mint leaves.
Arrange rolls close together in pan.
Cover with tomatoes.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 45 minutes.
Add lemon juice.
Simmer for 15 to 20 minutes longer, until rice is done.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Boil sweet potatoes in clear water until tender.
Peel while warm.
Put in large mixer bowl and, while warm, mash at low speed. Add butter, sugar, egg, milk and vanilla.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake at 350° until well set and lightly browned, about 30 to 40 minutes.

title: lapizzrito
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease the bottom of a 10-inch iron skillet (preferred) or a 10-inch pie pan or dish with the melted butter.

title: japanese fruit cake
directions: Mix cake
mix
as
directions say.
Take out enough mix for 1 plain
layer.
To
remaining
mix, add nuts and spices. Bake 20 to 25 minutes until toothpick stuck in center of cake comes out clean.
When
cake
is cool, spread Royal Pineapple Filling (page 72)
between layers, putting light layer in the middle.
Frost top
and sides with Betty Crocker fluffy white frosting mix.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Mix and press into 8 x 8-inch or 8 x 12-inch dish.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Cook sausage until brown, stirring to crumble.
Drain well. Beat eggs well and mix all ingredients together.
Put in a 2-quart buttered baking dish.
Cover and chill overnight.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes or until set.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix together the broccoli, onion, bacon, raisins, sunflower seeds and celery. Add mayonnaise, vinegar and sugar. Stir well.

title: banana nut loaf
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 7 1/2 x 3 1/2-inch loaf pan.
Blend together all ingredients.
Pour batter into prepared pan.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Cool.

title: raisin fudge squares
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and chocolate; beat well.
Add flour, raisins and vanilla; mix well.
Pour into greased shallow pan (batter 1/2 inch thick).
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: fruit dip
directions: Soften cream cheese; add Marshmallow Creme and extract.
Blend until smooth.

title: chili
directions: Saute onions, garlic and green pepper until tender.
Brown ground beef and drain.
Add onions, garlic and peppers to ground beef, then add tomatoes (cut up or crushed) to mixture.
Bring mixture to a boil and simmer until tomatoes cook down.
At the same time, add seasonings to taste.
Sometimes, I let this mixture sit overnight by adding beans, then reheat and serve next day. Serves 6.

title: pecan crunch cookies
directions: Cream together butter, sugar and vanilla.
Add crushed potato chips and chopped nuts.
Stir in flour.
Form into small balls (about the size of a walnut).
Place on ungreased baking sheet. Press down with a glass dipped in sugar.
Decorate with half a candied cherry or a pecan half.
Bake in 350° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: cream cheese cookies
directions: Cream the shortening, cream cheese and sugar. Add vanilla to egg yolk and add both to creamed mixture. Add flour and salt.
Mix well. Drop by teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 325° for 12 minutes. Cool and frost.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Squeeze lemon and grate rind.
Mix all ingredients.
Pour into crust and bake.
Beat whites of eggs and add 3 tablespoons sugar. Brown in hot oven.

title: hot milk cake
directions: Beat eggs and sugar, mixing well.
Sift flour and baking powder and add to egg-sugar mixture.
Heat butter and milk, add to mixture.
Add vanilla.
Place in
large
tube
pan.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool before removing.

title: onion and red pepper relish
directions: In a medium frying pan over medium-high heat, combine the red onion, garlic, sugar, vinegar, salt, mustard seeds, black pepper, cloves and 2 tablespoons water.
Bring the mixture to a simmer and cook 5 minutes.
Add the red pepper and cook until vegetables are tender-crisp, 7 to 9 minutes.
Cover and chill.
Serve with burgers, hot dogs or sandwiches.
Fat free!

title: decorator icing
directions: Mix salt with warm water.
In mixer, mix shortening, flour and salted water.
Blend well.
Add flavorings and mix.
Add powdered sugar and blend 5-7 minutes.
2 lbs. of powdered sugar ices 5-6 batches of sugar cookies or 1 cake mix cake.

title: molasses chocolate cake(very moist cake)
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: basic salsa
directions: Combine in a medium bowl. Can be served at room temperature or refrigerated.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients (except tomato sauce) together.
Make into a meat loaf; put in pan and pour tomato sauce over meat loaf. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream butter, cream cheese and sugar. Add salt and vanilla.
Beat well.
Then add eggs, one at a time; beating after each.
Stir in flour last.
Then mix well.
Bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: puppy tacos
directions: Put a cooked hot dog into warmed taco shell.
Put shredded Cheddar cheese on top.
Add catsup and mustard or onion, etc.
Also can add lettuce, tomato or taco sauce.

title: black beans and rice
directions: Soak beans and green pepper in approximately 10 cups water. Cook in same water approximately 45 minutes.
Put olive oil, onion, garlic, 1/2 green pepper and 1 cup mashed beans in a frying pan.
Add to beans in pot.
Put in salt, paprika, oregano and bay leaf.
Cook 1 hour; then add vinegar and red wine.
Cook 1 more hour.
Serve with cooked rice.

title: fresh pear salad
directions: Core and quarter pears. Core and cut apple into wedges.
Peel and slice oranges.
Arrange fruit on platter lined with salad greens.

title: german apple cake
directions: Beat eggs until frosty.
Add oil, vanilla and sugar; beat well.
Mix dry ingredients together in another bowl; gradually mix into egg mixture.
Fold in apples and nuts.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with butterscotch morsels and bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Combine sugars and flour. Add milk and beaten eggs.
Stir until thoroughly blended. Add melted margarine, vanilla and pecans.
Stir.
Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.
Lower oven temperature to 375° and continue to bake for 30 to 35 minutes. Yields 2 pies.

title: quiche
directions: Fry bacon and chip into pieces; place on bottom of pie shell. Top with shredded cheeses and minced onion.
Mix eggs, cream, salt, sugar and pepper together.
Pour over cheeses in pie shell. Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Then reduce heat to 300° and bake for 30 minutes.
Allow to cool for 15 minutes.

title: chicken and wild rice
directions: Cook and dice chicken breast.
Cook rice according to directions.
Simmer onions in margarine; add flour and stir.
Add soup, milk and mushrooms.
In casserole dish, layer chicken, rice and sauce.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: chocolate goobers
directions: In small mixing bowl combine sugar and graham cracker crumbs; set aside.
In small saucepan heat butter and peanut butter over low heat until melted.
Pour over sugar mixture in small bowl. Shape dough into 1-inch balls.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, flour (do not sift) and salt together in pan.
Add well beaten egg yolks with milk.
Stir in dry ingredients and mix well.
Cook over medium heat until thick.
Add vanilla and butter and pour into precooked pie shell.
Top with meringue and brown in oven.

title: chicken-macaroni salad
directions: Cook noodles.
Drain.
While warm, add chicken and Italian dressing. Blend mayonnaise, lemon juice and mustard.
Add olives, onion, celery, cucumber, pepper and salt.
Combine vegetable mixture with the chicken-macaroni mixture. Chill at least 2 hours. Serves 4 to 8.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix together pineapple, fruit cocktail and pudding.
When thick, add the nutmeats and one-half of the whipped topping.
Top with the other half of the whipped topping.

title: banana freeze slices
directions: Place chocolate in saucepan over low heat and stir constantly until chocolate melts.
Remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter. Peel bananas and dip or roll in chocolate, coating bananas on all sides.
Roll bananas in cereal.
Freeze until firm, at least 4 hours.
Cut into 1/2-inch slices.

title: touch down taco
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Spread bean dip in baking pan. In large bowl combine

cream cheese, sour cream and taco seasoning. Mix well. Place garlic in mixture and mix well. Spread on top of bean dip. Grate cheddar on top. Bake 20 minutes. Remove from oven and top with, olives, tomatoes, onion and garnish with sour cream. Sprinkle top with tortilla chips. Serve warm.

title: strawberry jello salad
directions: Add boiling water to jello, stir until dissolved.
Add frozen strawberries and mix gently.
Chill until slightly congealed.
Add pineapple and nuts.
Pour 1/2 of mixture into oiled mold. Refrigerate to harden.
To other 1/2 fold in sour cream.
Pour on top of hardened mixture.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: cornbread skillet casserole
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients in a bowl and set aside.
Cook ground beef until browned.
Drain well and set aside.
Pour half of corn meal mixture into a greased 10 1/2-inch cash iron skillet.

title: corn salad
directions: Mix all the ingredients. Refrigerate.

title: pickled beans or corn(may be put together)
directions: You will need a 5-gallon jar.
Cook green beans or corn until done.
Let cool.
Cut corn off cob (corn may be pickled on cob, if desired).
Mix salt in 4 gallons of water, pour over beans or corn or both.
Press down, lay grape leaves or brown paper on top.
Lay a clean creek rock on top to hold down.
Cover jar.
Top with clean white cloth.
The corn and beans may be layered in jar and pickled together.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Beat all together with electric mixer until smooth.
Then fold in 1 (9 ounce) container Cool Whip, thawed.
Pour into a graham cracker crust and freeze.
Remove from freezer 1/2 hour before serving.

title: fudge brownies
directions: Grease and dust with flour a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan and set aside. Use a deep plastic bowl or mixing bowl and mix batter (sugar and cocoa) in bowl; mix well.
Put oleo or Crisco on top of mix and microwave 1 to 2 minutes to melt oleo.
Add cooking oil; add eggs, one at a time, and beat after each one.
Add flour, a little at a time, and beat if batter gets too thick; microwave a little more. Add vanilla and chopped nuts, if wanted.
Pour batter into greased pan and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: purple cow salad
directions: Dissolve jello in
boiling
water.
Let
stand	for
10 minutes.
Mix pie
filling,
pineapple and nuts.
Add to jello and mix well.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch dish and chill until set. Mix remaining ingredients
and	spread	topping
on set jello. Refrigerate.
Cut in squares and serve on lettuce.

title: judy's corn chowder
directions: Cut potatoes into bite size pieces.
Boil potatoes and onion in enough water to cover.
Add the rest of the ingredients and simmer until warmed through.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Using an electric mixer, mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a loaf pan and bake at 325° for 60 to 70 minutes.

title: husband's delight
directions: Brown beef and pour off fat.
Add seasonings and tomato sauce. Cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Cook noodles and drain.
Mix scallions, cream cheese and sour cream.
Make a layer each of noodles, meat sauce and sour cream mixture in greased casserole. Sprinkle top with grated cheese.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 minutes.

title: hush puppies *
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add all milk and beat well.
Add all the dry ingredients and onions.
Cook in deep fat at 350°.
They should be mealy on the inside and a golden crisp brown on the outside.
If the dough becomes too thick, add more milk.
Wonderful with fish and soups, especially with Brunswick Stew.

title: ice cream cake
directions: Make cake as directed.
Cool.
Line bottom and sides of cake pan with waxed paper, leaving some hanging over.
Freeze ice cream until firm.
When firm, place between layers of cake.
Frost cake with Cool Whip.
Garnish anyway you want.

title: hash potatoes for a gang
directions: Mix all ingredients together and place in 9 x 13-inch pan. Make topping by crushing 2 cups corn flakes and 1/2 cup melted butter to sprinkle over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
This can be prepared ahead of time, placed in the refrigerator and baked prior to serving.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Put pecan pieces in bottom of sheet cake pan.
Mix cake mix as directed on box; pour over pecans.
Mix the powdered sugar, room temperature soft margarine and cream cheese.
Drop by spoonfuls on top of cake mix.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: honey-vanilla oat bran muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Combine dry ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Stir in raisins and nuts.
Combine liquid ingredients in a small bowl.
Mix well.
Stir liquid ingredients into dry ingredients just until moistened.
Fill 12 paper lined muffin cups to 3/4 full.
Bake 15 to 18 minutes.

title: marge's banana bread
directions: You may add some spices, cinnamon, cloves or perhaps allspice.

title: rissetto salsa
directions: Remove seed from peppers and chop finely or grind.
Wear gloves when working with the peppers if they are hot ones.
Wash, scald and peel tomatoes.
Mix all ingredients, bring to a boil and simmer 10 minutes.
Refrigerate and use salsa fresh or pack in jars for future use.
Sterilize canning jars, pack mixture into hot jars, leave 1/4-inch headspace.
Wipe off rims of jar, seal with sterilized canning lids.
Submerge in a hot water bath, cover and bring to a boil.
Boil for 15 minutes for pints, 20 minutes for quarts.
Remove from water and let sit for 24 hours.
Check lids on jars for proper seal.
Refrigerate any jars that did not seal properly.
Recipe yields about 6 pints.

title: macaroni fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple and oranges, reserving juice and refrigerate. In saucepan, mix sugar, salt, flour and juice.
When well heated, add beaten eggs.
Cook until thick.
Cool.
Pour over macaroni and fruit.
Mix.
Refrigerate overnight.
Fold in 8 ounces Cool Whip. Mix well.
Refrigerate.

title: ice cream fudge dessert
directions: Press the cookies and butter (mixed) into a 9 x 13-inch pan for the bottom crust.
Freeze.
Put the ice cream over the crust, freeze again.
Cook
milk,	sugar
and
chocolate
over medium heat,
stirring
constantly until thick.
Cool.
Spread over the ice
cream. Top with whipped cream (Cool Whip freezes nicely) and chopped nuts.
Keep frozen until ready to serve.

title: souper soup
directions: Cook until done. You may add other vegetables.
Cauliflower or turnips are good.

title: burritos
directions: Mix together in a bowl.
Cheese and salsa can be added for taste.
Should make 10 to 12 burritos.
Can be frozen.

title: pasta sauce(fat free)
directions: Simmer on low for 2 hours, then cool.
Makes 1 gallon.
Can separate into 4 quart containers for quick meals.

title: foolproof pie crust
directions: In large bowl, stir together with fork flour, sugar and salt. Cut in shortening until crumbly.

title: rice and mushrooms
directions: Brown the rice in the butter.
Add mushrooms and saute.
Add the soup and water.
Cover and simmer until the liquid is absorbed.
Stir frequently.
Yields 3 to 4 servings.

title: microwave rice krispie treats
directions: Place butter in a 12 x 7-inch or 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish. Microwave for 1 to 1 1/2 minutes on Medium-high (Roast) or until melted.
Stir in marshmallows.
Microwave 1 minute on Medium-high (Roast).
Stir and continue cooking for about 1 1/2 to 2 minutes on Medium-high (Roast) or until marshmallows are softened.
Stir until smooth.
(Add peanut butter now if desired and stir until smooth.) Mix in cereal.
Press into dish.
Cool until set.
Cut into squares.

title: barbecue beans
directions: Brown onion and ground beef until well done.
Add all other ingredients and simmer over low heat until flavors are absorbed.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix the green beans and soup together.
Put in casserole dish. Lay dried onions on top. Bake at 350° until it bubbles on the side a little.

title: smothered hamburger patties
directions: Place ground beef in bowl.
Season all together.
Shape ground beef into thick patties.
Brown on each side in 1 tablespoon shortening.
After browning all of the meat, pour out all, except 1 tablespoon, of fat out of the skillet.
Pour mushroom soup into skillet.
Add 1/2 can of water; stir until mixed.
Place meat patties into mixture.
Slice onion and lay slices on top of meat. Cook under low heat for 45 minutes.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in buttered dish or pan at 300° for 45 minutes (or slightly less).
Serve with butter (if you want more calories!).

title: shrimp mold
directions: In a pot, warm together:
tomato soup and Knox gelatine (add gelatine after soup is warm); then stir in cream cheese and beat until smooth.
Add celery, green peppers, onions, salad dressing and shrimp.
Stir well.
Pour into mold and refrigerate until firm.
Serve with serving knife on crackers.
Will keep 3 to 4 days.

title: corn casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake in greased casserole until firm, about 50 minutes at 350°.

title: hash brown potatoes
directions: Mix everything together, then add hash browns.
Pour in greased baking dish.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Dribble butter on top. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 10.

title: cabbage salad dressing
directions: Boil sugar and vinegar 1 minute.
Cool.
Add salad dressing, salt and pepper.

title: corn oysters
directions: Mix all together.
Fry in deep fat until brown.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Makes 1 large or 2 small casseroles. Bake about 45 minutes at 350°.
Can be made ahead and frozen.
If frozen, be sure to allow more baking time.

title: pistachio pudding salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in a cake pan.
Chill.
Cut in squares.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add syrup, well-beaten eggs, salt and vanilla.
When well mixed, add coarsely chopped pecans.
Turn into pie plate lined with pastry.
Bake in moderate 350° oven about 1/2 to 1 hour or until firm.

title: taffy apple salad
directions: Drain pineapple; save juice.
Beat egg, sugar, flour and vinegar into juice.
Cook over medium heat until thick, stirring constantly, until it bubbles.
Cool completely.
Stir in remaining ingredients and chill.
Makes 8 servings.

title: quick and easy banana bread
directions: Mix first six ingredients together.
Next, add two well-beaten eggs.
Next, add three mashed ripe bananas.
Mix on low speed until blended.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix broccoli and onion and cook until tender; drain.
Mix all ingredients together and pour into hot greased pan and bake until done.
Serve warm.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until light and fluffy.
Add oil, zucchini, sugar and vanilla.
Mix well and blend in dry ingredients.
Add nuts and cherries.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: fruit-peanut salad
directions: Finely chop salted peanuts.
Cut bananas into chunks; roll in the peanuts.
Slice up the apples, cherries and grapes.
Mix into the Cool Whip all fruit except grapes and cherries.
Place lettuce leaves on plates.
Spoon onto leaves the fruit salad.
Mix cashews, grapes, cherries and coconut.
Sprinkle over the top of the fruit salad on plates and serve.

title: waffles or pancakes
directions: In a large bowl, beat egg yolks with mixture until light.
Add sugar and milk, blend well.
Sift flour and add gradually to egg mixture.
Pour in margarine and stir to blend.
In a separate bowl, beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold into batter with rubber spatula. Cook in a hot waffle iron until steaming stops, or cook as pancakes on griddle.
This batter keeps well in refrigerator for several days.
Yield:
6-8 waffles or pancakes.

title: raspberry tangy salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water and set aside to cool. Soften cream cheese with mayo and add gradually the pineapple, bananas and nuts.
When gelatin mixture begins to thicken, add cheese mixture.
Fold in whipped cream.
Chill until firm in 1-quart mold.
In summer, fresh strawberries can be added.

title: lemon buttermilk pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Beat sugar and butter until creamy. Add eggs, 1 at a time, beating well after each addition. Add buttermilk, cornstarch, lemon juice and salt; mix well. Pour filling into crust. Bake 55 to 60 minutes or until done.

title: no bake peanut butter cookies
directions: Boil sugar, butter and milk for 3 minutes.
Add rolled oats, peanut butter and vanilla.
Drop by tablespoon on waxed paper.

title: zucchini cookies
directions: Cream oleo, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients, zucchini and raisins.
Drop onto greased cookie sheet.
Cookies don't spread.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: macaroni au gratin
directions: Cook macaroni and place in buttered casserole.
Melt butter in saucepan.
Add flour and milk; stir slowly until it thickens and add salt and pepper.
Cut cheese into cubes and scatter over macaroni.
Cover top with bread crumbs.
Pour sauce over all. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Grind up calves liver.
Mix in ground beef.
Add eggs, onion and garlic.
Put tomato sauce on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, or until done.

title: sausage potato casserole
directions: In large skillet, cook sausage until no longer pink.
In a bowl, combine soup, milk, onion, salt and pepper.
In an ungreased 11 X 7-inch baking dish, layer half the potatoes, soup mixture and sausage. Repeat layers.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hrs.
Uncover and sprinkle cheese on top.
Cook 5 mins. until cheese is melted.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix sugar, salt and syrup.
Add beaten eggs.
Line pie pan with plain pastry.
Place pecans in it, then pour in filling. Pecans will rise to top.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 10 minutes, then reduce heat to 300° and bake until filling is set. If pie becomes too brown, cover with piece of plain paper.

title: dill bread
directions: Warm cottage cheese and butter over low heat.
Mix warm water and yeast.
Let stand.
Beat soda, onion flakes and sugar with a fork.
Dump all these in with egg mixture.
Add flour.
Let rise until doubled, 40 to 50 minutes.
Punch down and put in 2-quart casserole and let stand 30 minutes.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350° (until brown).

title: low-fat baking mix
directions: Mix together.
Store in No. 3 coffee can in cool, dry place.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Sift together the dry ingredients.
Add raisins, chopped walnuts, melted butter and applesauce.
Beat until well blended. Pour into greased and floured 9 x 9 x 2-inch or 11 1/4 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch pan.
Bake in moderate oven, 350°, for 45 to 50 minutes. Cool; spread with confectioners sugar butter icing; sprinkle with shredded orange rind.
Decorate with whole walnut meat.

title: refrigerator fruitcake
directions: Roll wafers until finely crushed.
Chop pecans and cut cherries.
Mix all ingredients together.
Press tightly in loaf pan.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: golden cheddar puffs
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Prepare as usual.
Beat in 1/2 cup of cheese.
Drop by spoonfuls.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese and sesame seed.
Bake until firm and golden, 25 to 30 minutes. Pierce top with knife.
Bake 5 minutes longer.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add berries, pineapple, bananas and nuts if desired.
Chill and serve.

title: ham and cheese casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except 1/2 of the cheese.
Put in a greased casserole and top with remaining cheese.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar.
Add
egg,
flour, baking powder, salt and milk.
Mix well, then add blueberries. Bake in tins for 20 minutes at 400°.

title: jumbo cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Lightly grease cookie sheet.
Mix brownie mix (dry), flour, oil, water and eggs until well blended. Stir in M&M's.
Drop by tablespoonfuls onto cookie sheet.
Bake until just set, 10 to 12 minutes.
Let stand 2 to 3 minutes before removing from cookie sheet.
Cool completely on rack.

title: moe's spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti according to box directions.
Drain and rinse with cold water until cool.
After water is completely drained, add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Enjoy.

title: broccoli dip
directions: Cook broccoli as directed.
Drain.
Saute onion in butter. Add soup, cheese and seasonings.
Add broccoli, mushrooms and nuts.
Serve hot on crackers.

title: fruit salad or dessert
directions: Mix all fruit with juices and add pudding.
Stir until smooth. Chill and serve.
Can be frozen and served icy.

title: corn flake krispies
directions: Put sugar and syrup in large pan and cook to soft ball stage (about 1 minute).
Take off heat, add peanut butter and stir good. Pour in corn flakes.
Stir until coated.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Fresh or frozen pumpkin is best.
Mix all ingredients except milk in food processor.
Add milk.
Pour into 2 deep dish unbaked pie crusts.
Place on cookie sheet and bake at 300° for 30 minutes.
Reduce heat to 275° until golden brown.

title: jambalaya
directions: Cook and stir onions, green pepper, garlic and 2 tablespoons of the oil in 4-quart Dutch oven over low heat 3 minutes.
Add shrimp. Cook, stirring frequently until shrimp are pink, about 5 minutes. Turn shrimp mixture into bowl; reserve.

Cook remaining 1 tablespoon oil and the rice in Dutch oven over medium-high heat, stirring frequently until rice is light brown, about 10 minutes. Stir in chicken broth, tomatoes (with liquid), salt, pepper, thyme, pepper sauce and bay leaf.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer until rice is tender, about 15 minutes.
Stir in reserved shrimp mixture and the ham.
Cover and cook just until shrimp and ham are hot.
Makes 6 servings.

title: shriner's corn dogs
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Cut in shortening and add milk and egg.
More milk may be used if a thinner batter is desired. Place stick in hot dog and dip in batter.
Fry in deep fryer until golden brown.

title: zucchini cobbler
directions: Cook zucchini in lemon juice until tender (about 20 minutes). Add sugar, nutmeg and cinnamon. Simmer one more minute. Add 1/2 cup of crust mixture to thicken.

title: impossible cheeseburger pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease a 10-inch pie plate.
Brown beef and onion; drain.
Stir in salt and pepper.
Spread in plate. Beat milk, eggs and baking mix until smooth.
Pour into plate. Bake 25 minutes.
Sprinkle top of pie with 1 cup cheese.
Bake until knife inserted comes out clean, 5 to 8 minutes.
Cool for 5 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.
You can also top pie with sliced tomatoes before you sprinkle the cheese on.
Then follow directions the same.

title: cherry cheese delight
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs, margarine, gelatin and powdered sugar; put in 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Combine remaining ingredients until fluffy.
Pour over crumb mixture, then spread 2 cans cherry pie filling over this and refrigerate 24 hours.
A favorite.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Put chicken in a large cooker to boil.
Cook until well done. Remove the chicken from the cook pot.

title: stir-fry salad pizza
directions: Place crust on baking sheet (12-inches).
Prick bottom.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes or until golden.
Preheat a wok or large skillet over high heat.
Add cooking oil.
Stir-fry garlic and fennel in hot oil for 30 seconds.
Add mushrooms and stir-fry for 1 minute.
Add Canadian bacon to wok and stir-fry for 1 minute.
Remove wok from heat.
Add greens to wok and toss. Sprinkle 1 1/2 cups cheese over crust.
Broil 5 inches from the heat for 1 to 2 minutes, until cheese melts.
Spoon wok mixture evenly over crust to within 1 inch of the edge.
Sprinkle remaining cheese atop.
Broil 5 inches from heat for 1 minute.

title: pineapple punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid, sugar, ginger ale and water.
Add pineapple juice and stir.
Pour over ice to serve.

title: corn-onion shortcake
directions: In pan, melt oleo and saute onion until it's transparent.
Set aside and drain.
In bowl, combine cornbread mix, milk, egg and corn.
Mix well.
Add drained onion.
Spoon into a greased 9-inch baking pan.
Spread cheese over batter.
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes.
Cut into squares and serve.
This is soooo good!!

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Slice tomatoes in 1/4-inch slices.
Stir egg and water until egg is mixed well with water.
Pour egg wash over tomatoes.
Mix meal, flour, salt and pepper together.
Batter tomato slices in meal mixture.
Fry in skillet in about 1 inch of Crisco oil over medium heat.
When tomatoes are golden brown on one side, turn over and cook until brown on both sides.

title: philly cream cheese chive sauce
directions: Stir cream cheese and milk in saucepan over low heat until smooth.
Stir in chives, lemon juice and garlic salt.
Preparation time:
5 minutes.

title: marinara sauce(tomato sauce)
directions: Heat olive oil in a pan.
Saute garlic until brown, stirring frequently.
Remove from heat (to avoid splashing).
Add tomatoes. Return to heat.
Add tomato paste, 2/3 cup water, salt, pepper and sugar.
Stir well.
Add fresh parsley.
Cook over very low heat for 45 minutes to 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Add more parsley for garnish.
Serve cheese with this if you like.

title: almond chicken breast
directions: Fifteen to 30 minutes before you're ready to bake, preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly butter bottom of ovenproof baking dish.

title: play dough
directions: Mix together and cook over low heat, stirring constantly.
When it sticks together, remove from pan.
Keep in covered containers.

title: hot mexican dish
directions: Blend avocados, lemon juice, salt and pepper together.
Mix sour cream, mayonnaise and taco seasoning together.
Heat refried beans and put in bottom of glass baking dish.
Add avocado mixture to the sour cream mixture, then layer onions, tomatoes, olives and cheese.
Place in 325° oven until cheese is melted or desired consistency obtained.
For extra spice, add small jar taco sauce before putting on cheese or put on top as it is served.

title: green bean parmesan
directions: Take the green beans and dump them in a bowl. Sprinkle the Parmesan cheese and seasoned salt on top. Cover the bowl with waxed paper. Cook for 5 minutes on Medium-high in the microwave.

title: potato burgers
directions: Grate potatoes into a large bowl.
Add all other ingredients except tomato sauce; mix well.
Make into patties or meat balls; brown on both sides.
Put in baking dish.
Pour tomato sauce over meat, cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve with rice.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together (except nuts) and form into ball. Roll in nuts and garnish with parsley.

title: colonial cranberry salad
directions: Combine 1 cup water, sugar and cranberries in saucepan; bring just to a boil.
Remove from heat; cover and let cool for 5 minutes.
Combine 1 cup boiling water and gelatin; stir until dissolved.
Add 1 cup cold water, cranberry mixture and lemon juice.
Chill until partially congealed.
Fold in remaining ingredients.
Chill until firm.

title: pickled corn-on-the-cob
directions: Husk and silk corn and boil for about 5 minutes.
Remove from water and put in a churn or 10 gallon jar.
Dissolve 1 cup salt per gallon of fresh water.
Be sure corn is well covered.
Weight down with plate or some other suitable weight.
Tie cloth over vessel to cover.
Let stand 2 or 3 weeks.
Keep mold dipped off as it forms so that the corn will not be musty.
Corn can be cut off and canned if desired.

title: mother's forgotten cookies
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add sugar gradually.
Add chocolate chips, mint flavoring and food coloring.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Twist to make a peak.
Turn off oven.
Put cookies in the oven and leave overnight.
Makes 45 small cookies.

title: italian parmesan bread
directions: In
a
large mixing bowl, dissolve yeast in warm water. Add
2 cups flour, 1/4 cup butter, egg, sugar, seasonings and salt. Beat
at
low
speed
until
mixed,
about
30 seconds. Increase speed
to medium and continue beating for 2 minutes. Stir in remaining flour and 1/3 cup cheese; beat until smooth. Cover bowl and let rise in a warm place until doubled, about 1 hour.
Stir batter 25 strokes.
Spread batter into a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole;
brush
with
melted butter and sprinkle with
the remaining cheese.
Cover and let rise until doubled, about
30 minutes.
Bake
at
about 35 minutes or until golden
brown. Cool
on
wire rack 10 minutes before removing from the casserole.
Yield:
1 loaf.
Diabetic Exchanges:
One serving (1 slice) equals 1 starch, 1/2 fat; also, 97 calories, 216
mg sodium,
21 mg cholesterol, 13 gm carbohydrates, 3 gm protein and 3 gm fat.

title: joyce's pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs. Add sugar and syrup, then add salt, vanilla and butter. Place pecans in bottom of uncooked pie shell. Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: quick cookies
directions: Mix together.
This will be stiff.
Drop by teaspoonful on greased cookie sheet. Cook 10 to 12 minutes or until done at 350°. These cookies will be soft when done.

title: chocolate cheese cake
directions: Heat oven to 300°.
Prepare chocolate crumb crust and set aside.

title: crustless pumpkin slices
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients in order given.
Pour into baking pan that has been greased and dusted with corn meal.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over top of pumpkin.
Next sprinkle nuts over the top. Melt butter and pour over last.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes. Reduce temperature to 350° and bake for 45 minutes longer.
Cool and serve with whipped cream.

title: cider citrus sparkle punch
directions: In large punch bowl, combine cider and concentrate.
Stir to dissolve.
Add ginger ale.
If desired, garnish with apple or lemon slices.
Serve over ice.

title: pork chop-potato casserole
directions: Brown chops in skillet; set aside.
Place potatoes, onions and bell pepper in alternate layers in casserole dish.
Season with salt and pepper.
Combine soup and milk; pour 1/2 of mixture over potatoes and onions.
Lay chops on top; pour remaining soup mixture over all.
Bake about 1 to 1 1/2 hours in 350° oven. Serves 6

title: dutch apple bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream together the margarine and the sugar.
Add and beat well the eggs and vanilla.
Combine separately the flour, soda and salt.
Add dry ingredients alternately with the sour milk.
Fold in the apples and walnuts. Bake in a greased and floured 9 x 5-inch loaf pan or several smaller loaf pans for 55 minutes or until loaf tests done.
Serve thin slices with whipped cream cheese.
Wonderful for Christmas gift giving.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Tear boiled chicken into small strips.
Mix the sour cream, soup and 2 tablespoons poppy seed together.
Fold in the chicken. Put in a buttered casserole dish.
Top with crackers and sprinkle 1 tablespoon of poppy seed.
Dot with butter and bake for 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: raisin-applesauce nut muffins
directions: Cream shortening or oil and sugar.
Combine remaining ingredients and mix until well blended.
Pour into greased muffin pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes until toothpick comes out clean.

title: chicken enchilada
directions: Mix together cream of chicken soup, sour cream, green chilies and onion for sauce.
Soften tortillas in microwave, if necessary. Spoon some sauce in bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Fill center of each tortilla with sauce, chicken and cheese.
Roll and place folded side down in pan.
Spread remaining sauce and cheeses over tortillas.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: secret kiss cookies
directions: In large mixer bowl, beat butter, granulated sugar and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Add flour and walnuts.
Beat on low speed of electric mixer until well blended.
Cover, refrigerate dough 1 to 2 hours or until firm enough to handle.
Remove wrappers from chocolate pieces.
Heat oven to 375°.
Using approximately 1 tablespoon of dough for each cookie, shape dough around each chocolate piece; roll to make ball.
(Be sure to cover each chocolate piece completely.)
Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until cookies are set but not brown. Cool slightly; remove from cookie sheet to wire rack.
While still slightly warm, roll in powdered sugar.
Cool completely. Store in tightly covered container.
Roll again in powdered sugar just before serving.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: lorraine's buns
directions: Mix flour, salt & sugar.
Mix yeast and water together and pour onto flour mixture.
Add oil & beaten eggs.
Knead dough and cover. One hour later, knead again.
Let sit for another hour.
Repeat this process 3 more times.
The last time you knead the dough, let it rest for 2 hours.
Then form buns on a greased cookie sheet and cover with towels until the next morning.
Bake uncovered in the morning at 350° for 12 mins. or longer.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Sift dry Jell-O on cottage cheese and stir.
Add fruit.
Mix in Cool Whip.
Chill overnight.

title: easy and quick sweet pickles
directions: Pour pickles out of the jar.
Wash out jar and wash pickles. Slice pickles round and put back into the jar.
Mix vinegar, sugar, onions and horseradish (if used) until sugar is pretty well dissolved and pour this mixture over the pickles in the jar. Shake the jar a few times and place in refrigerator.
Shake the jar again two or three times within 24 hours.
Better to let sit 36 to 48 hours before eating them. Should be refrigerated until used up.
(It makes them more crisp to keep refrigerated.)

title: eggplants-marinated
directions: Peel and slice thin.
Put in crock or glass container in layers with salt between layers.
Apply heavy weight for 24 hours. Pour out liquid and rinse well.
Return to container and cover with white vinegar.
Let set another 24 hours.
Squeeze out vinegar.
Add olive oil, minced garlic, oregano and crushed red pepper to taste.
Ready to eat or can be sealed in jar with oil.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix jello with 2 cups boiling water and 2 cups cold water; add cranberry sauce with pineapple and half of the nuts.
Pour 1/2 of the jello mixture in pan and jell until firm.
Save the other half of the mixture.

title: cat head biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients together, mixing well.
Roll out on floured paper.
Work in some of the dry flour.
Make the dough into a
loaf.
Pinch
off
in pieces about the size of a small apple.
Pat out with your hand.
Will make a large biscuit.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Combine blueberries, sugar and cornstarch.
Pour into pie crust.
Sprinkle with lemon juice.
Dot with butter.
Put top pie crust on and seal.
Cut small slices in top crust.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and cook 40 to 45 minutes. Cool and serve.
Serves 12.

title: easy pie crust
directions: Mix flour, salt, oil and water with table fork.
Form a ball with your hands and put between wax paper and roll out with rolling pin.
This makes one medium pie crust.
It gets flaky. Don't over roll it, that makes it tough!

title: savory chicken sauce
directions: Mix ingredients together; pour over chicken, then bake chicken as usual.

title: homemade soup
directions: You can add any vegetables you want.
I usually add stewed tomatoes and tomato juice.
Sometimes I add 1 can of cut green beans.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Dissolve soups together in milk.
Layer potatoes, onion and seasonings.
Pour in soups.
Bake 1 hour at 400°.

title: delicious chicken sandwiches
directions: Salt and flour chicken breasts.
Place chicken breasts in microwave-safe dish and cover.
Place breasts in microwave oven and cook on High 22 minutes.
Remove and cool chicken breasts.
Cut breasts in small chunks.
Place breasts in food blender and chop.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Break up spaghetti and boil in salted water until tender. Drain. Rinse with water and set aside.
Cut up vegetables.
Add Italian seasoning and Italian dressing to vegetables.
Mix with spaghetti and chill several hours. Serve cold.

title: strawberry pie
directions: In a saucepan, boil sugar and water together until sugar is dissolved.
Pour mixture over berries and let cool.
Drain syrup from berries and thicken with cornstarch which has been dissolved in cold water.
Cool.

title: blueberry bran muffins
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients and set aside.
Mix flour, sugar, baking powder, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg together.
Add dry mixed ingredients to the cereal mix.
Then add vanilla and blueberries. Pour into greased muffin tin or muffin liners.
Bake at 400° about 20 minutes or until lightly brown.
Makes about 14 muffins.

title: chocolate almond sundae squares
directions: Toast almonds at 350° for 20 minutes.
Crush wafers.
Reserve 1 cup.
Mix remaining with melted oleo.
Pat into 9 x 13-inch pan. Put on the almonds, then fudge.
Slice ice cream and put on top. Squish into place.
Sprinkle reserved crumbs.
Freeze.
Remove from freezer a bit before serving.

title: eggplant au gratin
directions: Peel and boil eggplant in salted water until soft.
Strain off water and mash.
Saute onion in margarine or butter.
Beat egg. Combine eggplant, onion, egg and cheese and place in greased casserole.
Cover with bread crumbs and dot with butter.
Bake in moderate oven for 30 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix ingredients in order listed.
Drop by spoonfuls, pressing down with a fork.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: swedish apple pie
directions: Slice and peel apples, enough to fill a lightly greased deep pie plate.
Sprinkle with 1 tablespoon of sugar and cinnamon.
Mix melted butter, flour, 1 cup sugar, egg, walnuts and salt together in small bowl.
Spoon over the apples and bake at 350° for about 45 minutes, until golden brown.
Serve with whipped cream or warm with ice cream.

title: easy pork chop supper
directions: Brown pork chops on both sides in frying pan.
Trim off excess fat.
Pour off grease.
Add potatoes, carrots, broccoli and onion. Mix soup with water until well blended.
Pour over pork chop mixture.
Add salt and pepper.
Cover and simmer 45 minutes to 1 hour or until potatoes are tender and soup mixture is the consistency of gravy.

title: mary brewer's peanut brittle
directions: Boil sugar, syrup and water until it spins a thread (210° on candy thermometer).
Add peanuts and butter.
Cook until golden brown, stirring gently.
Take from fire and add soda.
Beat well. Spread on two well-greased cookie sheets.
Let cool a bit then, using a spatula, lift the edges and pull thin.
Store in airtight container.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Cream shortening with 1 cup sugar and 1 cup brown sugar.
Add beaten eggs, milk and apples.
Beat in rest of the sifted dry ingredients.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased cake pan.
Sprinkle nut meats and 1/2 cup brown sugar over top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serve plain or with whipped cream.

title: herbie's 3 stage chili(from solid to liquid to gas)
directions: Brown hamburger and 1/2 of onion in skillet; drain.
Chop up green pepper, tomatoes and rest of onion; put in slow cooker.
Add all the beans; drain juice from kidney beans.
Put all in slow cooker and cook on low about 3 to 6 hours.

title: baked ham in a bag
directions: Use paper bag (not waxed) and place in a baking dish or just a baking dish if you prefer. Put ham slices in layers in bottom of bag.
Cover each ham layer with 1/4 cup brown sugar, a few celery leaves and a teaspoon of mustard.
Top with another layer of ham and repeat ingredients.
Fold down bag and bake 3/4 hour at 350°.

title: mississippi mud pie
directions: Heat oven to 250°, then melt butter and both chocolates in oven and let cool.
Increase oven temperature to 350°.
Dissolve coffee in sour cream and beat with eggs, sugar, corn syrup and vanilla until well blended.
Stir in chocolate and butter mixture, then pour into pie shell.
Bake 35 to 45 minutes or until filling puffs and forms a crisp, deeply cracked crust.
Let cool to room temperature, then serve with scoop of vanilla ice cream on top.

title: easy spinach quiche
directions: In a medium size bowl combine spinach souffle, eggs, milk, onion, mushrooms, bacon and grated cheese.
Pour spinach mixture in pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: easy oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix sugar, butter, cocoa and milk.
Boil for 3 minutes.
Add vanilla and oats.
Drop by spoonfuls on wax paper.

title: cheeseburger loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients except cheese and blend thoroughly. Line loaf pan with heavy waxed paper.
Place 1/2 cup cheese in bottom of pan; cover with half of meat mixture.
Repeat with remaining cheese and meat.
Bake at 350° about 1 hour.
Allow loaf to stand 10 minutes before turning out on platter.
Remove waxed paper; slice for serving and garnish if desired.
Makes 6 servings.

title: prosage sizzle
directions: Saute onion.
Add prosage and brown.
Boil noodles according to package directions.
Salt to taste.
In a large bowl, mix sour cream, cottage cheese and mushroom soup.
Combine noodles, prosage mix and cream mixture.
Pour into casserole and bake until bubbly at 400° for 45 minutes.

title: chocolate chip banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large mixing bowl, combine all ingredients except chocolate chips and walnuts.
Blend well on medium speed.
Stir in chips and walnuts.
Pour batter into greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake 60 to 65 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool 10 minutes.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: seasoned oyster crackers
directions: Mix seasonings, dressing mix and oil.
Pour over crackers in a big bowl.
Stir for several hours.

title: paper bag microwave caramel corn
directions: Bring brown sugar, butter, syrup and salt to boil on High power (2 1/2 to 3 minutes).
After it comes to a boil, microwave on High for 2 minutes more.
Remove from microwave and stir in baking soda.
Pour over popped corn.
Close bag and shake well. Put bag in microwave oven and cook on High for 1 1/2 minutes. Shake well.
Microwave 1 1/2 minutes more.
Shake.
Pour into large pan.
Cool.
Enjoy.

title: strawberry frost punch
directions: Place 2 cups of water in large metal pan. Add Jell-O and bring to a boil. Add sugar and citric acid to dissolve. Remove from heat and add pink lemonade and Bicardi mix to cool. When completely dissolved, add pineapple juice and fill pineapple can with water. Add to mixture. Divide into 4 one-gallon freezer bags and freeze.

title: butter frosting
directions: Cream butter in 1/4 cup sugar; add egg yolk.
Beat well.
Add remaining sugar, a little at a time.
For flavoring, add 1/2 teaspoon vanilla or other extract.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Line a buttered pan with graham crackers.
Mix pudding with milk.
Fold in Cool Whip.

title: shrimp mold
directions: Bring soup to a boil.
Beat in the cream cheese with a fork. Add gelatin and water together.
Mix in soup mixture.
Cool in icebox (1 hour), then add rest of ingredients.
Put in mold and set.

title: million dollar cookies
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar until fluffy.
Add egg, vanilla and salt.
Put dry ingredients with flour; beat in good with the sugar mixture.
Add nuts with the flour.
Make into small balls and roll in white sugar; roll flat with bottom of glass that's dipped in sugar.
Cook in greased cookie pan at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Mix sugar and syrup.
Bring to a boil. Stir in peanut butter and vanilla, then mix in Special K.
Drop by spoonful on wax paper.

title: yogurt pops
directions: Combine the yogurt, banana, vanilla and juice in a blender. Blend until the mixture is smooth.
Pour into 5 small individual paper cups.
Place in freezer until half frozen; insert a wooden stick into each cup.
To eat, turn the cup upside down and run hot water over it until the pop slips out.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Roll out 4 biscuits.
Cut in strips and add to mixture.
Roll out the 6 remaining biscuits and put on top for crust.
Bake at 400 degrees until brown.

title: mississippi mud
directions: Grease and flour 3-qt. casserole.
Melt 2 sticks butter with with 1/3 c. cocoa, then cool.
In second bowl, beat sugar and eggs until creamy.
Add flour and pecans.
Add the cooled cocoa mixture to the sugar mixture and add vanilla.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 to 35 minutes.
Spread marshmallow cream on hot cake as soon as it is removed from the oven.
While the cake is baking, prepare icing by melting the remaining butter, cocoa and milk, the add powdered sugar.
Nuts are optional.
Pour icing over the marshmallow cream.

title: banana pudding
directions: Layer vanilla wafers and sliced bananas.
Prepare instant banana pudding according to instructions on package.
Pour over vanilla wafers and sliced bananas; chill.
Top with whipped topping when serving.

title: crab meat dip
directions: Mix all together and chill.

title: apple pie topping
directions: Combine and cook until thick; let cool.
This is a topping for Apple Dumplings or you can put it on top of apple pie pieces.

title: egg custard
directions: Pour in uncooked pie shell.
Bake slowly until done.

title: beef and macaroni bake
directions: Brown beef, onion and green pepper in skillet.
Drain off fat. Add macaroni and cheese, tomato sauce, salt, garlic salt and oregano.
Spoon into 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Bake for 20 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese and parsley.
Bake 10 minutes longer.
Bake at 350°.

title: cranberry-apricot compote
directions: Cook over low heat for 20 minutes.
Delicious hot or cold with chicken or turkey dishes or other meats.

title: crunch drop cookies
directions: Add both kinds of cereal, coconut and nuts.
Batter is stiff so use your hands to mix it.
Drop teaspoon of batter onto greased cookie sheet.
Cookies spread during baking.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: portuguese sweet bread
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling water.
Reserve 1/2 cup potato water and mix in when potatoes are mashed.
Mix all dry ingredients together in a large bowl.

title: pineapple pound cake
directions: Cream Crisco, margarine and sugar.
Add sifted flour and baking powder together.
Add eggs and flour and beat after each. Add vanilla.
Fold in pineapple.
Cook in a tube cake pan at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: strawberry shortcake
directions: Sift flour, soda and salt.
Add Crisco (cut into flour until it resembles coarse meal).
Add buttermilk and mix well.
Divide dough into equal parts.
Roll first part out on floured waxed paper into 8-inch circle.
Put on baker (iron) and spread with melted butter.
Roll out second piece the same and top with butter.
Place on top of first piece.
Bake at 375° until browned (medium).
Cut into pie shaped wedges.
Split and cover with berries and cream.

title: hello dollies
directions: Melt butter.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add graham cracker crumbs to form crust.
Layer in order the chocolate chips, coconut and then the pecans.
Cover with condensed milk.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool before cutting into squares.
Can be made in advance and frozen.
Can use 1 1/2 cups graham cracker crumbs for less crust.
Refrigerate well before cutting to avoid gooey mess. The hardest part is cutting these things.

title: taco salad
directions: Combine everything but Doritos.
Then add Doritos just before serving.

title: homemade vegetable soup
directions: Put roast in Dutch oven.
Dissolve the bouillon cubes in hot water.
Add water just to top of roast.
Cook for about 20 minutes (to get good broth) in a 250° oven.

title: gingerbread
directions: Mix syrup, shortening, sugar and eggs.
Add flour gradually. Pour boiling water over soda and dissolve.
Add to mixture.
Add pecans.
Bake in a well-greased and floured pan at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: corn casserole
directions: Melt oleo in skillet.
Saute pepper and onion.
Mix rest of ingredients except cheese.
Pour into oblong baking dish (11 x 7-inch).
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.
Then sprinkle cheese and paprika on top.
Return to oven for 10 minutes.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix together and refrigerate.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and let it boil. Remove from heat. Cool 1 minute. Add last 4 items.
Mix well. Drop on waxed paper.

title: stuffed zucchini
directions: Parboil squash 5 minutes.
Cut squash in half; scoop out seeds and pepper.
Cook ground beef, celery and onion in butter until lightly browned.
Add tomato sauce and bread crumbs; mix well. Spoon meat mixture into squash.
Place in shallow baking dish and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until squash is tender.

title: blue ribbon cookies(bradley county fair jr. division 1960)
directions: Sift together the flour, soda and salt.
Add sugars, egg, vanilla and shortening.
Blend all ingredients.
Mix the batter until smooth, about 1 minute.
Add chopped nuts and chocolate chips.
Drop by teaspoon onto an ungreased baking sheet.
Place about 2 inches apart.
Bake in moderate oven (375°) for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: chewy cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Can be chewy cake or brownie style.
If baked in a cake pan, it will fall and look terrible, but is still wonderful.

title: nippy carrots
directions: Simmer the first 4 ingredients until bubbly. Pour over the carrots. Makes 4 servings.

title: oyster crackers
directions: In a paper sack, mix dry ingredients with crackers.
Dribble oil over and shake.
Leave in sack and shake as you pass by it for about 3 hours.
Store in an airtight container.

title: punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together, then fill rest of way with water.
Makes 1 gallon punch.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Add lemon juice and beat.
Add milk and Cool Whip.
Mix well.
Fold in drained pineapple and nuts.
Pour into pie shells.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix first six ingredients together until creamy.
Add flour, stir until blended.
If batter is too loose, add a little more flour.
Roll dough into small balls and flatten with fork.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet in 350° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: granny's fruitcake
directions: Boil raisins and water 2 minutes, then cool.
Add to boiled mixture remaining ingredients.
Cook 1 hour or until toothpick comes out clean in a greased and floured tube pan.

title: joe's dinner
directions: Cook macaroni until done.
In separate pot, brown beef and onions.
Then add tomatoes, salt, tomato paste, ketchup and Worcestershire sauce; let simmer.

title: doughnut balls
directions: In medium bowl, combine mix, 1/4 cup sugar, 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon and nutmeg.
Add eggs, milk and vanilla.
Stir until well blended.
Heat oil to 400°.
Drop batter by rounded tablespoonfuls into hot oil and fry 3 minutes or until brown.
Drain on paper towels.

title: sis' chocolate revel bars
directions: Cream 1 cup margarine.
Add flour, brown sugar, eggs, vanilla and soda.
Mix well.
Add oatmeal.
Batter will be heavy.
Melt chocolate chips and add margarine and condensed milk.
Place heavy batter mixture in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread chocolate mixture on top.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: corn bread salad
directions: Crumble cornbread and bacon together very fine.
Chop onion, pepper and tomato very fine.
Add to cornbread mixture.
Add pepper and enough mayonnaise until very moist.
(This takes a lot of mayonnaise.)
Refrigerate.

title: molded cheese salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water and chill until it begins to thicken.
Whip until fluffy and fold in remaining ingredients. Pour into mold and chill until firm.
Serve.

title: 3 hour stew
directions: Brown meat
well.
Cover
with
water and add all other seasonings.
Simmer on top of stove or in oven at 300° to 325° for 1 hour.
Add carrots,
big
stalk
of
celery and green beans. Cook another hour.
Add
water
as needed to keep meat and vegetables covered.
Put
in
potatoes
and green peas the last 40 minutes or until
potatoes
are
done.
Mix
flour and water to thin paste and thicken stew to desired consistency.

title: passover date nut cake
directions: Beat eggs.
Add oil and sugar.
Beat well.
Chop dates and nuts.
Add to mixture with remainder of ingredients. Pour into greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Cut into squares a few minutes after removing from oven.

title: tacos
directions: Brown and drain hamburger.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer until onion is done.
Serve inside taco shells with shredded cheese, lettuce, onions, chopped olives and sour cream.

title: layered enchilada casserole
directions: Cook meat.
After done, stir in beans, seasoning and 1 cup water.
Pour sauce into pie plate.
Dip tortillas in sauce and place in casserole dish.
Layer meat and tortillas.
Sprinkle cheese over all and bake 20 minutes.

title: no bake chocolate cookies
directions: Combine in saucepan the first 4 ingredients; bring to a boil. Boil hard for 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add the remaining ingredients.
Blend well.
Work quickly.
Drop on wax paper.
Let cool.
Eat!

title: chicken salsa spaghetti
directions: Saut onions in butter until clear, then place in the bottom of casserole dish. Mix the salsa, cheese dip and soup thoroughly. Add spaghetti and chicken and stir well.
Pour into casserole dish; top with cheese. Bake in 350° oven until bubbly. Allow to set for 10 minutes before serving.

title: tomato sauce
directions: Heat the oil in a saucepan and add the garlic.
Cook briefly, stirring.
Add the tomatoes, oregano, rosemary, salt and pepper. Bring to a boil and cook, stirring occasionally, about 15 minutes. Stir in the basil and serve hot.
Yield:
About 1 1/2 cups.

title: rice meatballs in tomato sauce
directions: Cook rice until
dry.
Let
cool
slightly;
add onion, green pepper, egg,
meat
and salt and pepper.
Mix thoroughly and shape into balls.
Brown in skillet.
Place in flat baking dish or skillet.
Pour
tomato sauce over all using some water if mixture is too thick.
Bake
to 60 mintues or on top of stove in covered pan at 350°.

title: nuts and bolts
directions: Melt margarine and mix all ingredients in large roasting pan. Cook at 250° for 2 hours, stirring every 30 minutes.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Cook all ingredients well.
Serve over hot rice with a hot loaf of bread and a salad and you've an excellent, quick dinner.

title: coconut cake
directions: Mix all ingredients, except coconut.
May add 1 cup fresh coconut, if desired.
Bake cake according to directions on box. (Don't follow directions on box, except for temperature.)

title: hamburger hot dish
directions: Mix tomato soup, corn and cheese together.
Place a layer of hamburger.
Place the tomato mixture on top; season.
Repeat layers.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.
Serves 8.

title: hot yeast rolls
directions: Combine milk, oil, sugar and salt in saucepan. Bring just to boiling point. Cool to lukewarm. Dissolve yeast in water. Add to lukewarm mixture. Add egg and flour. Knead well. Let rise in greased, covered bowl for 1 hour or until doubled in bulk. Shape into rolls. Place well apart on baking sheet. Let rise until doubled in bulk. Bake at 400° until golden brown. Yield: 1 1/2 dozen rolls.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Put all the ingredients in a pan and heat.

title: underwood picnic dip
directions: Mix all ingredients, except bell pepper, until smooth.
Add pepper.
Cover and refrigerate 1 hour.
Serve with crackers or veggies.

title: cajun sophisticated shrimp
directions: Saute shrimp and onions in margarine, 10 minutes.
Add mushrooms, cook 5 minutes.
Sprinkle flour, salt and pepper on top.
Stir in sour cream, cook gently on low fire until boil.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix together in a large casserole dish.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Drain pineapple.
Mix sugar, flour and juice.
Add pineapple, butter and cheese.
Mix well.
Pour into 2-quart casserole dish. Bake at 300° for 20 minutes and then at 350° for 20 minutes.
Put crumbs on top and brown lightly.

title: tom's mushroom pate
directions: Melt 2 tablespoons butter (or olive oil) in skillet and saute chopped mushrooms (2 to 3 minutes).
Add garlic and white scallion bottoms for 1 minute.
Add chicken stock and cook, stirring, over high heat until liquid is gone.
Cool to room temperature. Combine remaining butter or olive oil and cream cheese in mixing bowl.
Mix well.
Add cooled mushrooms and remaining ingredients. Put in covered bowl and keep chilled until ready to serve.
Serve with nice crackers.

title: banana split cake
directions: Have margarine and whipped topping at room temperature.
Melt 1 stick margarine and mix with graham cracker crumbs.
Place in bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan and press out until bottom is covered. Bake 5 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: beef and rice skillet
directions: Cover and bring to boiling. Simmer until cooked, about 15 minutes. Stir often.

title: grandma daigle's rice dressing
directions: Cook meat in oil in a large pot until brown.
Add onions, celery and bell pepper.
Reduce heat and cook until wilted.
Add water and add more water if needed to keep about the same amount of juice that you started with.
